name: Cozy & Colorful by Nature (Private Room)
description:
Up in the hill of Montjuïc (a mountain overlooking the city where Jewish people were forced to retire when they were thrown out of town), only 10 minutes by bus from Girona's beautiful Old Town.

Private oom with private bathroom and garden just for you! You also have a wood house in the garden where to store your bike and other sports equipment.

The space
YOU'LL HAVE ONE PRIVATE ROOM WITH A PRIVATE BATHROOM AND GARDEN JUST FOR YOUR USE - IT'S A SHARED APARTMENT, MEANING YOU'RE NOT RENTING THE FULL PROPERTY. WE LIVE HERE, TOO ;)

Cozy, Sunny & colorful apartment with a refreshing garden facing east where to chill out in the hot summer nights.

You will have a private room with a direct and exclusive access to the garden. It has a new very comfy bed (135cm) and you will have your own bathroom.

There is a closet in the room.

The apartment is in a lovely suburb area 2' walk to the entrance of a Natural Park with g
neighborhood_overview: Montjuïc is most likely the best neighborhood in Girona. We are up in a hill, only 15-20 minutes to the center of the city, and surrounded by Nature. it is very safe and quiet.
host_about:
It's hard to define oneself in such a narrow space. I think we people are really complex material. But since I guess it's good I say a bit, I would define myself as someone fascinated about living and getting to know both this planet and its inhabitants. I'm interested in serving people, especially, but not exclusively, my friends. I enjoy good food and if possible better company. My interests are broad and go from traveling, literature, creative writing, philosophy and body "care" to Buddhism.  I'm pushful, curious, a bit narcissist maybe, hahaha, and I guess I tend to dream pies in the sky far too often.

I am original Catalan, from lovely Girona - Costa Brava but I've lived abroad for many long periods: Miami, Dubai, Bali and Melbourne (Australia). My live partner is a lovely aussie-greek Personal Trainer named Stelios and, together we travel the world, when not working.

I like outdoors sports and I am addicted to mountain biking. I also like snowboarding, climbing, hiking, swimming ...; I also do some mat work like yoga and Pilates (of which I am a certified Instructor). 

I read a lot, books facinate me!!

I like to go out eating with my friends from time to time, although I am most of a day-creature and at night I like my sleep. I practice ioga and meditation and have a second level on Reiki. I'm a flexitarian (meaning I eat fish but not meat) by moral reasons and I enjoy a lot good food, if possible made with organic products. Music, all kind of music - depending on the moment - is very important to me; couldn't live without it. But my main and huge passion is travelling and meeting new people, travellers like me, or locals, and learn about them and their experiences in life. 

After many yearts working for others, I am now running my my own company. It's a fresh project dedicated to giving marketing and creativity services & solutions to other companies. I am also a teacher at the University of Girona, where I teach at the Faculties of Tourism and Economics and I run an international women's project named "Grace of No Age", devoted to mature women.

I am pretty busy however I don't complain, as I do what I like.

name: CAN FELIP - Ático loft del s.XVIII
description:
Magnífica casa de pueblo del siglo XVIII, ubicado en el centro de la villa de Palafrugell. La casa ha sido totalmente rehabilitada y dividida en 3 apartamentos “Can Felip”

The space
Magnífica casa de pueblo del siglo XVIII, ubicado en el centro de la villa de Palafrugell. La casa ha sido totalmente rehabilitada y dividida en 3 apartamentos “Can Felip”: -Piso 1: 156m2 + 33 de terraza. -Piso 2: 114 m2 + 70m2 de preciosa terraza soleada a 4 vientos. -Piso Ático: 76m2 + 47 de fabulosa terraza privada a 3 vientos.

Todas las habitaciones son grandes y frescas. Estas disponen de un ventilador en verano y calefacción en invierno.

“Can Felip” se encuentran situados en el centro del pueblo de Palafrugell a 50 metros de la Iglesia y del Mercado. En una zona tranquila con agradables vistas, situada en el corazón del “Baix Empordà” (Costa Brava).

A 3 Km de las fantásticas playas de Calella de Palafrugell, Llafranc y Tamariu.
neighborhood_overview:
Palafrugell se remonta al siglo X. El núcleo antiguo, conserva aún hoy algo de su trazado urbanístico medieval, encabezado por la iglesia de Sant Martí y formado por un conjunto de calles y callejones que configuran un gran centro comercial.

El máximo desarrollo de la localidad se produjo a finales del siglo XVIII con el inicio de la producción de tapones de corcho, hecho que aún hoy es evidente en la arquitectura local, con las fábricas de corcho y los edificios modernistas de la época. En el Museo del Corcho podrá conocer más a fondo esta industria.

A pie o en bicicleta, y a tu ritmo, explora tanto como desees, por la extensa red de 350km de caminos que hay actualmente en la Costa Brava, por los arrozales, o por las dunas de la playa de Pals a través de miradores privilegiados sobre el mar o bien por los yacimientos del Empordà... y, por supuesto, por los caminos de ronda: un impresionante paseo que acaricia el mar entre acantilados y que une todas las playas d

description:
Enjoy this spacious house in a quiet village only 10 minutes drive from Figueres and 20 minutes drive from the Costa Brava beaches

The space
The house is on a first floor. It comprises a big kitchen with dinning space, a dinning room, a living room, 4 bedrooms (one with a double bed), two bathrooms, and a little terrace. The kitchen overlooks the main square of the village with its church. There is normally plenty of parking spaces in the streets nearby the house. There is a bar and a shop next door where you can buy a bit of everything, from bread to a newspaper.

This house is situated in the very centre of a quiet village near Figueres, the Costa Brava beaches and the Pyrenees. Also close to Figueres, Girona and Barcelona, where you can enjoy day trips.

If your stay is less than 1 week, please request a price. It is difficult to cover all eventualities and lengths of stay with the automatic system. In July and August bookings run from Saturday to Saturday-

- rooftop terrace and solarium

The house is within 5 km of some of the best Costa Brava beaches, set in a quiet Mediterranean village in the Empordà with views of the Pyrenees, surrounding fields and neighbours wor
neighborhood_overview:
Torroella de Fluviá is a small peaceful rural village located a short drive from the beach (about 4 km). The immensely long beach of Sant Pere is famous for its beauty and (in designated areas) as a wind surfing, surfing, and kite surfing venue.

Sant Marti de Empuries offers a series of more protected coves adjacent to the Roman ruins of Empuries and the picturesque hamlet of Sant Marti.

Our house is a minute's walk from a great local shop. Fresh bread and newspapers in the morning, good local produce (including organic products) and most essential items. A village bar/restaurant in the town square offers great lunch options and small plates at all times. Or you can sit in the sun while the kids play safely.

The neighbouring village of Sant Pere Pescador offers a good range of shops including a largish supermarket. There are also restaurants for every pocket and taste in Sant Pere. See our guide book for some favourites.

Roads through the f
host_about: We have both been living in Barcelona for over 30 years and we met here in our adopted home. Girona and the Empordà are part of the attraction for us and we were very happy to be able to buy our beautiful village house in 2003. We are keen cyclists and get in some Touring every year in Ireland, France, and Spain. Our other passions are wine and food and having a place near the French border has allowed us to get to know the wonders of the wines of the south of France (Languedoc Rousillon). We like to travel simply so Airbnb is a perfect solution and we have been hosting on Airbnb and elsewhere for over 10 years with great results, meeting interesting people for all over the world.

neighborhood_overview:
The house is located in the old part of town, just 2 minutes away from the beach and high quality restaurants.
One minute away you will find the church plaza, where you can enjoy nice meals with a quiet and relaxing atmosphere, at the same time your kids play at the plaza without danger.
Just 2 minutes away, you will find a little supermarket and the commercial zone, where is difficult not to stop and watch the beautiful shops.

At the entrance level, a very nice suite with its private bathroom, and 2 large doublerooms with 2nd bathroom with same views. At the garden level, large livingroom with bar and its 28sqm porch. The space

Guest access

The swi
neighborhood_overview:
Close to Begur you'll be free to choose between the long Pals sand beach and the many beaches and calas of the Begur Cape (Sa Riera, SaTuna, Fornells, Aiguablava, ...) which are amongst the most beautiful of the Costa Brava. We recommend as well to explore the pathways that link them.
Diving (various marine reserves), nautic sports, tennis and various golf courses (one PGA) are available close by.
Gastronomy quality of the area is well known, and you'll find a large variety of restaurants in Begur and its surroundings.

name: Ecofriendly getaways in Costa Brava
description:
LA CASETA is an ideal combination for an enjoyable holiday, especially for those who love nature, organic food and bio-architecture.

The space
"LA CASETA ECOLÓGICA" has one bedroom with double bed, kitchen/living/dining room, bathroom with shower and a sofa-bed (2+1 people).
La Caseta is located along la CASA DE FANG which means the house of clay in Catalan. Clay is one of the basic materials we used to construct the walls, in the traditional "tapial" style used by the ancient iberians of this area. I live here together with Lluís Auquer who is an architect, specialized in the construction and restoration of old houses. Our house is a haven for lovers of "bio-architecture and is not for everyone.

We are located in Rupià, a quaint medieval town, 12km away from the coast and the hustle and bustle. Our house is located within 7000m2 of land, consisting of the local cork tree. We grow our own fruits and vegetables in our organic garden. From the house

description:

The apartment is distributed from a distributor hall with an old well, which gives way to the whole, with 5 bedrooms, 3 bathrooms, dining room, living room and a kitchen equipped with a terrace with wonderful views of the immensity of nature.

The space

We do not offer anything extraordinary, since everything here is quite natural, we will invite you to the castle and its history, to know the corners of the surroundings, waterfalls, ancient house in caves, the uniqueness of the "Bufadors" forest...

Welcome!

Guest access

neighborhood_overview: In the town of Llaés we are 12 inhabitants, and what we like the most about our neighborhood, the tranquility and harmony that is breathed, the green of the mountains with the contrast of the electric blue of the sky. We love quiet afternoons where just looking up you see eagles, owls at dusk, butterflies, hares, moles, foxes, and countless more neighbors running around the neighborhood!
host_about:
Hello!
 We love the rural environment and the variety of activities offered: hiking, mountain biking, climbing, and a lot more.
We are fortunate to be able to receive people from all over the world in this small and incredible X century castle.
Always there, 24 hours 7 days a week, we ensure that our guests feel like royalty!
 We hope you have the best experience during your stay :) Marc & Ginny

name: Can Portell by 123ole: the Pink Box 2 pers
description:
The space
Bed & Breakfast 123ole, Can Portell” has both the sea and mountains on its doorstep, is not far from the vibrant town of Girona, and only half an hour’s drive from the airport. Not only is it easy to get to, but Can Portell caters to everyone’s needs.
The house is an old masia farm and dates from 1690. The main building is surrounded by a beautiful plot of land with a swimming pool, stables, trees that provide shade and an original, abandoned corral where we now keep our horses. The house comes complete with a truly unique décor, intriguing corridors, steps, rooms aplenty and a charming veranda – the perfect spot for a morning coffee, for reading the papers and for surveying the garden. This is where you will be served breakfast, and the occasional dinner if you so desire. The shady area underneath the veranda, furnished with loungers, offers cool relaxation.
Each season here has its own charm and beauty, so our doors are open to guests all year round.

name: Quiet times by the riverside
description:
Stay in a historical building! Right in the Old Town, you will have shops, restaurants and walks literally round the corner. Very quiet, with wide views on the river. Parking is about 5 minutes walk. Long stays welcome. No late arrival fees.

The space
Days for a great break in the historical centre of a small pretty city!
The apartment is in the heart of the old town, on a privileged location: right in front of the riverside. So you'll see the birds fishing in the morning, and the sun sets will just be yours, on a huge 4 meters wide window on the river.
In addition to the views, the silence is one of the pros of the apartment; the river is very quiet, and as I live on the apartment below your you won't have parties every night (or you'll be one in it! :) )
The place has one big room; on one side the bed, very comfortable and wide, and on the other the sofa-bed and the computer. It doesn't feel small as the ceiling is very high, and a nice (sort of
neighborhood_overview: I believe we live in one of the best places in the world. It has the advantages of a city, but actually is is still a town- in the good way! Iis a lively area with many places to visit, shops, or simply walk around. I specially love the gardens around the city wall, 10 minutes from here. I deeply appreciate that cars are restricted in the area.
host_about:
I am someone who likes very different things, you will see. Let's start: I was born in a small town in l'Empordà, called Torroella de Montgrí. Those were also a mixture of happy and wild times, a bit like Amarcord from Fellini (watch it if you haven't).
Then I studied computer science in Barcelona, and a PhD with a part of it in London, about medical imaging.
In between something entered my life, for good: yoga: I started practicing and soon I was so pationated then when I finished my PhD it was obvious that becoming a teaching would be the best choice of my life.
So I practice yoga every day, and also: I love music, and I play myself the accordeon and the clarinet. Just as an amateur, but the pleasure of making music is amazing. I also like dancing, folk music and lately also Lindy Hop (Girona has a few places to dance if you are into it).
I like eating well and healthy. Not to much meat (I am sorry for those creatures we kill but sometimes it comes and I eat).
I like travelling, in all wild ways, but I am not a traveller that can tell thousands things! I participate as well in the couchsurfing project, from time to time- and when there isn't already someone at my place, a friend or a friend of a friend.
The apartment I rent, Girona Riverside, was planned to be for me as another floor was ment to be the yoga studio. However now I have another, bigger, place for yoga and I rent it. I hope you like it!
As a buddhist (if I can call myself that which I don't know) my motto would be to understand the sources of suffering, and enjoy immediate happyness.
Hola!Soy David!Soy profesor de yoga y os invito a una estancia estupenda en el centro de Girona en un apartamento con unas increibles vistas al rio!Naturaleza y silencio para tu felicidad!

We are Ana and Kristjàn and we’ve been offering accommodation in Tossa de Mar for over thirty years. Seven years ago, we were very happy to found Let’s Holidays.

The passion with which we’ve been working these past years has made us grow, and we now have a vast team of professionals working with us. 
With them, we will make sure to find the best option for you and to get you everything you will need during your stay :)

If there is something that we have learnt this past years is that we like to be treated the same way that we treat you. 
That’s where our philosophy comes from. We like to chat and we will try to get you anything that you need and find solutions to anything that you propose.

At the end, holidays should be exactly the way we want them, right?

We present some of our services :)

The Home Selector is the person who will help you choose the option most appropriate to your tastes. You will save time in searching and finding the best choice.

The Host is the person who will take care of you during the whole stay and try to find anything that you need with the help of the other hosts.

Let’s Holidays Home will be your second holiday home. A place where you will be able to meet with our Hosts, chat, have a glass of wine and listen to some live music.

We’ll love to meet you!

See you soon ;)

Tengo 50 años y administro mis propiedades como actividad principal. 
Mi último proyecto ha sido hacerme con la propiedad de una Masia en la frontera del Gironés con la Garrotxa, a 30 minutos de la entrada de Girona. 
Me ocupo del mantenimiento de la Masía, su jardín y bosque, me procuran trabajo de ajardinar, limpieza del bosque, cuidado del pequeño huerto (por ahora) además de ocuparme de las obras de restauración de la Masía. 
Aprecio de mis clientes que sepan valorar el comfort y la calidad de los espacios que me he dedicado a restaurar. Me tomo muy en serio el aspecto de dejar las viviendas en perfectas condiciones, con todos sus detalles, además de darles un estilo clássico y natural gacias a la ayuda de mi mujer Bea que tiene un buen gusto para los detalles.
Me gusta el orden y la limpieza, y espero de la gente que así lo sean. 
Somos una pareja que apreciamos tener gente de todas las edades. Apreciamos la gente que busca un sitio auténtico donde pasar unos días tanto buscando la tranquilidad como para festejar con amigos.

name: Together w family·friends in cozy apartment-lofts!
description:
Organize a holiday reunion together with family members or friends. We have 3 apartments for an independent stay use with central-heating for 3 fam. or 13 'pers. You can apart hire an extra separate large room having a wood stove celebrating a party.

The space
Can Banal is a former Catalan farmhouse called "masía" from the XVI century. Since 1987 it has been our home and camping business. Since 2012 we have been able to open up 3 holiday apartments on the upper floor that can be rented all 3 together for a group, specially 3 or 4 families "together but not mixed". The apartments can accommodate 3 '- 5' - 6 '= 14 persons in total. Besides there is a large room, beware rather rustic style, for a party event. We rent it out apart including a simple kitchen, wood stove with firewood and music-equipment. Consult us the price.

The apartments are independent multi space rooms containing bedroom, kitchen with dining area and bathroom. All have central heating
neighborhood_overview:
Can Banal is situated in the beginning of the Catalan Pyrenees, in a region called “Alta Garrotxa”. Located midway between the sea-shore (45 min) and the high mountains of the Pyrenees (1h) makes it possible for many types of day-trips.
Close to many interesting places of cultural, natural or gourmet aspects like Castelfullit de la Roca, Besalu, the Garrotxa Volcanic Park or Olot.
Within a 6 km drive, Sadernes is reached from where the wonderful trekking path towards Sant Aniol d'Aguja starts.

The landscape around Can Banal is peaceful and rural, with rivers and forests that changes colors depending on the season. In autumn there are varieties of mushrooms and in spring many types of orchids and butterflies to enjoy.

If you just decides to stay around in Can Banal you'll find enough to do for few days. Walk our own signed trails along water creeks, fields, forests, hermitage, farms and villages round us. We have mountain bike’s to rent and in a 25' walk
host_about:
Hola, we are Stendert & Maria

We live in Mas Can Banal for many years. Stendert, born '51, originally is from Breda-Holland, and Maria, born '66, is from Stockholm-Sweden, where her parents once had arrived from Spain. We enjoy very much living here in the countryside surrounded by hills, forests, and rivers. Halfway to the sea and to the high mountains.

We are accompanied by our daughter Saskia born '02 and Stendert's son - Luuk, born  '93, who works in our village and in their spare time help us.

Our professions are of the most diverse; Maria studied interior design and artistic glass techniques and Stendert studied to become a tropical agronomist and later carpentry. Probably this multifaceted mixture connects us with many diverse interests and activities, especially the maintenance of CB with its forest, animals, and agro-tourism.

We hope to be able to combine these aspects of us and make your stay as pleasant and memorable as possible. Together, we speak 7 European languages and understand a few more. We like very much to tell you about our favorite places, help you out for more personal advice and add if there is a special event going on.

  Welcome·Bienvenidos·Welkom·Benvinguts·Välmommen·Bienvenue·Willkommen

Hola somos Maria and Stendert

Vivimos en Mas Can Banal desde hace muchos años. Stendert, nacido '51, originario de Breda , Holanda y María, nacida '66, de Estocolmo- Suecia , donde sus padres una vez llegaron desde España . Nos gusta mucho vivir aquí en el campo, rodeado de colinas, bosques y ríos. A mitad de camino hacia el mar y la mitad del camino a las altas montañas.

Nos acompaña nuestra hija Saskia, nacida '02 y Luuk, hijo de Stendert,  nacido en el '93, que trabaja en nuestro pueblo. Ambos en sus ratos libres nos ayudan en diferentes tareas.

Nuestras profesiones son de la más diversa; María estudió diseño de interiores y técnicas de vidrio artístico y Stendert estudió para ser ingeniero agrónomo tropical y mas tarde carpintería. Probablemente esta mezcla multifacética , nos conecta con muchos diversos intereses y actividades, en especial el mantenimiento de CB con su bosque, los animales y el agroturismo.

Esperamos ser capaces de combinar estos aspectos de nosotros y como hacer que su estancia sea lo más agradable y memorable como sea posible. En conjunto, se habla 7 idiomas europeos y entender algunos pocos más. Nos gusta mucho que decir acerca de nuestros lugares favoritos, ayudará a cabo el asesoramiento más personal y añadir si hay un evento especial ocurre.

neighborhood_overview:
ABOUT OUR VILLAGE : LLAMPAIES

The small community of Llampaies is situated towards the east of the region, not far from Camallera (2 km), where all kinds of amenities are available. The surrounding countryside boasts gentle rolling hills, farmland and coniferous woodlands.

The tiny center of Llampaies is formed of typical local houses. The quarter around the church is the oldest part of the village. Around 100 meters to the north, is the smaller Vecindario del Puig, a group of houses, built in the 17th and 18th centuries. 200 meters from Vecindario del Puig is the Vecindario de los Masos. Some of the houses here date from the end of the 18th century, although the majority were built in the 19th century. There are around 100 people living in the center.

Me encanta estar en contacto con las personas, ayudarles en lo máximo que pueda y prestarles todos los servicios para que estén satisfechos. Después de 23 años de vivir en la ciudad de Barcelona, vivir aquí en una casa rodeada de casas medievales y campos es un cambio radical necesario para volver a disfrutar de la vida y la verdad muy bonito.

name: Casa Rural La Casanova de Beuda
description:
La casa se alquila entera, mínimo dos noches 430 Eu. independientemente del numero de personas. Situada en el Pre-Pirineo. Girona
Dispone de 2 h. matrimonio, 1 doble y 1 triple, 2 baños 1 aseo. Salón comedor gran cocina con chimenea, calefacción. Jardines que se funden en el campo.

The space
La Casanova fue construida a principios del siglo XX, en el año 1921. Recientemente, ha sido restaurada en piedra y madera, siguiendo el modelo original y la tradición arquitectónica local; y respetando así mismo, los colores preexistentes a su restauración.

description:
Exclusive rental property in the historical core of Girona

The space
Located in the heart of Girona's medieval quarter, inside the original city walls and overlooking Sant Domènec square, is the property Alemanys 5, whose original building dates from the sixteenth century.

Its recent restoration integrates old and new, with sober, clean lines that celebrate essential elements such as space, sunlight, shade, fire, stone, nature, water and silence.

The house is available to be rented as a whole unit, but it also can be divided into two independent apartments: "El Badiu" and "El Jardi".

"El Badiu" (The Veranda) is a 180 m2 duplex apartment equipped with a master suite and two junior suites, a fully equipped gourmet kitchen-dining space, spacious living room with fireplace and a spectacular sunny veranda terrace facing south, with exclusive views over the old quarter of Girona. Its capacity is up to 6 people.

The
neighborhood_overview:
The apartment is located in a family residence made of 2 small buildings.

The view from the terrace is exceptional because there is only a coastal trail between the apartment residence and the sea.

The apartment is on the fourth and last floor on the corner of the second building.

From the terrace, one can see all of Roses Bay (220 square km), and the Medes Islands located 21 km away, on the other side of the Bay.

And to go swimming, all you need to do is to walk down into the cove located in front of the residence.
host_about:
French and Canadian, married to a Spanish Catalan, with 3 daughters, including 1 American, I like to travel and meet people from all countries and different walks of life.

As a host, I am flexible and understanding as long as the guest respects my property and her/his engagements.

As a guest, I appreciate a caring host and I respect her/his property and leave up to my terms of the deal.

If any life motto, mine is: "keep on growing, with an open heart".

I do quite a lot of horse back riding, skiing and scuba diving.
I have a motor bike that I ride almost daily.

On the leisure side, I like to read in English, Spanish and French. 

I have eclectic tastes in music, movie and art, ranging from Mozart to Adele, Ingmar Bergman to Steven Soderberg, Michelangelo to Bastia.

I believe it is never too late to start new things in life and I am very close to my wife and family.

name: Casa Rabòs beautiful country house!
description:
Casa Rabòs is a traditional 17 century house,entirely renovated with all modern amenities and it is situated between Figueres (Dali's museum)and Llança/Rosas (sandy beaches) near Peralada (golf) in north Catalonia ,Spain.
Cadaquès, beautiful little harbour,with Cap de Creus,beautiful natural park are just half an hour drive.
Welcome.

The space
Casa Rabos is a traditional 17th century stone house, entirely renovated with all modern amenities and it is situated between Figueres and Llanca/Rosas near Perelada in north Catalonia, Spain.
The Orlina river runs down the village,and a beautiful bridgeunder which you can bathe.
You can treck around in the Albera natural park,discover dolmens, menhirs and the tipical méditerrannéen nature.

Perched in the renowned bay of Rosas close to the sea and entoured on one side by the Pyrenee mountains with 3,000 meter snowcapped summits. The climate is ideal with more than 300 days of sunshine per y
neighborhood_overview:
The house is on the outskirts of a charming medieval village at the foot of which the Orlina river flows.
The village is very peaceful, it has a small grocery store open in the morning only.
You can take beautiful walks, discover dolmens and menhirs in the middle of the surrounding garrigue, located in the Albera natural park.
host_about:
D'origine Québecoise, je m'occupe de cette merveilleuse maison de famille qui a au dessus de 400 ans ,et dans laquelle on fabriquait autrefois l'huile d'olive, le pain et le vin.
 Je partage cette occupation avec ma mère qui elle,est catalane d'origine et vit au Québec une grande partie de l'année.
J'ai suivi une formation en tourisme et aime partager ma passion pour la vie.
  Ma mère ,elle ,est massothérapeuthe et enseigne le Qi Gong, elle donne des ateliers d'initiation de cet art.
  Nous aimons toutes les deux recevoir les gens, qu'ils se sentent à l'aise et chaleureusement accueillis.
  Nous aimons aussi la nature, les plantes, la musique, la mer, la montagne, avoir du plaisir et partager tous ces merveilleux cadeaux que nous donne la vie;

name: Catalan Farmhouse Apartment with Mountain Views
description:
Can Cruanyes (complex of 4 private apartments with shared gardens) is a unique holiday escape, immersed in the rich culture and stunning scenery of the Spanish Pyrenees, and perfectly situated between the mountains and the exquisite beaches of the Costa Brava.

This Catalan farmhouse will be your private slice of rural bliss. We give you everything you'll need to feel at home, while still enjoying the comforts and ease of hotel-style convenience.

The space
From the ruins of the 400 year old farmhouse, three beautifully restored apartments have emerged, each retaining its own individual historic charm, while embracing some of the modern touches of interior design.

Secluded in twenty acres of peaceful woodland and paddocks, this Catalan farmhouse is a perfect destination for families and friends. The large swimming pool, play area and games garden all have views up to the imposing peaks of the mountains or down to the valley beyond.
neighborhood_overview: Can Cruanyes resides within the foothills of the Pyrenees where you can enjoy beautiful rural and mountain surroundings while remaining well connected to local amenities and the beaches of the Costa Brava. We are well connected also the local villages and towns including Tortella where you can buy all the basics including artesan bread and fresh fruit and vegetables. Besalu with many restaurants is only 10 minutes by car.
host_about: I'm Donny from Ireland and I enjoy meeting people from all over the world. I don't travel as much as before I had kids but meeting my guests helps me feel like I'm still travelling and learning about new cultures. I love helping people discover the area, and letting them in on the little local gems that I've discovered over the years.

name: Rural Hostel Mas Cadavall
description:
At Mas Cadavall we invite you to enjoy the simplest acts, to experience a slower pace that allows you to perceive the subtlety of the nuances of the changing nature that surrounds us and of the nature of oneself. We wish you a happy stay and coexistence!

The space
Mas Cadavall is a large, beautiful and simple white farmhouse surrounded by forest. It is located in a privileged place. Isolated and surrounded by nature and at the same time close to various locations. 15 minutes from Banyoles and Besalú. at 30min. from Girona, Olot and Figueres. And 45 minutes from the nearest beach (Sant Martí d'Empúries).

The accommodation belongs to the farmhouse, in which the hosts live and with whom the exterior of the house is shared.

The accommodation has a room with two bunk beds, an outside toilet, kitchen and porch / living room separated from each other. On the porch there is a sofa, table and an artisan wood oven.

Guest access
neighborhood_overview:
The hostel is located in a privileged natural environment! Close there are 2 rivers: the Fluvia (15 min. Walking), ideal for strolling along the beautiful path that borders the river and the Ser (20 min.), perfect for swinming and enjoying the journey.
For those of you who miss civilization, don't worry. 15min by car is Banyoles (a large town with supers, shops ... and the best ... a beautifu place for swinming and enjoy the walks it offers) and 30min. there is Girona, Figueres and Olot.
Besalú is at the gates of La Garrotxa, the beautiful medieval town just 15 minutes away. And nearby is also the volcanic area of ​​La Garrotxa.
And the sea? Well, the closest beach is in Sant Martí d'Empuries at 45min.
host_about: En Mas Cadavall vivimos Sergio, yo y nuestros dos hijos Abel (8años) y Shanam (4años). Dos niños muy sociales, con muchas ganas de compartir y jugar con los demás!

The space
We are in the heart of Costa Brava. Tamariu is the most exclusive and quiet beach in the coast.

Tamariu is situated in a small secluded bay between the towns of Begur and Palafrugell. Small coves set amongst rugged tree-lined cliffs, crystal clear water and beautiful beaches have made the area famous the world over for its beauty. Originally a small fishing village, Tamariu has not been over developed and has retained its identity and charm.

There are some new villas and apartments on the edge of the village and like everywhere the village center and beach gets busy in August, but you will find no high rise hotels or English pubs.

Amplio dormitorio c
neighborhood_overview: Situada en una urbanización tranquila, en la falda de una colina con vistas al mar y  rodeada de naturaleza,  donde viven vecinos del pueblo todo el año, a 5 minutos en coche de supermercados,  centro y playas.
host_about:
Hola, somos Manolo e Isabel, 
Desde Villalloret queremos  darles  la bienvenida. Este alojamiento que en principio nació para uso personal, para albergar reuniones familiares y vivir momentos únicos con familia y amigos, fue decorado con todo amor, por eso está lleno de pequeños toques con  sabor rural, para  los que utilizamos útiles de labranza propiedad de la familia.
Tiempo después vimos que por la dinámica de la vida diaria  no podíamos hacer uso de él y disfrutarlo nada más que en determinadas ocasiones,  y así fue como decidimos ponerlo a disposición para que otras familias pudieran disfrutarlo y pasar aquí  su tiempo de vacaciones, e incluso teletrabajar si este fuera su caso. 
Por eso nos  encantaría que pudieran conocer la Costa Brava desde  una perspectiva diferente, combinando el sabor de antaño, con lo actual, combinando el mar y la montaña, en un espacio para evadirse y reencontrarse con la naturaleza y con un ritmo más lento en su vida diaria más auténtico y sostenible. Pero a  la vez y cercano a lo urbano, a lugares de ocio y a las mejores playas de la costa Brava

neighborhood_overview: sin registro
host_about:
¡Hola, bienvenidos a nuestro perfil en Airbnb!

Nos hemos decidido a alquilar nuestra casa en Lloret de Mar, porque no la usamos lo suficiente, y dado que nos encanta viajar y apreciamos las numerosas oportunidades que ofrece el portal Airbnb, nosotros también lo utilizamos como huéspedes, nos gustaría poder ofrecer a los demás viajeros que conozcan esta bonita zona de la Costa Brava: ciudades costeras tan famosas como Lloret de Mar (5 min. en coche), que te ofrece un sinfín de posibilidades de diversión y buena comida, la ciudad medieval de Tossa de Mar (15 min. en coche), con su famoso castillo, o Blanes (15 minutos en coche) con sus famosas fiestas con fuegos artificiales. Nuestra casa está rodeada de muchas e increíbles playas como Canyelles, o la playa Llevadó, sin olvidar la playa de Santa Cristina, por citar algunos ejemplos. 

Nuestro deseo es que te sientas como en tu propia casa, y por eso hemos pensado en ofrecerte todo lo necesario para una estancia cómoda, lo más acogedora posible y que te lleves un bonito recuerdo. En nuestra casa encontrarás el relax y la tranquilidad que estás buscando, y podrás refrescarte en los días de calor en la maravillosa piscina de la urbanización. Estamos siempre a tu disposición para cualquier consulta, incidencia o sugerencia que surja durante tu viaje y estancia. Además, nos encantará ofrecerte recomendaciones e ideas sobre cómo pasártelo bien. 

Un abrazo, Ady y David

description:
50 m2 apartment located on the first floor. Has: 1 large bedroom with a double bed, 1 complete bathroom and a living area with a fully equipped kitchen and a sofa bed.
Our apartments are located in the beautiful Rectory of Regencos village, very close to begur with private garden and pool for the exclusive use of our guests.

The space
Spacious and fully equipped apartment of 50 m2 with views to our garden and pool. Perfect capacity for 2 adults and 2 child.

Apartment decorated by interior designer Anna Puig. Her vision has managed to turn our rooms into cozy and bright spaces, taking care of every detail accompanied by the practicality and comfort necessary to satisfy the needs of our clients.

Each apartment has:

• 50 m2

• 1 full bathroom with bathtub and shower

• Ai
neighborhood_overview:
Place that stands out for the tranquility of the town of Regencos at the same time that it is perfectly located, between the towns of Pals and Begur, just 10 minutes from the places of interest and the best beaches on the Costa Brava.
The perfect enclave for those who want to enjoy nature and the sea, in a dream environment.

The Rectoria de Regencós, as its name suggests, is located in the medieval town of Regencós, characterized by its tranquility. It is the ideal place for those who want to enjoy the village life characteristic of its people, its narrow and cobbled streets and surrounded by cultivated fields with views of the Quarlemany mountain.

It is located just 5 minutes by car from the best beaches such as Sa tuna, Sa Riera, Calella de Palafrugell, LLafranc, Pals and Platja del Castell.

description:

hijos.
La casa dispone de una distribución muy amplia y tiene todos los medios para poder disfrutar y sentirse como en casa, dentro de un ambiente acogedor y confortable.
Dentro del pueblo y a un paso de la casa caminando, hay de todo, supermerca
neighborhood_overview:
Es una autentica casa de pueblo ubicada en el casco antiguo de Pals, uno de los pueblos medievales con mayor encanto del Ampurdan. Tiene un premio de Bellas Artes.
Excelente comunicación con Barcelona, Gerona y Francia.
La casa esta ubicada en el llamado triangulo de oro, muy cerca de la playa de Pals a 4Km. así como de otras playas de aguas de color turquesa muy bonitas.
Hay innumerables y auténticos pueblos medievales para visitar, así como el Museo Dali ubicado en el pueblo de Figueras y el castillo de Pubol donde se encuentra enterrada Gala la mujer de Dali.
Pals esta a una distancia de 35 Km. de Gerona, una ciudad interesante para conocer ... barrio judío, catedral, etc...

Alegre y con muchas ganas de vivir y de disfrutar con mis amigos organizando eventos diferentes: comidas con vinito, ver películas, exposiciones de Arte, salidas en bicicleta...

neighborhood_overview:
ABOUT OUR VILLAGE : LLAMPAIES

The small community of Llampaies is situated towards the east of the region, not far from Camallera (2 km), where all kinds of amenities are available. The surrounding countryside boasts gentle rolling hills, farmland and coniferous woodlands.

The tiny center of Llampaies is formed of typical local houses. The quarter around the church is the oldest part of the village. Around 100 meters to the north, is the smaller Vecindario del Puig, a group of houses, built in the 17th and 18th centuries. 200 meters from Vecindario del Puig is the Vecindario de los Masos. Some of the houses here date from the end of the 18th century, although the majority were built in the 19th century. There are around 100 people living in the center.
host_name: Turisme Rural Can Gat Vell SCP
host_about: Haber realizado mi sueño de hace más de 20 años me hace muy feliz. Desde Mayo del 2013 vivimos mi marido y mis dos hijos Roger y Oriol en una masía rural Can Gat Vell, en un núcleo de 100 habitantes y a 2 km de Camallera. Me encanta estar en contacto con las personas, ayudarles en lo máximo que pueda y prestarles todos los servicios para que estén satisfechos. Después de 23 años de vivir en la ciudad de Barcelona, vivir aquí en una casa rodeada de casas medievales y campos es un cambio radical necesario para volver a disfrutar de la vida y la verdad muy bonito.

name: Els Racons del Fort: Castle in wine territory
description:
A stone building from 1694 having a shape of a fortified castle in the village of Capmany only 14 minutes away from Figueres and 26 minutes from Roses.

The fortified construction has a big garden, two terraces, and a covered outdoor space with a pergola. Swimming pool will be ready April 2022.

Capmany has more than ten wineries and your host Yves can teach you about local cuisine in form of: private dinners, hands-on cooking classes, or local experiences visiting wineries and food producers.

The space
The house offers a very unique feeling of the history that has happened inside and outside its walls. It has been renovated in a very respectful way and host Eli has decorated the house to make you feel good during your stay.

For family gatherings, it is possible to rent the apartments too and come together in the garden and pool.

There is also a huge diaphanous space very suitable for diverse activities such as retreats
neighborhood_overview: Capmany is a village with 614 inhabitants and more than 10 wine cellers. Beautiful walks can be done and the closest beach is a 26 min drive away.

name: Exclusive! only 45 m. from the sandy beach
description:
“Can Casellas” is an exclusive 18th. century village house in Sant Antoni de Calonge. The perfect location of our beach house in Costa Brava makes it the perfect place to stay whether you are visiting our area for leisure or business, as in our rental village house one finds exclusive serviced accommodation.

The space
The property has been carefully restored with charm, preserving as far as possible its original constructional features and preserving the architectural wooden beams, vaulted ceilings and centennial stone walls that gives warmth and authenticity to the house. The property has been refurbished without sacrificing comfort in order to offer the visitor a pleasant stay.
Distribution:
* Ground floor: the main entrance gives way to the living room opened on a nice dining room (for 10 pax) located under the original roof with Catalan vault.
From the entrance of the house, a long vaulted corridor leads the visitor to a beautiful well-equippe
neighborhood_overview:
Located in a very quiet area, the house is close to all shops, excellent restaurants and health services.
Every year the local beaches receive the blue flag granted by the European authorities for their uncontaminated crystalline waters.
host_about:
Hello! I'm so glad you are interested in renting one of my three properties here, in the heart of the Costa Brava. Each one has something special to offer our guests, a rustic village house with lots of character, a modern elegant family house and a stylish beach front apartment. 
What I love most about my place is the location, out of the ordinary and  literally steps away from supermarkets, restaurants, and the most beautiful beaches anywhere in Spain.
I work in a local real estate agency and I live only five minutes away from all the properties, I will help you make your stay perfect, just ask. I like to meet guests’ needs from before they even step foot in the door. Every year, at the end of the summer season, together with my husband, we plan a new improvements.

host_about:
NIÑOS, PERROS Y CINTAS DE VÍDEO

Mas Torrencito es una casa rural diferente. Una masía del siglo XV, restaurada con un estilo muy personal, y rodeada de campos, bosques y caminos que llegan hasta un río que merece ser escuchado al menos durante un rato. Su propietario, Miguel, se ha encargado de darle su propia personalidad a la casa durante siete años, creando diferentes rincones en los que puedes charlar con tu pareja disfrutando de una buena botella de vino mientras tus hijos juegan libremente por los alrededores, compartir con otros huéspedes costumbres y (Website hidden by Airbnb) de tus mascotas mientras ves cómo ellas disfrutan y se persiguen felices, o subir a la planta de arriba y escoger una de esas películas que tenías pendiente para hacerte un homenaje frente a una gran pantalla. Puedes hacer lo que quieras, porque en Mas Torrencito la libertad se respira a cada momento y en cada lugar.

Marcos, Manuela y Matías, tres de las mascotas de Miguel, son el auténtico espíritu de la casa. Esos tres perros deberían tener contrato indefinido y pensión vitalicia. Ellos muestran la casa a los nuevos huéspedes, sus 8 confortables habitaciones dobles y triples, los baños completos, el salón de techos altos y vigas de madera, el antiguo horno de pan, la sala de entretenimientos, la piscina y el jardín con mobiliario y juegos para niños. Pero también acompañan a los huéspedes durante los paseos, entretienen a mayores y niños con su buen carácter y sus ganas de jugar, y relacionan con las mascotas recién llegadas con paciencia, cariño y una gran amabilidad.

Mientras tanto, Miguel cocina. Y cómo cocina. Platos elaborados con productos de su propia huerta. Recetas que le chivan las madres de los propietarios de los restaurantes de los alrededores. Bizcochos con diferentes sabores, mermeladas, cereales, pan recién hecho y embutidos de la zona, una de las mejores del país en esta especialidad.

Mas Torrencito se puede disfrutar en pareja si te gustan los animales, ya que es una manera de poder disfrutar de su compañía siempre que quieras. También es un lugar ideal para niños, ya que rápidamente se enamorarán de Marcos, Matias y Manuela, probablemente la mejor buscadora de piedras del mundo. Y también es un lugar perfecto para visitar con tu propia mascota, disfrutar de unos días en la naturaleza y que los dos hagáis buenos amigos. En Mas Torrencito te sientes parte de algo, y cada visita es diferente a las demás.

El único problema de Mas Torrencito es que obliga a volver. Yo ya lo he hecho, y no será la única vez.

Hiking

neighborhood_overview:
We are about two kilometers from the village of Cistella. It is a small village of farmers and ranchers, welcoming and full of traditions. And although we have a reputation for being hard workers, always have time to chat with friends and a good celebration!.
In the village we have a small school, a church, a small grocery store (Lydia and Montse), the village café (The Society) is, and a good restaurant (Badó Restaurant), plus a wonderful environment to walk and contemplate dreamy landscapes.
host_about:
A mi marido y a mi nos gusta vivir en el bosque, su serenidad y frescura es nuestra energía. 
Yo siempre les digo a mi familia que soy como un nomo, pero que de vez en cuando necesito visitar a mi amigo el mar.
Puede sonar cursi, pero así es. 
Por eso este lugar donde vivimos es mágico.

Vivimos entre montañas en un precioso enclave,  pero tenemos a un paso magnificas playas donde disfrutar en verano y pasear en invierno. ¡ Qué más podemos pedir!. 
Juntos, nos ocupamos de la finca, sus animales, el huerto, la casa...
¡Nos encanta mimar cada detalle para que las personas que nos visitan puedan sentirse como en la suya propia y puedan así disfrutar de este lugar tan maravilloso!.

Os recibiremos encantados.
¡Bienvenidos al Mas Campmol"

Charo

host_about:
Hello!!
 
My name is Javier, and although I'm originally from Girona, I've been living in Barcelona for the past 25 years, so I know the city and its surroundings quite well.
 
Traveling is one of my favourites hobbies. I love getting to know different cultures and people from around the world. I had the chance to visit many countries, either for fun or for professional reasons, since my last job was as a publisher for trade magazines.
 
I started the business of rental apartments “The Vintage Rentals”  because as a tourist, I lived first hand the benefits of living a local experience wherever I go, and I know other people search the same type of authentic vacations. This is how I got into the this business and now I have apartments in the best areas of Barcelona with all the necessary facilities for an affordable price.
 
I invite you to come and discover a different and unique experience of Barcelona and all its beautiful locations and sites!
 
For further details, do not hesitate to contact me.
 
Javier
The Vintage Rentals

host_about:
Soy una mujer mediterránea que no podría vivir sin la luz del sol, la buena comida ni muy lejos del mar . Me gusta escribir, leer, la música y el buen cine. Y nadar en las playas de Palamós,  donde he pasado los veranos desde  mi infancia. 
Tengo tres maravillosos hijos: Carola  es músico profesional, Estela es pintora, y Eugeni , el pequeño de 10 años que quiere ser actor.
Con Jaume , mi marido, y con los hijos nos encanta viajar. Amigos europeos nos han hospedado en su casa (Paris, Bremen, London...)igual que nosotros les recibimos en la nuestra. Hace dos años que practicamos el intercambio simultaneo de casa . 
Nos encanta la gente y las tertulias después de una buena comida. 
Estamos muy orgullosos de nuestra segunda residencia y queremos compartir el placer de una estancia reparadora en l'Empordà, una de las zonas mas agradables del Mediterráneo.

neighborhood_overview:
Palafrugell se remonta al siglo X. El núcleo antiguo, conserva aún hoy algo de su trazado urbanístico medieval, encabezado por la iglesia de Sant Martí y formado por un conjunto de calles y callejones que configuran un gran centro comercial.

El máximo desarrollo de la localidad se produjo a finales del siglo XVIII con el inicio de la producción de tapones de corcho, hecho que aún hoy es evidente en la arquitectura local, con las fábricas de corcho y los edificios modernistas de la época. En el Museo del Corcho podrá conocer más a fondo esta industria.

L´Escala offers various activities and areas which can be enjoyed with children. The beaches of L´Escala are characterised by their fine sand and shallow waters, which means that they are ideal for children. host_about:
Hola, we are Stendert & Maria

We live in Mas Can Banal for many years. Stendert, born '51, originally is from Breda-Holland, and Maria, born '66, is from Stockholm-Sweden, where her parents once had arrived from Spain. We enjoy very much living here in the countryside surrounded by hills, forests, and rivers. Halfway to the sea and to the high mountains.

We are accompanied by our daughter Saskia born '02 and Stendert's son - Luuk, born  '93, who works in our village and in their spare time help us.

Our professions are of the most diverse; Maria studied interior design and artistic glass techniques and Stendert studied to become a tropical agronomist and later carpentry. Probably this multifaceted mixture connects us with many diverse interests and activities, especially the maintenance of CB with its forest, animals, and agro-tourism.

We hope to be able to combine these aspects of us and make your stay as pleasant and memorable as possible. Together, we speak 7 European languages and understand a few more. We like very much to tell you about our favorite places, help you out for more personal advice and add if there is a special event going on.

  Welcome·Bienvenidos·Welkom·Benvinguts·Välmommen·Bienvenue·Willkommen

Hola somos Maria and Stendert

Vivimos en Mas Can Banal desde hace muchos años. Stendert, nacido '51, originario de Breda , Holanda y María, nacida '66, de Estocolmo- Suecia , donde sus padres una vez llegaron desde España . Nos gusta mucho vivir aquí en el campo, rodeado de colinas, bosques y ríos. A mitad de camino hacia el mar y la mitad del camino a las altas montañas.

Nos acompaña nuestra hija Saskia, nacida '02 y Luuk, hijo de Stendert,  nacido en el '93, que trabaja en nuestro pueblo. Ambos en sus ratos libres nos ayudan en diferentes tareas.

Nuestras profesiones son de la más diversa; María estudió diseño de interiores y técnicas de vidrio artístico y Stendert estudió para ser ingeniero agrónomo tropical y mas tarde carpintería. Probablemente esta mezcla multifacética , nos conecta con muchos diversos intereses y actividades, en especial el mantenimiento de CB con su bosque, los animales y el agroturismo.

Esperamos ser capaces de combinar estos aspectos de nosotros y como hacer que su estancia sea lo más agradable y memorable como sea posible. En conjunto, se habla 7 idiomas europeos y entender algunos pocos más. Nos gusta mucho que decir acerca de nuestros lugares favoritos, ayudará a cabo el asesoramiento más personal y añadir si hay un evento especial ocurre.

name: Space Oasis - a tranquil and stylish retreat.
description:
Space Oasis is your haven of peace and quiet just a stones throw away from the beautiful beaches and bustling towns of the fabulous Costa Brava - a truly welcoming escape for friends & family to settle back, relax and unwind - hammock in the garden, a dip in the pool, fire pit BBQ, dinner & drinks on the terrace and total privacy as the space is all yours. Bliss!

The space
Space Oasis Holiday Villa is the perfect destination for groups of up to 12 people looking for somewhere a little bit special. We had a lot of fun creating the 'Pop Art' guest accommodation and love sharing our distinctive home with appreciative and laid-back friends from all over the globe.

Our living spaces are split into sections all accessible from a large central courtyard with 100 m2 terrace & 10 x 5 m swimming pool. The main guest house has 3 bedrooms, 2 bathrooms and a lovely spacious open plan kitchen/diner/living area with a wall of glass doors opening out to the terrace
neighborhood_overview: The setting is really special and unique. We enjoy lots of peace, quiet and tons of privacy but are just minutes away from some of the most stunning old towns and fabulous beaches in Europe. Pals old town is truly unique with narrow stone streets and a multitude of great restaurants and shops and Begur, Girona and Barcelona are of course bucket list places to visit.  If action and activities tickle your fancy then there is fab scuba diving on the Illes Medes a few minutes drive away plus skiing in the Pyrenees, road and mountain biking, great walking routes and beaches & sparkling little coves to die for all up and down the coast.
host_about:
Welcome to our Space Oasis! My name is Amalia, I am English/Canadian and my husband Dani is Russian. We met here on the Costa Brava, have lived here for almost 15 years. We speak EspanglishRuss together!

I work from home whereas Dani manages a super yacht in Barcelona and is often out 'at sea'. We both enjoy travelling and finding adventure when we can doing outdoorsy stuff like motorbiking or cycling; on-and-off road, horse riding and long dog hikes, but more often than not we're both working or relaxing in the garden at home. Well, to be honest, usually Dani is doing the gardening whilst I practise juggling, hula hoop, poi - or whatever is the latest skill I'm learning off YouTube!
 I'm a passionate animal lover and have 2 dogs, 8 cats and 1 horse. When I'm relaxing I love to just hang out with my animals and read a book. Guests have full access to my large library of books. Quite a few are beach-read best sellers - perfect for holidaymakers.

As we are often out-and-about our good friend Amber Jane will help you with  enquiries and bookings in the first instance and I will meet you when you arrive at Space Oasis Holiday Villa.

I will be here to help you get settled in but once I give you the keys my house is yours to enjoy in your own way. 

I like to share my house with good people , all I ask is that you respect my belongings and we both respect each others privacy. Other than that: 
Eat, Drink, Swim and Make Merry!

Lo hicimos  para uso de nuestra familia en vacaciones  hasta mi jubilación, cuando la pusimos en el (Website hidden by Airbnb) gusta caminar largos recorridos (llevo hechos más de 12000 Km por caminos de Santiago) la música (buena oferta en temporada en esta zona) la buena cocina y las buenas bodegas (oferta excelente en la zona) la naturaleza,y quienes en ella viven,entre ellos naturalmente el ser humanos,por encima de todo. El Serradell is an old "masia" (Catalan country house) which has been divided into two 2-storey appartments for 4/ 6 PAX each.
El Serradell is located in a magnificent remote outdoor setting, on a large estate with spectacular views overlooking the Catalan Pyrenees and the Garrotxa to the south. The house is 2hrs away from Barcelona, 1hr away from Girona, Figueres and the French border.
Access through 12km of forest road in good condition, you'll have to drive slowly.

The space
Typical "masia", or Catalan country house, dating back to the 10th century, but totally renovated in style and comfort.
This is your place if you are looking for nature, quiet and the best comfort.
The house is totally disconnected from the grid, and uses solar power and biomass for electricity and heating. Water supply from the nearby spring.

Guest access
Each appartment has an independent entrance and independent outdoor areas. The only shared

neighborhood_overview:
Cerdanya is a mountainous region with a high flat only because it is one of the wider valleys of Europe, between the Moixeró and the Pyrenees. In Cerdanya can find scenic beauty and diversity that make it unique.

Time in this region is variable, but mostly sunny throughout the year. The slopes have a high high mountain climate, while the lower slopes and plains enjoy a continental Mediterranean climate prone mountainous, with cold winters and cool summers.

In Cerdanya can enjoy variety of outputs, meadows, forests, beech, mountain ranges, massive rivers, lakes, peaks, a unique ... that offers a wide range of possibilities.

neighborhood_overview:
Palafrugell – Costa Brava
A pocos quilómetros del mar y la montaña, Palafrugell es un municipio de la comarca del Baix Empordà, en plena Costa Brava, en el que puedes encontrar la tranquilidad del mundo rural o el movimiento de un importante destino turístico.
Rodeado de naturaleza puedes descubrir las calas más representativas de la Costa Brava como Calella, Llafranc, Tamariu y Agua Xelida y a la vez practicar excursiones por el macizo Les Gavarres, el GR-92 por los caminos de ronda de la Costa Brava o por las vías verdes del municipio.
Palafrugell es perfecto para disfrutar en pareja, familia y amigos.
host_about: Soy madre de dos niños y profesora de yoga. Vivo en la casa restaurada de mis abuelos, y después de unos años viviendo en ciudades grandes he vuelto a mis orígenes para así poder darles a mis hijos la calidad de vida que se merecen. Disfruto mucho de la naturaleza que hay en este entorno maravilloso que es l'Empordà.

name: El Molí d' en Solà. Golfes Oest PG 204
description:
Charming appartment in an ancient mill-farmhouse in a green peaceful valley, between the Costa Brava and the Pyrinees. Perfect place for a relaxed holiday in the country.

The space
Our house, El Moli d'en Solà, is a Catalan farmhouse situated in a privileged environment for its beauty and peacefulness. It dates back to the fourteenth century. The house is surrounded by meadows and forests and the river that moved the mill is clean and perfect for swimming. If you find it too cold you can also bathe in the pool.

Guest access
The house has a large communal green area with playground
Each unit has access to its own BBQ and shared pool (open from June 1 to September 31).
The old mill and a small collection of antique farm tools can be visited.
We also have a small farm where children can meet our chickens, ponies, pigs, donkeys ...

neighborhood_overview:
The house is at the bottom of a valley in a rural area with few isolated farmhouses. It is a green and quiet corner, away from the madding crowd but only 5 minutes from the village.
We are in the region of La Garrotxa, which is famous for its volcanoes, the Fageda d'En Jorda and medieval villages like Santa Pau, Besalu. It is an excellent starting point for trips to the Costa Brava or the Pyrenees, as we are between the two sites.

We are Ana and Kristjàn and we’ve been offering accommodation in Tossa de Mar for over thirty years. Seven years ago, we were very happy to found Let’s Holidays.

The passion with which we’ve been working these past years has made us grow, and we now have a vast team of professionals working with us. 
With them, we will make sure to find the best option for you and to get you everything you will need during your stay :)

If there is something that we have learnt this past years is that we like to be treated the same way that we treat you. 
That’s where our philosophy comes from. We like to chat and we will try to get you anything that you need and find solutions to anything that you propose.

At the end, holidays should be exactly the way we want them, right?

We present some of our services :)

The Home Selector is the person who will help you choose the option most appropriate to your tastes. You will save time in searching and finding the best choice.

The Host is the person who will take care of you during the whole stay and try to find anything that you need with the help of the other hosts.

Let’s Holidays Home will be your second holiday home. A place where you will be able to meet with our Hosts, chat, have a glass of wine and listen to some live music.

We’ll love to meet you!

See you soon ;)

neighborhood_overview:
Llafranc es una entidad de población del municipio de Palafrugell, comarca del Baix Emporda en Cataluña. En 2009 tenía 316 habitantes. Llafranc es una de las pedanías costeras de Palafrugell, situada en plena Costa Brava, una localidad pintoresca y que conserva el antiguo encanto de los pueblos de la zona antes de la llegada del turismo de masas. Pueblo situado sobre una costa rocosa, junto a otro núcleo costero y turístico como Calella de Palafrugell. Junto a Llafranch se encuentra el faro de San Sebastián, con un magnífico mirador en su cima.
Cuando lo visites te enamoraras de Llafranc...

description:
This is a spacious house with uninterrupted views of the stunning Mediterranean for people who want fun and exploration but value comfort and relative peace when they get back from their excursions.

It is light, spacious and very comfortable, with a/c, high speed, unlimited wifi and well-equipped kitchen.

The shared pool is very large - for swimming in, not splashing, and never crowded.

We use Maremar ourselves and want to keep it like a home. You will feel like our personal guests!

The space
Maremar is our holiday home not "a rental". Everything is designed with our own comfort in mind - from the extra comfortable beds and bedding to the A/C and unlimited wifi to the well equipped kitchen to the fact you will not have to go shopping for loo rolls and tea bags as soon as you arrive!

We have one of the largest houses in our community, which means you will not be cramped.

Our town is one of the very best on th
neighborhood_overview:
The beauty of Sant Feliu de Guixols is that it is a prosperous Catalan town visited by the well-healed of Barcelona and France. It is not a town that relies on packing visitors together like sardines and offering them a uniform touristic experience.

It has all of the best resort amenities but has not had to go "down market" to attract visitors and therefore attracts people who are genuinely interested in a Catalan experience (although the inhabitants do speak many languages).

You will have access to many beautiful coves, stunning beaches and all of that, but also history, first class gastronomy and fantastic art such as the three Salvador Dali properties.

You can spend the day on the beach or exploring the marina or the fishing port. You can enjoy first class shopping and night life. But then you can come "home" to relative peace and tranquility at Maremar.
host_about:
I am a semi retired company director and chartered accountant who has escaped to travel and have fun!

I love good company, food, wine, music, experiences and kind thoughtful people.

My wife and I delight in helping people to have really memorable holidays and experiences - we get a real buzz out of it!

neighborhood_overview:
Can Banal is situated in the beginning of the Catalan Pyrenees, in a region called “Alta Garrotxa”. Located midway between the sea-shore (45 min) and the high mountains of the Pyrenees (1h) makes it possible for many types of day-trips.
Close to many interesting places of cultural, natural or gourmet aspects like Castelfullit de la Roca, Besalu, the Garrotxa Volcanic Park or Olot.
Within a 6 km drive, Sadernes is reached from where the wonderful trekking path towards Sant Aniol d'Aguja starts.

The landscape around Can Banal is peaceful and rural, with rivers and forests that changes colours depending on the season. In autumn there are varieties of mushrooms and in spring many types of orquids and butterflies to enjoy.

If you just decides to stay around in Can Banal you'll find enough to do for few days. Walk our own signed trails along water creeks, fields, forests, hermitage, farms and villages round us. We have mountain bike’s to rent and in a 25' wal
host_about:
Hola, we are Stendert & Maria

We live in Mas Can Banal for many years. Stendert, born '51, originally is from Breda-Holland, and Maria, born '66, is from Stockholm-Sweden, where her parents once had arrived from Spain. We enjoy very much living here in the countryside surrounded by hills, forests, and rivers. Halfway to the sea and to the high mountains.

We are accompanied by our daughter Saskia born '02 and Stendert's son - Luuk, born  '93, who works in our village and in their spare time help us.

Our professions are of the most diverse; Maria studied interior design and artistic glass techniques and Stendert studied to become a tropical agronomist and later carpentry. Probably this multifaceted mixture connects us with many diverse interests and activities, especially the maintenance of CB with its forest, animals, and agro-tourism.

We hope to be able to combine these aspects of us and make your stay as pleasant and memorable as possible. Together, we speak 7 European languages and understand a few more. We like very much to tell you about our favorite places, help you out for more personal advice and add if there is a special event going on.

  Welcome·Bienvenidos·Welkom·Benvinguts·Välmommen·Bienvenue·Willkommen

Hola somos Maria and Stendert

Vivimos en Mas Can Banal desde hace muchos años. Stendert, nacido '51, originario de Breda , Holanda y María, nacida '66, de Estocolmo- Suecia , donde sus padres una vez llegaron desde España . Nos gusta mucho vivir aquí en el campo, rodeado de colinas, bosques y ríos. A mitad de camino hacia el mar y la mitad del camino a las altas montañas.

Nos acompaña nuestra hija Saskia, nacida '02 y Luuk, hijo de Stendert,  nacido en el '93, que trabaja en nuestro pueblo. Ambos en sus ratos libres nos ayudan en diferentes tareas.

Nuestras profesiones son de la más diversa; María estudió diseño de interiores y técnicas de vidrio artístico y Stendert estudió para ser ingeniero agrónomo tropical y mas tarde carpintería. Probablemente esta mezcla multifacética , nos conecta con muchos diversos intereses y actividades, en especial el mantenimiento de CB con su bosque, los animales y el agroturismo.

Esperamos ser capaces de combinar estos aspectos de nosotros y como hacer que su estancia sea lo más agradable y memorable como sea posible. En conjunto, se habla 7 idiomas europeos y entender algunos pocos más. Nos gusta mucho que decir acerca de nuestros lugares favoritos, ayudará a cabo el asesoramiento más personal y añadir si hay un evento especial ocurre.

name: Cosy Modern Family Apartment with Mountain Views
description:
Can Cruanyes (complex of 4 apartments with shared gardens) is a unique holiday escape, immersed in the rich culture and stunning scenery of the Spanish Pyrenees, and perfectly situated between the mountains and the exquisite beaches of the Costa Brava.

The space
From the ruins of the 400 year old farmhouse, three beautifully restored apartments have emerged each retaining its own individual historic charm while embracing some of the modern touches of interior design.

Can Cruanyes (Alzina) is a unique holiday escape, immersed in the rich culture and stunning scenery of the Spanish Pyrenees, and perfectly situated between the mountains and the exquisite beaches of the Costa Brava.

The vaulted ceilings and original window frames are reminders of the farmhouse as it once was, while the large window into the open plan kitchen/livingroom gives a lovely vantage point onto the adjacent woodland of holm oak, pine and hackberry trees.

Seclu
neighborhood_overview:
Can Cruanyes is set within the Alta Garrotxa. Nature will be your neighbour while you are here. Immerse yourself in the forests, mountain views and valleys.

However we are well connected to local villages and towns including Tortella and Besalu. In Tortella you can buy all the basics including artesan bread. Besalu in only 10 mins in the car and has some wonderful restaurants.
host_about: I'm Donny from Ireland and I enjoy meeting people from all over the world. I don't travel as much as before I had kids but meeting my guests helps me feel like I'm still travelling and learning about new cultures. I love helping people discover the area, and letting them in on the little local gems that I've discovered over the years.

neighborhood_overview:
El pequeño municipio de Guils de Cerdanya está situado en los Pirineos gerundenses, en el valle de La Cerdanya, cuya capital es Puigcerdá, en la que el viajero encontrará todos los servicios, tales como tiendas, Hospital, cines, etc.
Guils de Cerdanya es un pueblo pequeño y muy tranquilo. Solo hay un restaurante, El Picarol, que abre los fines de semana, en Navidad y durante el mes de agosto. La estación de esquí nórdico Guils-Fontanera pertenece al municipio, y se accede por la carretera que sube desde Puigcerdá.
host_about:
Soy ingeniero de profesión, lo que hace que sea muy meticuloso y perfeccionista. Soy extrovertido, me encanta conocer nuevas gentes y culturas de las que aprendo muchas cosas.
Una de mis pasiones es viajar, que comparto con mi mujer. Juntos hemos visitado muchas de las hermosas ciudades europeas. Me encanta conocer mundo, soy un enamorado del continente africano, he viajado por diferentes países de ese continente.
Practico varios deportes pero sobre todo que sean al aire libre: esquí, tenis y golf, pero mi gran pasión es la pesca a mosca.
Me encanta el cine, las obras maestras las veo varias veces para no perder los detalles, y la lectura de novelas.

name: Beautiful apartment along the beach, pool, parking
description:
Spacious apartment in Roses, with view from the terrace over the beach and the swimming pool in the garden.
The apartment is very comfortable distributed. It has a large living with sofas and a dining table for 6. The Kitchen has all the utilities to have a comfortable holiday. There a 2 comfortable bedrooms with 2 bathrooms. All the rooms have windows and view over the back garden or the front garden with the swimming pool.
It has good quality wifi, TV satellite and a private parking.

The space
The apartment is decorated in light and sunny colours. The apartment is about 70 m2 and the terrace an extra 10 m2.
The very spacious living room with American kitchen is directly connected to the beautiful terrace where you can enjoy a delicious meal with a view over the pool in the garden and the sea in front of you. In the salon there are sofas, a table for 6, a television and internet. There are 2 bedrooms, 1 with a double bed and tele and an en-suit
neighborhood_overview:
The apartment is in a very quite neighborhood. Nearby there is a small supermarket with fresh bread. In front of the apartment on the promenade there are restaurants to enjoy breakfast, lunch or diner. The beach is just 2 steps from the apartment.
You can walk in the neighborhood, or rent bikes.
Also you could visit, Cadaques, Figueres (Dali), Castello de Empurias or Girona.
host_about:
I live in Roses with my husband and 2 children since 2006. It is a lovely place to live, always something to do and many days of the year you can find us playing on the beach, biking at the boulevard or walking in the nearby mountains. 
We would be glad to welcome you to our apartments.

Es un apartamento de un solo espacio con un sofa cama y unas literas con cortina de separacion, pequeña cocina y baño Tambien tiene un pequeño jardin.

name: MASIA AISLADA EN LA ALTA GARROTXA
description:
Se alquila Masía aislada del S XV totalmente restaurada conservando los elementos originales, pero con las comodidades actuales. La casa está situada en el Espacio Natural de la Alta Garrotxa a 12 Km del pueblo de Tortellà por un camino rural en buenas condiciones (20 mints en coche).

The space
Lugar para desconectar de la rutina, autentica Masia catalana del año 1403 rodeada totalmente de naturaleza y grandes bosques, donde podrás estar integrado en un paisaje Único y totalmente aislado.
La casa es auto sostenible y ecológica: se calienta con caldera de leña se ilumina con energía solar y el agua brota directamente de unas fuentes.
Junto a la casa está la Masoveria y la casa de los propietarios que se dedican a la ganadería ecológica.
Con una superficie de 220 metros y capacidad para 8 personas dispone de 4 habitaciones dobles y dos baños completos. Cocina con chimenea, Salón de 55 metros, pequeña capilla y zonas exteriores con piscina de mader

description:
Apartamento a primera línea de mar, muy luminoso y acogedor, ideal para parejas, hay otra mini habitación con una litera, hay un lavabo con bañera. La estancia mínima es de 5 días.

The space
Tiene vistas al mar y al río Muga que es una zona de reserva natural de l'empurdá, las vistas son impresionantes, el piso es muy luminoso y se encuentra a 50m de la playa y paseo marítimo

Other things to note
se pueden hacer paseos en barquita por los canales,de nuestra pequeña venecia,paseos en bici y si eres mas atrevido y te gusta el riesgo saltos de paracaidismo,anímate es muy divertido. Y la novedad túnel de viento y sino simplemente,relax,sol y playa y a disfrutar de las vacaciones

name: Mas del siglo XVII ENTRE MAR Y MONTAÑA COSTA BRAVA
description:
Mas Arnau es una impresionante masía para disfrutar con tu familia o amigos, ubicada en uno de los lugares más solicitados del Alt Empordá, con más de 3 hectáreas de jardín, frutales y una gran piscina adaptada para los más pequeños (disponible del 15 de abril hasta el 31 de octubre)
La Masía dispone de grandes espacios de vida para relajarse y desconectar del ritmo acelerado de la ciudad. A pocos km, Golf Torremirona, Figueras (Museo Dalí),playas de la bahia de Roses, Cadaqués y Cap de Creus.

The space
Cuenta con una superficie útil de más de 1000 m2 distribuida en dos plantas con capacidad para 15 / 16 personas. En la planta baja encontrarás 4 salones con confortables sofás, chimenea, una cocina independiente (totalmente equipada) y 1 baño. Desde esta planta se accede al gran porche y la piscina. En la primera planta, 4 Suits . En la segunda planta, una master suit de 60m2 con 5 camas individuales y 1 doble. Se alquila con todos los enseres ( sábanas, toa
neighborhood_overview: Cistella es un pueblecito encantador, de vida tranquila y familiar. Se ha convertido en un punto estratégico por su cercanía a Figueras (Museo Dalí), a los campos de Golf de Torremirona y Perelada, además si te gusta la aventura podrás tirarte en Paracaídas en Ampuria Brava, practicar el senderismo y disfrutar de los placeres del mar ( buceo, navegar en velero, pescar, etc...) en las playas de la Costa Brava. Un lugar apacible para descansar.

name: PROMO LAST WEEK AVAIL COSTA BRAVA 16 to 23 July
description:
Exclusive apart on the seafront in a residential complex, overlooking the Gulf of Roses and the Pyrenees, fully equipped for 4 persons with swimming pool, playing room, parking, concierge and close to the most charming villages of Emporda. With a tourist license, it is only available for a few weeks a year, those that we leave free, and the guests who repeat year after year.

The space
The apart is located in an exceptional resort on the sea and overlooking the Pyrenees, in the Alt Emporda area of fishing villages and coves with clear water as Cadaqués, Roses, Port de la Selva, Begur and small and charming medieval villages like Madremanya, Pals, Peratallada or Foixá, castles and quiet and green surroundings, just 3 km from the center of L'Escala, but located in a sea environment and forests and very quiet. (see .kmz locator (website hidden) Earth.)

By the magic of his views and the Emporda region of Catalunya -the Tuscany I love the sunrises and sunset
neighborhood_overview:
The neighborhood, like L'Escala in gral., have 95% a profile family holiday with children or single adult couples who love nature, good food and history of the area and outdoor sports.

Due to the absence of public transport, we dont´ have adolescent groups alone, those who prefer other cities such as Lloret de Mar or Roses.

The small island located opposite is a well known center for diving and snorkelling, and very close, 500 mts has a beach in Cala Montgo with sand if you come with little children.

If you enjoy sailing and windsurfing, you have at the port two schools that teach and rent small boats like 420, hobbycat, H20, Laser and other sailboats.

Also in the area there are golf courses and trails for hiking and other sports related to nature.

If you like Dalí, 20 km in Figueres is Dali Museum with much of his work.

The weather is usually sunny in July and August, with an average temperature of 26º and a good pleas
host_about:
Hola, mi nombre es Bruno, soy arquitecto y mi pareja Luz se desempeña como profesional en el área del turismo. Somos 4 si contamos a Nachito, de casi 4 años, y a Valentina de 19 que viaja con nosotros una vez al año.
Vivimos y trabajamos en BCN y disponemos en alquiler sólo por un tiempo muy corto y en verano, de un hermoso apartamento completamente equipado para 4 personas en L´ Escala, Costa Brava a 40 km de Francia, en primera línea de mar, con unas vistas increíbles al Golfo de Roses.

El resto del año tratamos de disfrutarlo nosotros, es realmente nuestra segunda casa, y es un placer salir de BCN poniendo rumbo al Empordá a relajarnos cada vez que podemos.

Somos viajeros mas que turistas, y eso, entre otras cosas, nos define.
