name: Mas Quatre Camins.
description:
Nineteenth century cottage located in an exceptional place. You can enjoy the wonderful views of the pastures and forests that surround it, as well as easy access to the most important places and the best beaches of the Costa Brava.

The space
This nineteenth century Catalan cottage, available for ten people, has the best amenities and comfort to make you feel at home. On the ground floor, there is a big living room with two different chilling areas. from wich you can acces to the toilet and to a double bedroom. At the other end of the floor there is the kitchen, fully equipped with a large solid wood table and a fireplace.
The first floor has a small lounge, four double bedrooms and three bathrooms. From every room you can enjoy wonderful views of the fields and the woods surrounding the house.
And, if the cozy inside of the house has dazzled you, the outside is even better!
In the garden you can prepare a delicious barbacue in the summer porch,
neighborhood_overview: The house is located in a road within 2 kilometers from the village of Viladasens and Sant Jordi Desvalls. It's a quiet place where you can enjoy the silence, fresh air and the sights  reach you until the last meadow. A beautiful landscape, where small forests offer you nice walks next to the Ter river.
host_about:
Somos una familia que reside en Barcelona.
Somos amantes del viaje, de los buenos paisajes y vivir con harmonía y felicidad.
Nos fascina conocer culturas y mundo.

name: Charming farm cottage near our organic cellar!
description:
Lovingly restored stone cottage next to our Catalan farmhouse at the foot of the Albera mountains.
Beside a small river, 2.5km from town, with private patio and garden, amid vineyards, dolmens and olive groves.

We make ORGANIC WINE!
Near Figueres and the "Costa Brava".

The space
The cottage is separate from the main farmhouse, with its own entrance, private garden and large patio with views of the river and mountains.
YOU WILL BE SURROUNDED BY CALM AND QUIET!
Restored with passion and charm, with all the details to make you feel at home!
The two single beds in one of the bedrooms can be joined to make a double.
Small, fully-equipped kitchen stocked with all the basic essentials for cooking meals (oil, salt, sugar, honey, coffee, tea...)
We offer catered lunches and suppers: please let us know in advance.
official rural house n. PG-936

Guest access
Just outside the cottage, you can enjoy a p
neighborhood_overview:
The cottage is 2.5km from the village of Sant Climent Sescebes.
The village has shops and basic services (bank, pharmacy...)
The Albera Natural Park is within walking distance, with hiking trails and the chance to explore Requesens Castle.
The natural parks of Cap de Creus and Aiguamolls and city of Figueres are all within a 20-40 minute drive.
host_about:
Som la Barbara i en Joan Carles. Tenim una petita finca a peu de l’Albera on cultivem vinyes i elaborem vi natural i ecològic.
El paisatge és característic per la presencia de dòlmens i menhirs i d'un espai protegit.
Cuidem les vinyes velles i les noves petites parcel·les amb la passió per aquest indret, l'esforç i la tenacitat que ens fan forts i units, la gana de protegir i mantenir el territori que vam heretar.
En 2016 vam arreglar la que ara és la nostra caseta rural, a on us acollim per donar-vos un espai i uns moments de tranquil·litat i natura amb la possibilitat de conèixer la nostra feina i tot el món dels productors ecològics de la nostra zona.

name: BEACH APARTMENT 2rooms with PARKING
description:
Nice and cozy apartment, very bright, with terrace and excellent location, just 1 minute away from the beach, supermarkets, restaurants and more. Privileged by being in a quiet street, where nightlife noises won’t be a problem.

The space
That apartment has 2 bedrooms, 1 bathroom, American kitchen equipped with washing machine and living room with access to a little terrace, prepared for you to spend time outdoors..
It has private parking lot in the same building.
There is room for 4/5 people, with the following distribution:
-Bedroom with double bed.
-Bedroom with bunk bed for 2 people. In case you are 5 people, and if it’s not an inconvenient for you, we have a mattress under this bunk bed, that you can put on the flor, for the 5th person.
We have cribs and high charis if needed. Please requested it in advance. Costs 25€ for the hole stay.

Guest access
ADDITIONAL SERVICES

- Cot and high chair.
- Cle
neighborhood_overview:
The apartment is located in a centric area, but at the same time is quiet and everything is near.
Just 1 minute away from the beach, a big supermarket and restaurants.
Less than 3 minutes away you will reach the commercial street, with another big supermarket, excellent shops where you can find fish, perfumes, clothes, presents and mucho more.
Just 5 minutes away, you will find the old part of town, the walled city called “Vila Vella”. A really beautiful place

Tossa is a beautiful and quiet town, with a lot of charm. Ideal to travel with your couple, family or with the kids.
It is one of the most beautiful town in all Costa Brava, where you can steel feel the little old town atmosphere and where is not allowed to build tall buildings.
Besides enjoying the beaches, there are a lot other things to do. For example: walk around the old and narrow streets from the walled town "Vila Vella", go the the lighthouse and relax at the "Bar del Far", while you e
host_about:
We are Ana and Kristjàn and we’ve been offering accommodation in Tossa de Mar for over thirty years. Seven years ago, we were very happy to found Let’s Holidays.

The passion with which we’ve been working these past years has made us grow, and we now have a vast team of professionals working with us. 
With them, we will make sure to find the best option for you and to get you everything you will need during your stay :)

If there is something that we have learnt this past years is that we like to be treated the same way that we treat you. 
That’s where our philosophy comes from. We like to chat and we will try to get you anything that you need and find solutions to anything that you propose.

At the end, holidays should be exactly the way we want them, right?

We present some of our services :)

The Home Selector is the person who will help you choose the option most appropriate to your tastes. You will save time in searching and finding the best choice.

The Host is the person who will take care of you during the whole stay and try to find anything that you need with the help of the other hosts.

Let’s Holidays Home will be your second holiday home. A place where you will be able to meet with our Hosts, chat, have a glass of wine and listen to some live music.

We’ll love to meet you!

See you soon ;)

name: 10th century medieval Castle
description:
In the Ripollès region, between rivers, valleys and mountains, the ancient Castle of Llaés (10th century) stands splendidly. A unique place, of exceptional beauty, where absolute tranquility reigns in the middle of an exuberant nature.
The Castle has been fully renovated for the comfort required by the facilities for rural tourism, with 8 rooms, 5 with a double bed, and 3 with two single beds. It has a living room, dining room, kitchen, 4 bathrooms, garden and terrace.

The space
The Llaés Castle is a project of reform and maintenance of this national cultural asset that, by force of spirit and the guests from all over the world who come to visit us, can continue its journey.

Guest access
Currently the fortification retains the physiognomy of a castle, the homage tower, the parade ground, and the religious enclosure with a garden area, the small cemetery, and the church of San Bartolomé, in a marked Romanesque style.

Other
neighborhood_overview: In the town of Llaés we are 12 inhabitants, and what we like the most about our neighborhood, the tranquility and harmony that is breathed, the green of the mountains with the contrast of the electric blue of the sky. We love quiet afternoons where just looking up you see eagles, owls at dusk, butterflies, hares, moles, foxes, and countless more neighbors running around the neighborhood!
host_about:
Hello!
 We love the rural environment and the variety of activities offered: hiking, mountain biking, climbing, and a lot more.
We are fortunate to be able to receive people from all over the world in this small and incredible X century castle.
Always there, 24 hours 7 days a week, we ensure that our guests feel like royalty!
 We hope you have the best experience during your stay :) Marc & Ginny

Hola!
  Somos una pareja joven, amamos el entorno rural y la variedad de actividades que ofrece: senderismo, ciclismo de montaña, escalada y mucho más.
  ¡Somos afortunados de poder recibir personas de todo el mundo en este pequeño e increíble castillo del siglo X!
  Siempre allí, las 24 horas, los 7 días de la semana, nos aseguramos de que nuestros huéspedes se sientan como la realeza.
  ¡Esperamos que tengas la mejor experiencia durante tu estancia! :) Marc y Ginny

name: BEGUR. Country house in Costa Brava
description:
Restored house from 1.870 in the center of Begur one of the most beatiful villages in Costa Brava.

The space
The house was an old little factory to produce corks for wine bottles. It was refurbished as a summer residence for our family and friends.
We kept all the old elements from the past, old Catalonian ceiling, wooden doors, and old tile floors, opening big windows to make the place special and full of sun and light.
We love cooking, so the kitchen is perhaps bigger than normal, with all the equipment to prepare fresh food just bought in the local farmers.
It has a little garden of about 25m2. A special place to relax under the shadow of a jacaranda tree which gives flowers once a year (in June).

Guest access
The house was fully prepared as a summer residence 4 years ago. You will find 3 double rooms with two double beds and a double bunk. One of the rooms 100% independent on the lower floor close to the garden like a
neighborhood_overview: This is a quite pedestrian street with just one entrance. Only 5 lovely houses, our is the coziest one ;) . Good relationship with our neighbourhood, you will feel like a local soon. Some British, Spanish, Welch...
host_about:
...Life is short so I feel I need time to enjoy it as much as possible: lot of energy and creativity, the best friend of my friends, and a father 100% love.
Thus our house is always plenty of good friends who likes enjoying the good life that Costa Brava offers us, love wine, cooking, running  and staying on the beach till the sun goes down everyday.
...Dicen que la vida es corta. Es por eso que la quiero vivir tanto como pueda. Me considero positivo, creativo, el mejor amigo de mis amigos, y un padre envidiable con mi hijas.
Es por esto, que nuestra casa está siempre llena de buena gente, que le gusta la buena cocina, el buena vida en general, el deporte, aprovechar las puestas de sol para despedir el dia...y dar gracias al que está por llegar....

name: Nice studio vintage in Old Town
description:
Our cozy studio is equipped with everything you need to feel comfortable during your stay. It's an ideal place for couples, located in the old city center, near the main tourist attractions and the best restaurants

Due to the current situation, caused by COVID-19, we have taken extreme higienic measures to clean and disinfect in order to avoid any risk of infection and we have installed a remote system that will allow you to dispose of the key autonomously, without to have physical contact.

The space
First of all, we want to tell you that our studio is located on the first floor without a lift, so when you arrive, you will have to climb about 15 steps.

Once inside, you will see that the distribution consists of an open space with living room, dining room, office and kitchen, a bathroom and an attic with a double bed.

The balcony is a viewpoint of one of the most emblematic streets in the city. Here you can spend pleasant moments r
neighborhood_overview:
The studio is located in the old town, exactly in the historic center of Girona (Cort reial street). It is a charming area, close to the major historical sites and museums as well as the best restaurants in town.

At two minutes walking there is a supermarket where you can find all that you can need to cook your meals.

On the other hand, is a 10 minutes walk from the shopping area of the city and the bus and rail station. Do not forget that Girona has great attractions as a city, but it is also the starting point for visiting other inescapable places as the Costa Brava, the Dali Museum in Figueres, the charming villages of the Empordà or the Pirineus. As well, high-speed rail takes you in Barcelona in only 30'.
host_about:
Hello! 
We are Jaume and Marta. We live with our children in a small village half an hour from Girona, where we enjoy nature and peace of mind. 
We work as professor and librarian and we like to travel and discover curious and original spaces at the places we visit. 
We invite you to enjoy the small studio we have in the historic center of Girona and we promise to share with you everything we know of the city to make your stay very special and memorable.

name: CAN FELIP - Apartamento 1 (s.XVIII)
description:
Magnífica casa de pueblo del siglo XVIII, ubicado en el centro de la villa de Palafrugell. La casa ha sido totalmente rehabilitada y dividida en 3 apartamentos “Can Felip”

The space
Magnífica casa de pueblo del siglo XVIII, ubicado en el centro de la villa de Palafrugell. La casa ha sido totalmente rehabilitada y dividida en 3 apartamentos “Can Felip”: -Piso 1: 156m2 + 33 de terraza. -Piso 2: 114 m2 + 70m2 de preciosa terraza soleada a 4 vientos. -Piso Ático: 76m2 + 47 de fabulosa terraza privada a 3 vientos.

Todas las habitaciones son grandes y frescas. Estas disponen de un ventilador en verano y calefacción en invierno.

“Can Felip” se encuentran situados en el centro del pueblo de Palafrugell a 50 metros de la Iglesia y del Mercado. En una zona tranquila con agradables vistas, situada en el corazón del “Baix Empordà” (Costa Brava).

A 3 Km de las fantásticas playas de Calella de Palafrugell, Llafranc y Tamariu.
neighborhood_overview:
Palafrugell se remonta al siglo X. El núcleo antiguo, conserva aún hoy algo de su trazado urbanístico medieval, encabezado por la iglesia de Sant Martí y formado por un conjunto de calles y callejones que configuran un gran centro comercial.

El máximo desarrollo de la localidad se produjo a finales del siglo XVIII con el inicio de la producción de tapones de corcho, hecho que aún hoy es evidente en la arquitectura local, con las fábricas de corcho y los edificios modernistas de la época. En el Museo del Corcho podrá conocer más a fondo esta industria.

A pie o en bicicleta, y a tu ritmo, explora tanto como desees, por la extensa red de 350km de caminos que hay actualmente en la Costa Brava, por los arrozales, o por las dunas de la playa de Pals a través de miradores privilegiados sobre el mar o bien por los yacimientos del Empordà... y, por supuesto, por los caminos de ronda: un impresionante paseo que acaricia el mar entre acantilados y que une todas las playas d
host_about:
Como representantes de una pequeña empresa familiar que se dedica a la restauración de Casas y Apartamentos nos complace mucho integrarnos en la comunidad Airbnb para poderos ofrecer nuestras viviendas, que esperamos sean el futuro de magníficas experiencias para nuestros invitados...

------------------

As partners of a small family business dedicated to the restoration of properties, we are delighted to become Airbnb members to offer our Houses and Apartments, which we hope will be the future of great experiences for our guests...

description:
Duplex-Atico Penthouse with community POOL, roof TERRACE with wonderful VIEWS over the Bay of Rosas, Empuries and the old town up to the port and Montgó. The fully equipped apartment accomodates 4 people - It has 2 double-bedrooms with bathroom en-Suite. AC and heating.
Oldtown and beaches 5 min walking.
No parking problems with a garage!

The space
My wonderful view- penthouse with 2 bedrooms, balcony and roof terrace accomodates 4 people.
On the first floor you have one bedroom with bathroom and the livingroom, dinnertable and fully equipped kitchen. Upstairs you find the main bedroom with a 160cm bed and a bathroom. From there you exit onto the roof terrace with sunbeds, table and BBQ - and amazing views :-)
For direct refreshment you can jump in the pool.
No parking problems with a garage!

5 min. walk to the oldtown, 5 min walk to the lovely beaches of Empuries (just take the steps at the end of my road, or the new pano
neighborhood_overview:
- Quiet street, 5 min walk to old town and Empuriesbeaches (direct steps at the end of my road leading down to the beaches ad the beautiful walkway to Sant Marti d'Empuries).

- Around us:
Have a walk to the roman-greek Ruins or the little village Sant Marti dEmpuries, passing by the Hostal Empuries – it’s worth a look inside! Its terrace or the “Chiringuitos” invite to take a aperitif on the way to the village or just during your stay on the beaches. The space
CASA 2 “CAN JANOT” (Disponible) Capacidad: 8 personas más una cuna/ cama de 60x120cm (para bebes o niños de hasta 6 años)

PRIMERA PLANTA

1. Sala anexa con llave y salida directa al gran Jardín trasero de la casa (1.500 m2) para 2 pax TV.
2. Salón con mesa para 8 comensales al lado de la chimenea, sofá y butaca individual para leer, juegos de mesa, televisión, calefacción y TV. El Salón tiene salida directa al jardín principal, de unos 2.500 m2

neighborhood_overview:
Este magnífico lugar ubicado en Rocabruna está rodeado de montañas, riachuelos, prados donde pastan vacas, ovejas, caballos y cabras, y dónde podemos encontrar espectaculares bosques, árboles frutales, setas e infinidad de rutas para descubrir y explorar. En los alrededores de Rocabruna podemos encontrar desde cuevas naturales hasta una mina abandonada de cobre, piedras semipreciosas y plata, y que según cuenta una leyenda, parece ser que estuvo habitada por gnomos, así como una historia medieval de un amor imposible - al estilo de Romeo y Julieta -entre los hijos de dos señores feudales.

Hay constancia escrita de su existencia desde el siglo IX. Es un pequeño y armonioso ejemplo del Románico Pirenaico con su gran castillo de defensa en ruinas, su iglesia del siglo Xll y un núcleo de casas antiguas a su alrededor.

Las tres casas están situadas en Rocabruna (Camprodón), que es un pueblo de origen medieval y uno de los rincones más bellos y vírgenes del Pirineo Ca
host_about:
Somos muy familiares, nos gusta leer cerca de un buen fuego, con una buena comida a la brasa de leña, somos amantes de los animales. Es por eso que queremos que otras personas puedan disfrutar de nuestras casas.

neighborhood_overview: It is an "isolated" house with more than 70 hectares of land, where puppies and people can walk to our langillo ... Surrounded by woods and rivers ... a quiet place where silence is only broken by the singing of the Little birds We are 2 kms from Bascara, 14 from Figueres (museum Dali) 19 from the beach (La Rubina, an immense beach where you can go with your pet), 40 from France, 14 from Besalú and Banyoles, ....
host_about:
NIÑOS, PERROS Y CINTAS DE VÍDEO

Mas Torrencito es una casa rural diferente. Una masía del siglo XV, restaurada con un estilo muy personal, y rodeada de campos, bosques y caminos que llegan hasta un río que merece ser escuchado al menos durante un rato. Su propietario, Miguel, se ha encargado de darle su propia personalidad a la casa durante siete años, creando diferentes rincones en los que puedes charlar con tu pareja disfrutando de una buena botella de vino mientras tus hijos juegan libremente por los alrededores, compartir con otros huéspedes costumbres y (Website hidden by Airbnb) de tus mascotas mientras ves cómo ellas disfrutan y se persiguen felices, o subir a la planta de arriba y escoger una de esas películas que tenías pendiente para hacerte un homenaje frente a una gran pantalla. Puedes hacer lo que quieras, porque en Mas Torrencito la libertad se respira a cada momento y en cada lugar.

Marcos, Manuela y Matías, tres de las mascotas de Miguel, son el auténtico espíritu de la casa. Esos tres perros deberían tener contrato indefinido y pensión vitalicia. Ellos muestran la casa a los nuevos huéspedes, sus 8 confortables habitaciones dobles y triples, los baños completos, el salón de techos altos y vigas de madera, el antiguo horno de pan, la sala de entretenimientos, la piscina y el jardín con mobiliario y juegos para niños. Pero también acompañan a los huéspedes durante los paseos, entretienen a mayores y niños con su buen carácter y sus ganas de jugar, y relacionan con las mascotas recién llegadas con paciencia, cariño y una gran amabilidad.

Mientras tanto, Miguel cocina. Y cómo cocina. Platos elaborados con productos de su propia huerta. Recetas que le chivan las madres de los propietarios de los restaurantes de los alrededores. Bizcochos con diferentes sabores, mermeladas, cereales, pan recién hecho y embutidos de la zona, una de las mejores del país en esta especialidad.

Mas Torrencito se puede disfrutar en pareja si te gustan los animales, ya que es una manera de poder disfrutar de su compañía siempre que quieras. También es un lugar ideal para niños, ya que rápidamente se enamorarán de Marcos, Matias y Manuela, probablemente la mejor buscadora de piedras del mundo. Y también es un lugar perfecto para visitar con tu propia mascota, disfrutar de unos días en la naturaleza y que los dos hagáis buenos amigos. En Mas Torrencito te sientes parte de algo, y cada visita es diferente a las demás.

El único problema de Mas Torrencito es que obliga a volver. Yo ya lo he hecho, y no será la única vez.

The house is in an area between pine trees, overlooking the sea and has a priv
neighborhood_overview: The house is completely independent and located in a convenient spot, very close to some of the most beautiful beaches such as Sa Tuna, Sa Riera, Aiguablava or Aiguafreda. The house is in front of the "Camí Vell" of Sa Tuna, a forest path that goes from Begur to Sa Tuna. It is a pleasant path that allows you to walk to the town or to Sa Tuna. You can walk to Sa Tuna (about 10/12 minutes) and the town of Begur (18m). By car it takes 2 minutes to Sa Tuna and 5 minutes to Begur. A drive to Barcelona takes about 1:30 h and to Girona about 45 minutes, both worth day excursions! Not more than 20 minutes away you have many nice villages to visit and even Dali spots.
host_about: Vivimos en Barcelona con nuestros hijos pero siempre que podemos nos escapamos a la Costa Brava. Nos encanta ir a la playa para hacer snorkelling y padel surf, relajarnos y disfrutar de los muchos restaurantes y rincones que ofrece la costa.  Esperamos que disfrutes igual que nosotros!

name: Habitación privada en Casa Medieval  del Siglo XII
description:
Viaje a la época medieval.
Game of Thrones stage. Dentro escenario de Juego de Tronos.
Casa de piedra muy grande del siglo XII, reformada. Habitación privada para 2 personas ( cama de matrimonio ) con baño privado.
En pleno barrios medieval y judío, edificio adosado a los Baños Arabes, al lado de la catedral, rodeada de iglesias, conventos, jardines, plazas y paseos que rodean la catedral de Girona.
Restaurantes y bares con encanto al lado. A 4’ del Sunset Jazz Club y de bares de copas.

The space
Es una vivienda única por su belleza y singularidad, considerada patrimonio de la ciudad. Primeros cimientos datan del S XII.
Rodeada de la catedral, la colegiata de Sant Feliu, de la iglesia de Sant Lluc, de los Baños Arabes y de 2 conventos de monjas.
Zona peatonal, tranquila y a 4/5 minutos de plazas, restaurantes y bares con ambiente todo el año.
A 3' club de Jazz con encanto y con conciertos de alto nivel todo el año, Sunset J
neighborhood_overview:
La casa esta ubicada al lado mismo del edificio de los Baños Arabes y la pequeña iglesia de Sant Lluc, entre la Catedral y la Colegiata de Sant Feliu.
Al lado mismo están los jardines del Paseo Arqueológico q llevan a la Muralla desde la cual se puede ver toda la ciudad y el paisaje.
El Barrio Judio está al lado con su museo y antigua Sinagoga.
El Museo de la catedral y el claustro de la misma son visitas obligadas al igual q el Museo de Arte, el de Historia de la ciudad o el de arte romanico de Galligans si se dispone de más tiempo.
El Museo del Cinema és también muy interesante.
Las callejuelas, plazas, bares típicos y de diseño al igual q todo tipo de restaurantes están a 4' / 7' de la casa.
Al estar en el corazón del "Barri
Vell " todo está al lado.
host_about:

host_about:
Bonjour,
Mon nom est Olivia Sales et je suis née le 18 mai 1981.
Je vis dans le sud de la France à Perpignan dans les Pyrénées-Orientales.
Les Pyrénées-Orientales sont un département français situé dans le sud de la France, dans le nord de la Catalogne, à la frontière avec l'Espagne, dans la région du Languedoc-Roussillon.
Je vis entre la mer Méditerranée et les Pyrénées.
C'est une belle région baignée par le soleil. Il y a de nombreuses activités à faire qu'elles soient sportives, culturelles ou de détente.
Voyager est ma grande passion, j'ai visité de nombreux pays:
L'Espagne, le Portugal, l'Italie, la Hongrie, la Roumanie, l'Irlande, la Slovénie, la Grèce, Malte, la Sardaigne, les Baléares, les îles Canaries, le Royaume-Uni, la Turquie, Cuba, l'île de la Réunion, les États-Unis et les îles d'Hawaï.

Area:
The villa is located in the Mas Nou Mountain, just up from Platja D'Aro (5min drive to the city center). As common in the area, the streets leading to the Villa are not very well maintained and slow driving is recommended to avoid damages to the car.

Region:
Costa Brava is a 220km long coastal region of northeastern Spain in the province of Girona. The Costa Brava stretches from Blanes, northeast of Barcelona, to the French border. Its rich culture includes picturesque fishing villages such as L'Estartit and Tamariu, hidden beaches and bays, some of which are only accessible by boat. The average air temperatures range between 24°C and 28°C in summer and in spring between 17°C and 25°C. The water temperature is comfortable for swimming from May 20°C until October and in summer goes up to 24°C.

neighborhood_overview: sin registro
host_about:
Hola! Som la Laia i en Jofre. Som de Tossa, on vivim i tenim la nostra família. Treballem en el món de la cuina en diferents projectes, un d’ells a Tossa mateix, la Braseria Pini, un restaurant que sense perdre les arrels familiars aposta cada any per una carta més actual. Gaudim menjant bé, ens encanta descobrir llocs i provar nous plats. Fa més de 8 anys que allotgem hostes a Airbnb llogant apartaments i ben aviat també la Baby Blue, una “glamper van”. Ens agrada conèixer i compartir experiències amb altres persones que, com a nosaltres, els agrada viatjar i conèixer nous racons de món. Tossa és el nostre racó, un poble de la Costa Brava que ens dona molta vida a l’estiu i molta pau a l’hivern.
No dubteu a demanar-nos recomanacions.
Fins aviat!

name: www·empuriaholidays·com - Farigola
description:
Magnífica casa de planta baja de 2 habitaciones y cocina separada. Casa a 3 vientos equipada con chimenea, patio delantero y una amplia zona ajardinada en su contorno. Situada en una calle sin salida, muy tranquila, ideal para alojarse familias con niños. Puertas de cristal correderas y puertas exteriores de aluminio, totalmente plegables. La casa es totalmente plana, sin escalones. El exterior está equipado con barbacoa, hamacas, sombrilla, mesa y sillas de jardín.

The space
Magnífica casa de planta baja y jardín situada en una calle muy tranquila, sin salida. La casa dispone de un comedor con chimenea, aseo con ducha, cocina separada y 2 habitaciones (una doble y la otra con dos camas individuales).

La cocina dispone de utensilios para 6 personas y está equipada con lavavajillas, encimera de gas con 4 fuegos, extractor, nevera con congelador, cafetera eléctrica y microondas.

El acceso al comedor es por 2 puertas correderas acristaladas

neighborhood_overview:
The apartment is in the first line for sea views and at the same time, right next to the “Vila Vella”, the walled city.
For those who don’t know Tossa, you don’t have to worry about noises for being at the first line. Not much later than midnight all restaurant are close and the street is really quiet.
Distance from the beach is less than 1 minute. There is a little supermarket a minute away and another one, a little bit bigger 4 minutes away. The biggest is 10 minutes walking.
This zone belongs to the old neighborhood, so you will find narrow streets, nice shops and much more.

Tossa is a beautiful and quiet town, with a lot of charm. Ideal to travel with your couple, family or with the kids.
It is one of the most beautiful town in all Costa Brava, where you can steel feel the little old town atmosphere and where is not allowed to build tall buildings.
Besides enjoying the beaches, there are a lot other things to do. For example: walk around the ol
host_about:
We are Ana and Kristjàn and we’ve been offering accommodation in Tossa de Mar for over thirty years. Seven years ago, we were very happy to found Let’s Holidays.

The passion with which we’ve been working these past years has made us grow, and we now have a vast team of professionals working with us. 
With them, we will make sure to find the best option for you and to get you everything you will need during your stay :)

If there is something that we have learnt this past years is that we like to be treated the same way that we treat you. 
That’s where our philosophy comes from. We like to chat and we will try to get you anything that you need and find solutions to anything that you propose.

name: Private villa with pool & sea view for families
description:
Villa with great sea views overlooking the valley of Palamos and St Antoni de Calonge. We accept families and guests 30+.
Top floor: kitchen, living room, WC, roof terrace and small balcony.
Lower floor: 4 bedrooms w/ double beds - two new bathrooms.
Large terraced garden with pergola and generous pool area.

Quote from previous guest: "French riviera meets vintage Hollywood Hills."

The space
Villa Mariposa is very private - set on the end of the street Carrer Om in the urbanization of Rio de Oro - located on the hillside of Calonge. The house offers a spectacular view over the valley of Calonge and bay of St Antoni de Calonge/Palamos.

The house have a large landscaped garden with pergola for comfortable shade and a pool area with space for 8 pool beds.
The partly refurbished (2013) terraced house is 190+ sqm over two floors. Upper floor with a brand new kitchen, a large roof terrace, spacious living room area with
neighborhood_overview:
The house is located in the quiet urbanization Eio de Oro - only 10 minutes with car from the ocean front. Two good supermercados in the village of Calonge - only five minutes with car. Eurospar the closest one and Suma by the entrance to the village.
There is a great restaurant in the urbanization - Restaurant Rio de Oro.
host_about:
Villa Mariposa is our dream project. After searching for both the right area and then the right house - we found Villa Mariposa in febuary 2013. The house was in bad shape but we saw the potential.

We planned the renovation with an architect from Barcelona and finished the first renovation phase for the summer of 2013 - and we will continue with more renovation projects along with time.

We travel a lot - New York, Sydney, Europe, Asia - and over the years we have come to places where we have found special details or fantastic ambience or great views. These "moments" have been the inspiration for Villa Mariposa. Spacious, not to much furniture, a garden garden that tells a story over the year - and a view that takes the breath away.

The space
Beautiful apartment, 45m2, perfect for 2 to 5 people. Right by the sea, with breathtaking views. The apartment is fully equipped (air conditioning, dishwasher, washing machine, vitro…) and has Wifi and cable TV.

Guest access
Cap Sa Sal used to be a luxury hotel. It has direct access to the sea from the lift. The estate has 30,000m2 of common areas, including a paradisiacal swimming pool with seawater right by the
neighborhood_overview:
Begur is a typical, small town that started out as a fishing village. It is the proud location of some of the prettiest bays on the Mediterranean coast, all offering the crystalline water and pine forests that have made the Costa Brava famous. This area is also known for its many medieval towns, some of which (e.g. Peratallada) were declared historical and artistic monuments in 1975. In addition to the many small coves (Aigua Blava, Aigua Feda, Aigua Gélida, Sa Tuna, Fornells, etc.), Begur also has excellent sandy beaches (Sa Riera, Playa Pals, etc.) and even a nudist beach – the red island. There are many picturesque coastal towns that are worth a visit such as Calella de Palafrugell and Tamariu, and attractive harbours such as Llafranc.

The ruins of Begur castle offer one of the Costa Brava’s most spectacular views. The castle was the scene of pirate attacks that led the local inhabitants to turn their village away from the sea. The towers they built in the 16th and 17th

neighborhood_overview:
Es una zona en plena naturaleza, característica por su tranquilidad, silencio, harmonía. Es un lugar ideal para descansar y disfrutar de la naturaleza.
A 30 minutos de Girona (donde pueden disfrutar de su casco antiguo, su muralla, la catedral y el barrio judío) y Figueras (museo Dalí, museo del juguete, castillo de San Ferran considerado el castillo más grande de Europa) así como disfrutar de sus zonas comerciales.
A 30 minutos de la playa en coche (l'Escala, Estartit, Sant Pere Pescador, Roses, etc) y de 45 minutos de la montaña (Olot donde pueden visitar la Fageda d'en Jordà con sus parajes y su Zona Volcanica, Santa Pau, etc).
Y a 25 minutos de Banyoles, famoso por su lago.

description:
Fully renovated luxury villa, located in one of the most prestigious areas of the Costa Brava - S'Agaró, just 500 meters from the unique and beautiful beach of Sant Pol. The villa is fully equipped with everything you need for holidays in family and is within walking distance of all services.

The space
The house has a total area of ​​about 250 m2 and is divided into 3 floors:

1st floor: entrance hall, through which you can go directly to the kitchen or living room, living room with dining room and access to a large sunny terrace with direct access to the pool, fully equipped modern kitchen, 3 spacious double bedrooms (one of them with own dressing room), a large bathroom with bathtub and shower and a guest toilet.

Basement: study with its own bathroom and a small equipped kitchen, games room, laundry, addition
neighborhood_overview:
S’Agaró is a luxury residential area located in the heart of laqa Costa Brava, between the towns of Sant Feliu de Guíxols and Playa de Aro.

S’Agaró has two main beaches: Sa Conca and San Pol, one of the most beautiful on the Costa Brava. Sa Conca is even officially considered one of the best beaches in Europe, surrounded by beautiful houses between pines and rocks.

The beach has all the services: bathrooms, showers, Red Cross, bars, sun beds and umbrellas for rent, playgrounds, adaptation for people with disabilities. Cafes and restaurants serving Mediterranean cuisine are located on the beach promenade of Sant Pol.

Guests of S’Agaró should definitely visit the promenade of Cami de Ronda. The 1.8 km long route is immersed in vegetation and has several viewpoints with spectacular views of the sea and the landscape of the Costa Brava.

name: BAIX EMPORDÀ Rustic house rental
description:
This is your ideal home if you are looking for a quiet and wonderful landscape of Empordà without wanting to skip the easy access to the beaches of the Costa Brava. St Martí d'Empuries is 15 min. away and the Medes Islands not more than 20 min.

The space
It is an ideal house to enjoy with the family. It allows you to host very comfortably up to 7 people. Personally, I consider it important to note that one of the bedrooms, and a bathroom with shower, are located on the ground floor of the house (see the plans!)
On the other hand, from the garden and the lounge you have direct access to the porch leading to the garden.

In connection with its geographical location, it’s the perfect place if you want to enjoy a holiday in a quiet, rural location without giving up your daily swim on the beaches of the Costa Brava.

Furthermore! If you practice the golf, Golf or Pitch & Putt Golf Empordà and Pitch & Putt Gualta are just 15 minutes away.
neighborhood_overview: The neighborhood is a very quiet and perfectly located place near the beaches of St. Martí d'Empuries, L'Escala and Estartit. It's also a spot with easy and convenient access.
host_about:
Soy nacido en el Empordà, en la población de Palafrugell, y actualmente tengo 42 años.

Vivo en La Bisbal d'Empordà, con Silvia, mi compañera y con Mel, Maui y Bruno, nuestras mascotas.

Me licencié en Derecho en el año 2000 pero nunca he ejercido la profesión; seguramente, porqué prefiero la tranquilidad de la vida en mi tierra que teñir mi existencia con las tensiones de los Tribunales ( no estoy hecho para esto ).

En Airbnb anunciamos casas de la familia ( 2 casas en Canet de La Tallada y dos apartamentos en Palau-Sator ) y también otra casa cuyos derechos de explotación he adquirido ( Sant Iscle d'Empordà ).

El proyecto inicial de las casas de Canet de la Tallada era la venta pero la depresión del sector inmobiliario hizo a la familia cambiar de opinión y decidimos su explotación en modo de arrendamiento. Además, cuando no están alquiladas las usamos la familia ( somos 5 hermanos ).

En Palau-Sator, los apartamentos que tienen origen en la rehabilitación de la casa de mis abuelos paternos. Era una casa muy grande y hace ya más de 15 años la familia tomó la decisión de restaurara en este sentido.

Después de 3 años en la plataforma, mi experiencia como anfitrión con Airbnb es francamente buena. Salvo pequeños detalles y algún caso aislado estamos muy contentos con los huéspedes que nos han llegado.

Recomiendo el Empordà de forma enérgica, cualquiera de sus rincones, espacios, paisajes o playas...Esta región, es muchísimo más que el conocido Triángulo de Oro. Os lo aseguro!! 

Aquí, puedes relajarte, divertirte, ir de fiesta, en globo, practicar equitación, bajar en canoa por el río Ter, alquilar un velero, ir en bici, jugar a Golf o Picht&Putt, practicar nudismo, bañarte en calas preciosas o, si lo prefieres, en playas kilométricas, perderte en largos paseos al atarceder y comerte un buen arroz!!
neighbourhood: Canet de la Tallada, Catalonia, Spain

description:
The sound of waves and seagulls instead of traffic noise and phone calls.
A great studio apartment for joyful holidays in Fenals, a quiet bay next to Lloret de Mar, Costa Brava. Bounded by pine grown cliffs you find beautiful little bay beaches. 5 min to the beach of Fenals. The studio, located on the top floor of a beautiful white plastered 3-story building with view to the sea and romantic garden with pool is tastefully furnished and fully equipped for 2 adults, a child is welcome.

The space
From the apartment you reach in 5 min by foot at the lovely sand beach. In the beach bar at the car free promenade you view over the cliffs bounded bay onto the dark blue sea. At the end of the bay a trail invites for a walk trough the pines, up the cliffs and to further bays.

The studio has a living room with kitchenette and balcony towards the garden and the sea, a bedroom with big closet and a bathroom with bathtub and washing machine.

neighborhood_overview:
The apartment is in a nice building with white plastering and red tiles assimilating the traditional construction style, located on the top of a rise in the center of the village.
It belongs to facilities with gardens and pools, build solitary on the hill and only drivable through a blind alley. Using a stairway you can reach in 5 minutes the beach by foot or for a walk along the cliffs, which leads to further bays. In the other direction you reach the bakery, the supermarket, green grocery or small restaurants and typical Spanish bars, to grab just ›una caña‹ (beer), ›un vino‹ (wine) with some ›tapas‹ or ›un cortado‹ (espresso with little milk) with ›croissant‹. As well the bus stop for a fast and easy connection for excursions in other villages, or to downtown Lloret is reached in a 5-10 minutes walking distance.

name: Habitación doble en La Trobada Hotel Ripoll
description:
Somos un hotel familiar, con historia y de alta calidad. Estamos ubicados en el centro de Ripoll, sobre el río Ter, a 2 minutos a pie del Monasterio, a 5 minutos de la estación de trenes y autobuses, y con aparcamiento gratuito justo en frente.

The space
Nuestras habitaciones dobles superiores han sido totalmente remodeladas con el objetivo de ofrecer un espacio perfecto para nuestros clientes. Equipadas con una cama doble o dos camas individuales, cuentan con un cálido suelo de parquet y ropa de cama de algodón. Asimismo, los baños han sido diseñados pensando en el máximo confort, para ello cuentan con una amplia ducha o bañera de fácil acceso. Disponen de un escritorio preparado para para las nuevas tecnologías. Debido a su buena relación calidad-precio, las habitaciones dobles superiores son nuestras habitaciones más populares.

License number
HG-002103
neighborhood_overview:
Ripoll y El Ripollès, punto de nacimiento y confluencia de los Ríos Ter y Freser, es ideal para diferentes actividades de naturaleza y cultura.
En este sentido, cabe destacar la Vía Verde Ruta del Hierro y del Carbón, que comienza en el mismo paseo del hotel, la puerta principal del monasterio de Ripoll, ahora candidata al reconocimiento como Patrimonio Mundial de la UNESCO, el Museo Etnográfico de Ripoll,
y nuestra querida Vall de Núria. Somos buenos conocedores de nuestro territorio y estaremos encantados de recomendar a nuestros clientes los mejores lugares y actividades dirigidas y libres según sus intereses.
host_about:
Soy Jaume Farrés. Nací y crecí en La Trobada, el hotel que fundó mi abuelo junto con mi abuela y mi madre durante los años ochenta en Ripoll, en pleno corazón del Pirineo Catalán. Estudié arquitectura en Girona, preciosa ciudad donde viví seis años. Mi pasión por el hoquei patines, deporte me ha acompañado toda mi vida, me llevó a vivir en Barcelona durante dos años más. Ahora vivo de nuevo en Ripoll, en el hotel de mi familia. Combino mi profesión, arquitectura, con el negocio familiar, y el hoquei sobre patines. 

Me interesa el contraste entre lo local y lo global, y me gusta ser el anfitrión de los viajeros que llegan a Ripoll. 

Si quereis hacer excursiones, a pie o en bicicleta, os daré detalles de varias rutas que conozco perfectamente, y os recomendaré una u otra según vuestras preferencias!

neighborhood_overview:
The house is located inside the emblematic walled neighborhood of “Vila Vella”, declared historic-artistic national monument, with lovely narrow streets. An area full of magic where is a privilege to stay.
One minute walking, you have the beach, restaurants next to the wall and 4 minutes away there is the commercial area, where is hard not to stop and see the beautiful shops.

The house is located inside Vila Vella, therefore, it is not possible to reach the door of the house with the car.

Tossa is a beautiful and quiet town, with a lot of charm. Ideal to travel with your couple, family or with the kids.
It is one of the most beautiful town in all Costa Brava, where you can steel feel the little old town atmosphere and where is not allowed to build tall buildings.
Besides enjoying the beaches, there are a lot other things to do. For example: walk around the old and narrow streets from the walled town "Vila Vella", go the the lighthouse and relax at
host_about:
We are Ana and Kristjàn and we’ve been offering accommodation in Tossa de Mar for over thirty years. Seven years ago, we were very happy to found Let’s Holidays.

The passion with which we’ve been working these past years has made us grow, and we now have a vast team of professionals working with us. 
With them, we will make sure to find the best option for you and to get you everything you will need during your stay :)

If there is something that we have learnt this past years is that we like to be treated the same way that we treat you. 
That’s where our philosophy comes from. We like to chat and we will try to get you anything that you need and find solutions to anything that you propose.

At the end, holidays should be exactly the way we want them, right?

We present some of our services :)

The Home Selector is the person who will help you choose the option most appropriate to your tastes. You will save time in searching and finding the best choice.

The Host is the person who will take care of you during the whole stay and try to find anything that you need with the help of the other hosts.

Let’s Holidays Home will be your second holiday home. A place where you will be able to meet with our Hosts, chat, have a glass of wine and listen to some live music.

We’ll love to meet you!

See you soon ;)

name: Casa Rural⭐Cal Masover Rocabruna⭐CAMPRODON
description:
Casa en Rocabruna, Camprodon, Pirineo Catalán. Tranquila y luminosa. Increíbles vistas de la Alta Garrotxa. Naturaleza, paisaje y aire puro. Casa Rural con gran tranquilidad, grandes espacios exteriores, adecuados para multitud de actividades: Descanso, Sol, Juegos Infantiles, Barbacoas...
Ofrecemos amplitud en los espacios interiores, bañados de luz y paisaje. Nuestro propósito es buscar la comodidad y la calidad respetando el medio ambiente y las características de la antigua “Masia Catalana”

The space
La casa tiene para vuestro uso exclusivo, una sala de estar-comedor con cocina incorporada. La cocina esta totalmente equipada (Utensilios para cocinar y comer. Electrodomésticos: Nevera-congelador, horno, microondas, tostadora, batidora, exprimidor, lavavajillas, cafetera italiana,lavadora)
Estos espacios se complementan con 2 habitaciones con baño.
Podemos alojar hasta 6+2 plazas.
Tiene un espacio exterior de uso exclusivo.
neighborhood_overview: Rocabruna es una pequeña aldea del municipio de Camprodon, situada en  la Alta Garrotxa, espacio de Interés Natural. El pueblo de Rocabruna dispone de dos restaurantes de gran calidad, la iglesia románica de Sant Feliu de Rocabruna del s. XII y las ruinas del castillo de Rocabruna, además de multiples rutas de montaña. Perfecto para salidas en caballo, BTT, 4x4, trecking, trail running o asequibles paseos por la más rural o salvaje y apacible naturaleza.

There is an unlimited amount of water sports from kayaking, boat hire, windsurfing/boarding and other water-borne sports.  The Illes Medes islands, just off the coast of Estartit, is a protected marine area and has some of the best diving experiences in the Mediterranean. There are great cycling routes and for the more tranquil pursuits, there are wonderful walks and bird watching opportunities. Ubicación ideal para no utilizar el coche durante toda la estadía. description:

The space

Esta propiedad consiste en un salón con sofá-cama italiano de 135cm, una amplia cocina equipada con horno, lavavajillas, nevera-congelador, microondas, cocina vitrocerámica y otros pequeños electrodomésticos, también dispone de utensilios y productos básicos como sal, azúcar, aceite o productos de limpieza. Además, el apartamento está equipado con una lavadora-secadora, plancha y tendedero de ropa.

host_about:
D'origine Québecoise, je m'occupe de cette merveilleuse maison de famille qui a au dessus de 400 ans ,et dans laquelle on fabriquait autrefois l'huile d'olive, le pain et le vin.
 Je partage cette occupation avec ma mère qui elle,est catalane d'origine et vit au Québec une grande partie de l'année.
J'ai suivi une formation en tourisme et aime partager ma passion pour la vie.
  Ma mère ,elle ,est massothérapeuthe et enseigne le Qi Gong, elle donne des ateliers d'initiation de cet art.
  Nous aimons toutes les deux recevoir les gens, qu'ils se sentent à l'aise et chaleureusement accueillis.
  Nous aimons aussi la nature, les plantes, la musique, la mer, la montagne, avoir du plaisir et partager tous ces merveilleux cadeaux que nous donne la vie;

neighborhood_overview: The small community of Llampaies is situated towards the east of the region, not far from Camallera (2 km), where all kinds of amenities are available. The surrounding countryside boasts gentle rolling hills, farmland and coniferous woodlands. The tiny center of Llampaies is formed of typical local houses. The quarter around the church is the oldest part of the village. Around 100 meters to the north, is the smaller Vecindario del Puig, a group of houses, built in the 17th and 18th centuries. 200 meters from Vecindario del Puig is the Vecindario de los Masos. Some of the houses here date from the end of the 18th century, although the majority were built in the 19th century. There are around 100 people living in the center.
host_name: Turisme Rural Can Gat Vell SCP
host_about:
Hola a tod@s,
Fue en Mayo del 2013 que decidimos venir a vivir aquí en la provincia de Girona ... y hacer un cambio radical de vida. Necesitábamos alejarnos de la ciudad, de la falta de respeto, de una convivencia que se hacía cada vez más insoportable, del egoísmo y anonimato que conocíamos en Barcelona. Ahora disfrutamos de estos pequeños detalles de cada día, en Llampaies, un núcleo de muy pocos habitantes: el cielo, sus amaneceres y puestas de sol, el ambiente rural al 100%. la naturaleza con nuestros insectos, plantas y árboles, nuestros animales con las gallinas y conejos, nuestro gato Llamp y sobre todo disfrutar cada momento con nuestros hijos, Roger y Oriol.
Estamos muy felices de poderos recibir en nuestra casa y haceros descubrir nuestra comarca tan bonita. 
Hasta pronto.
Eduard, Isabelle, Roger y Oriol

neighborhood_overview: The small community of Llampaies is situated towards the east of the region, not far from Camallera (2 km), where all kinds of amenities are available. The surrounding countryside boasts gentle rolling hills, farmland and coniferous woodlands. The tiny center of Llampaies is formed of typical local houses. The quarter around the church is the oldest part of the village. Around 100 meters to the north, is the smaller Vecindario del Puig, a group of houses, built in the 17th and 18th centuries. 200 meters from Vecindario del Puig is the Vecindario de los Masos. Some of the houses here date from the end of the 18th century, although the majority were built in the 19th century. There are around 100 people living in the center.

Hola a tod@s,
Fue en Mayo del 2013 que decidimos venir a vivir aquí en la provincia de Girona ... y hacer un cambio radical de vida. Ahora disfrutamos de estos pequeños detalles de cada día, en Llampaies, un núcleo de muy pocos habitantes: el cielo, sus amaneceres y puestas de sol, el ambiente rural al 100%. la naturaleza con nuestros insectos, plantas y árboles, nuestros animales con las gallinas y conejos, nuestro gato Llamp y sobre todo disfrutar cada momento con nuestros hijos, Roger y Oriol.

Hasta pronto.
Eduard, Isabelle, Roger y Oriol

name: Lovely house in the Emporda
description:
Special and peaceful village house, restored respecting the traditional architecture of the area, in the heart of the village of Vilafant.
Situated at 1 km distance of the AVE train station and 3 km away from Figueras and the Dalí Museum

The space
An old village house with vaulted ceilings in the traditional style of the volta catalana, carefully restored with ecological materials, maintaining and respecting the original architecture of the house and giving it a special charm.

Guest access
There is a balcony where you can enjoy the fresh air in the summer, and even enjoy your meals, at night and during the day if you're three people or less.

Other things to note

neighborhood_overview:
The AVE (a specially fast train) station is 1 km outside the village and the AP7 highway is at a 2 km distance.
You can reach Barcelona in 55 minutes in the AVE train and in 1.5 hours by car.
The house is situated in an ideal spot, both to go to the beach and to explore the mountains. It is at a distance of 3 km from Figueras and the Dali Museum. Llança, Sant Pere Pescador, Rosas and the natural park of Alvera are also great places to visit. The nearest beaches are at only 20 km.
You can make great excursions to places with excellent gastronomy such as the natural parks of Cap de Creus and Alvera, the lake of Banyoles, Besalú, Sant Llorenç de la Muga, Port de la Selva, Empuriabrava and the city of Gerona, as well as architectonic Romanic and Gothic highlights...
host_about: La casa situada en el L´Alt Empordà, una zona bella,  con lagos, bosques, parques naturales,  cerca del mar y la montaña a su vez,  localizada en el casco antiguo del pueblo, ha sido restaurada pensando en el respeto al medio ambiente y con la intención de conectar con lo esencial  y grato de la convivencia.

neighborhood_overview: La vila de Ripoll se encuentra en un espacio natural privilegiado, ríos y montañas invitan al viajero a conocerles. El románico está muy presente en nuestra comarca, varios municipios cuentan con puente o iglesia románica. El monasterio de Santa María de Ripoll es destacable por su gran peso histórico y cultural.
host_about:
Soy Jaume Farrés. Nací y crecí en La Trobada, el hotel que fundó mi abuelo junto con mi abuela y mi madre durante los años ochenta en Ripoll, en pleno corazón del Pirineo Catalán. Estudié arquitectura en Girona, preciosa ciudad donde viví seis años. Mi pasión por el hoquei patines, deporte me ha acompañado toda mi vida, me llevó a vivir en Barcelona durante dos años más. Ahora vivo de nuevo en Ripoll, en el hotel de mi familia. Combino mi profesión, arquitectura, con el negocio familiar, y el hoquei sobre patines. 

Me interesa el contraste entre lo local y lo global, y me gusta ser el anfitrión de los viajeros que llegan a Ripoll. 

Si quereis hacer excursiones, a pie o en bicicleta, os daré detalles de varias rutas que conozco perfectamente, y os recomendaré una u otra según vuestras preferencias!

name: Charming Seaside Family Home, 2 Min Walk to Beach
description:
Our eclectic, charming family home is located in a picturesque vibrant seaside village, just a couple of minute's walk from the fabulous local beaches. Situated in the "old-town" centre, our townhouse retains original features e.g. patterned ceramic floor tiles, vaulted ceilings & characteristic window shutters. You'll benefit from the "home from home" (as in family home/not a hotel!) atmosphere while immersing yourself in village life, with an array of cafes & bars on your doorstep. Enjoy :)

The space
Our home is located in the "old town" of L'Escala, a former fishing village, on the beautiful Costa Brava. This is not a hotel style rental but rather it is our family home.

The accommodation is situated over three floors, with kitchen and dining room on the ground floor. The 4 bedrooms (one with kingsize bed and 3 with single beds) and the WC and bathroom are found on the middle floor. The sitting room is located on the top floor and leads onto
neighborhood_overview:
The house is situated in a peaceful residential area in the "old town" of L'Escala, close to several beaches. The sandy family beach, surrounded by a variety of cafes and restaurants, is located just beyond the bottom of our road. A short stroll away are a number of independent boutiques, jewellery and craft shops, also shops selling local Anchovies of L'Escala. Creu Cove, a minute's walk away (to the left of our house), is great for snorkelling. The larger, sandy crescent beaches of Empúries are a short walk away, and if you want a bit of culture you can visit the nearby Greco-Roman ruins of Empúries. Also within walking distance (a bit of a hike, but worth the walk!), along the beautiful scenic coastal path, is Sant Marti d'Empúries, a charming hill top hamlet with a selection of fabulous restaurants, overlooking the Golf of Roses.

If you drive, there is free parking in our street but the residents use the spaces so you will most likely have to park your car at the to
host_about:
Hello from Seeta and John!

I'm an editor and John is an architect who undertook the renovations on our house which hadn't been lived in for 40 years.  We hope you will enjoy our home as much as we do :)

description:
Casa con chimenea , patio privado y piscina compartida.
Cal Ouaire ofrece una experiencia auténtica en el corazón del Empordà. Se trata de una casa restaurada, rodeada de bosques y pequeñas casas que conforman el tranquilo barrio de Diana. El edificio un antiguo pajar se ha reformado con la premisa de preservar su estructura original como sus paredes de piedra, buscando siempre serenidad y confort. El resultado no es más que un hogar tranquilo que transmite una sensación de simplicida...

The space
Cal Ouaire es una masia Catalana restaurada rodeada de pequeñas casas que conforman el tranquilo vecindario de Diana.
El edificio ha sido renovado a partir de la ruina de una antigua granja. Las renovaciones se llevaron a cabo con las premisas de preservar sus paredes de piedra, buscando siempre la serenidad y comodidad. El resultado no es más que un hogar tranquilo que transmite una sensación de simplicidad y calma. La casa está amueblada con un estilo na
neighborhood_overview:
Todo se reduce a una experiencia sencilla y pura. Huimos de las aglomeraciones y buscamos la discreción. Queremos que nuestros huéspedes formen parte de esta tierra, la vivan y la disfruten de una forma especial. Buscamos ser parte del recuerdo que te llevarás.
La desconexión y el descanso lo encontramos en una puesta de sol, en el ruido de los árboles, en el aire y la energía del viento del Empordà.La casa está emplazada en un camino a 2 kilómetros de Sant Jordi Desvalls. Es un lugar donde reina la tranquilidad y el silencio. Un precioso paisaje de interior, rodeado de campos, huertos y bosques donde disfrutar de agradables paseos.
A escasos kilómetros de la casa se encuentran las playas más bonitas de la Costa Brava. A tan sólo 20 minutos en coche de l'Estartit, i l'Escala, y a 25 minutos de Girona. También podrás visitar numerosos pueblos con encanto. En la casa encontraríes varias ediciones de la Guia de l'Empordà y recomandaciones.
En el pueblo de Sant Jordi Desva
host_about:
Nuestra familia siempre trabajó en el campo y nuestra ilusión de dar nueva vida a antiguos espacios utilizados para el ganado y sus cultivos nos llevaron a construir estas magníficas casas, respetando siempre el entorno y los lugares, con materiales honestos y de calidad.. 
Estaremos encantados de daros la bienvenida y explicaros lo que creemos es lo mejor y más bonito de la zona del Empordà y el Gironès.

description:
Located at the characteristic medieval village of Palau-Sator, this renovated apartment offers you a comfortable residency during your holidays. The living room, dining room, and kitchen merge into a single open-plan space, painted in warm tones and filled with light. Totally furnished, the living room area is fitted out with two sofas, a coffee table and, for your entertainment, a flat screen TV and Wi-Fi service.
The apartment offers also two bedrooms and one bathroom.

The space
This specific location, which is setteld in a very quiet medieval village is an exceptional catalan

Guest access

Other things to note

Minimum 7 nights from Saturday to Saturday
neighborhood_overview: Historic center of Palau-Sator, medieval village in the province of Girona. Located 10-15 minutes from the beaches of the Costa Brava (Pals, Begur, Estartit..). Palau-Sator, is a quiet tourist town. You will not find large crowds. The neighbours, mostly, are people from the country. It is also important to note that in the village there are exactly 4 restaurants, I particularly recommend Can Saló and Mas Pou.
host_about:
Soy nacido en el Empordà, en la población de Palafrugell, y actualmente tengo 42 años.

Vivo en La Bisbal d'Empordà, con Silvia, mi compañera y con Mel, Maui y Bruno, nuestras mascotas.

Me licencié en Derecho en el año 2000 pero nunca he ejercido la profesión; seguramente, porqué prefiero la tranquilidad de la vida en mi tierra que teñir mi existencia con las tensiones de los Tribunales ( no estoy hecho para esto ).

En Airbnb anunciamos casas de la familia ( 2 casas en Canet de La Tallada y dos apartamentos en Palau-Sator ) y también otra casa cuyos derechos de explotación he adquirido ( Sant Iscle d'Empordà ).

El proyecto inicial de las casas de Canet de la Tallada era la venta pero la depresión del sector inmobiliario hizo a la familia cambiar de opinión y decidimos su explotación en modo de arrendamiento. Además, cuando no están alquiladas las usamos la familia ( somos 5 hermanos ).

En Palau-Sator, los apartamentos que tienen origen en la rehabilitación de la casa de mis abuelos paternos. Era una casa muy grande y hace ya más de 15 años la familia tomó la decisión de restaurara en este sentido.

Después de 3 años en la plataforma, mi experiencia como anfitrión con Airbnb es francamente buena. Salvo pequeños detalles y algún caso aislado estamos muy contentos con los huéspedes que nos han llegado.

Recomiendo el Empordà de forma enérgica, cualquiera de sus rincones, espacios, paisajes o playas...Esta región, es muchísimo más que el conocido Triángulo de Oro. Os lo aseguro!! 

Aquí, puedes relajarte, divertirte, ir de fiesta, en globo, practicar equitación, bajar en canoa por el río Ter, alquilar un velero, ir en bici, jugar a Golf o Picht&Putt, practicar nudismo, bañarte en calas preciosas o, si lo prefieres, en playas kilométricas, perderte en largos paseos al atarceder y comerte un buen arroz!!

name: Habitación triple con porche
description:
En Sant Pere Pescador rodeado de campos fruteros, al principio de la reserva natural “Parc de Mig de Dos Rius” dónde hay una gran diversidad de fauna, al lado del río Fluvià i cerca de la playa, en el corazón de los Aiguamolls de l'Empordà.

The space
El mas se encuentra en Sant Pere Pescador rodeado de campos fruteros, al principio de la reserva natural “Parc de Mig de Dos Rius” dónde hay una gran diversidad de fauna, al lado del río Fluvià i cerca de la playa, en el corazón de los Aiguamolls de l’Empordà.

La masía está situada en la comarca del Alt Empordà, en la población de Sant Pere Pescador, en el Baix Fluvià. El pueblo se encuentra a unos 300 m y se puede ir dando un paseo. Aproximadamente a un kilómetro tenemos la desembocadura del Fluvià de gran valor ecológico y la playa que tiene una extensión de 6 km. de dunas de arena fina. Es una de las pocas playas que se mantienen vírgenes en la Costa Brava.

El camino que pasa por delante de
neighborhood_overview:
Desde Sant Pere podrá hacer muchas visitas turísticas, como son por ejemplo:
Figueres (19 km): Museu Dalí, museo del juguete, de la técnica, del Empordà, Castillo de Sant Ferran, ….
Castelló d’Empúries (8,5 km): villa condal, basílica de Santa María, la harinera, …
L’Escala (12 km): ruinas greco-romanas de Empúries, fábricas de anchoas,…
Roses (17 km): castillo de la Trinidad, Ciutadella, monumentos megalíticos, puerto pesquero, …
Sant Pere de Rodes (28 km): monasterio románico.
Cap de Creus (38 km): Parque Natural.
Besalú (38 km): pueblo medieval, Puente Viejo, baños judíos, ….
Girona (50 km): catedral, barrio judío, la Rambla, la Devesa, …
Barcelona: 147 km.
Perpiñán: 76 km.
host_about:
M'agrada llegir, cuinar, la natura, passejar amb els gossos i quan tinc un moment sortir a córrer pels voltants del mas. 
També m'encanta viatjar però des que tenim la casa rural no ens queda massa temps per fer-ho.

Exceptional situation close to everywhere and easy access. Within the natural park of the volcanoes of La Garrotxa (Girona)

Typical Catalan farmhouse from the 18th century, restored and very authentic

name: Beautiful old farmhouse with pool II  (PG-502)
description:
Mas Vinyoles is at the same time away from it all and close to everything: Beach, mountains, beautiful cities like Girona, Barcelona, Figueres.... After a full and busy day it is wonderfull to retire to it's unique quietness.

The space
Mas Vinyoles is a Catalan countryside house that is partly converted to offer a pleasant space to spend your holidays: 2 fully equipped apartments, for 4 and 6 people.
There is a garden with a swimming pool and bbq, a biological vegetable garden and an orchard.
We are in the heart of the protected area ″Les Gavarres ″, a series of hills of Mediterranean forest between Girona and Costa Brava.
This is a place to spend some quiet days of rest, exploring the surroundings by foot or on bicycle.

Guest access
Guests will have access to the swimming pool (sea salt water), a beautiful garden surrounding the house, tons of hills with cork trees, silence, bird songs and clean sky with outstanding stars.
neighborhood_overview: We are 33 neighbours in the middle of a protected wooden area.
host_about: I live in "Les Gavarres" since 1985 and I love it. To take care of the forest and the wild life has become an important project of my life. I am happy to realise that every year a new variety of birds discover that this is a good place for them to spend at least part of the year.

neighborhood_overview:
GPS Coordenades: 42.034452554751766, 2.9899871349334717

Can Carrió is located in the northern part of Foixà, in the neighbourhood of Cuells, in a residential zone surrounded by fields and pine and oak woodland which give a magical air of tranquillity.

4Km away is the Gala/Dali foundation in Púbol Castle, vertex of the Dali triangle with Figueres and Port- Lligat. 35km away is the town of Figueres and the Museo Dalí.

20 Km from Foixà are the beaches of Empúries, Escala, Estartit and Pals, and the Costa Brava stretching out before you. Estartit offers an important base for Scuba diving in the protected surroundings of the Medes Islands. Also 20km away is the historic city of Girona.

Around the village there are different cycle routes and footpaths which allow you to explore the local area.

Rural house (Only Adults) with sustainability certificate, with private parking, garden with barbecue and spaces for relaxation. Outdoor salt water swimming pool. Equipped Bikeroom and maps with information. Spacious kitchen, very well equipped with fireplace/BBQ, oven, dishwasher, American refrigerator, coffee makers, and a large table. Two rooms with softwos and fireplace, a pool and board games. With seven rooms, equipped with sheets. All rooms with private bathroom, towels and amenities.

The space
Sta located in the heart of the Natural Park of the Montgrí. Overlooking Cap of Begur and within walking distance of medieval villages and the sea.
Ideal for groups of friends, families, who want to relax and fun. We are in full nature and we have more and 15 hiking trails and bike.

Guest access
We have barbecue in the garden, area of picnic, park with swings, sandbank, toboggan... and farm animals.
We rent bicycles under request

name: El Jardí d'Alemanys 5
description:
Exclusive rental property with pool in the historical core of Girona

The space
Located in the heart of Girona's medieval quarter, inside the original city walls and overlooking Sant Domènec Square, is the property Alemanys 5, whose original building dates from the sixteenth century.

Its recent restoration integrates old and new, with sober, clean lines that celebrate essential elements such as space, light, shade, fire, stone, water and silence.

The house is available to be rented as a whole unit, but it also can be divided into two independent apartments that can be rented separately: "El Badiu" i "El Jardí".

"El Jardí” (The Garden) is a 90 m2 flat that offers:

two double bedrooms
a spacious bathroom
a large dining-living room with fully equipped kitchenette
a private sunny garden with swimming pool.
Its capacity is up to 4 people.

Facilities also include: free WiFi broadband Internet acc

name: House in Tossa de Mar, Costa Brava
description:
Áncora is a cosy house located in Sta. Maria de Llorell Beach, Tossa de Mar. It offers sea view, a terrace with BBQ area, a relaxing communal swimming pool and one of the best beaches of la Costa Brava. Free Wifi.

The space
Áncora is a 2 floor semi-detached house. The entrance is a big terrace with a barbecue area. Some steps further, you will be at the porch: a sheltered place to have dinner, read or just relax.
The ground floor is an open floor: living room and kitchen. There is a toilet and a fireplace as well.
On the first floor there are 2 double rooms (1 with a queen bed and 1 with 2 twin beds) and a bathroom with shower. There is also a balcony with sea views.

Guest access
Swimming pool (next to the house)
Beach (1km /15-20 minute walk)
Supermarket (5 minute walk)
Bus stop (5 minute walk)
Free parking on the street

Other things to note

*Kitchen f
neighborhood_overview:
Santa Maria de Llorell is a private estate located in one of the nicest beaches of La Costa Brava: Cala Llevado - Santa Maria de Llorell. It is a crystal clear water beach surrounded by cliffs and green valleys. It offers diverse water sports and there is a chiringuito and a restaurant.

Santa Maria de Llorell is 3 km away from Tossa de Mar. This beautiful town has plenty of restaurants, supermarkets and shops.

name: Can Sici Masia
description:
Can Sici es una masía tradicional del SXVIII, con piscina, situada en un entorno rural y tranquilo, donde encontrareis hospitalidad y confort para disfrutar de vuestras reuniones familiares y encuentros con amigos, a menos de 10 km de Girona.
Capacidad para 12 adultos más niños hasta 22 personas.

The space
La masía se alquila entera y tiene una capacidad de hasta 22 personas (máximo 12 adultos) distribuidas en 6 habitaciones dobles, una habitación con 6 camas y un altillo con 4 colchones.

Dispone de amplios espacios donde poder compartir momentos en común: en la planta baja la Sala de la entrada y el magnífico Salón-comedor con una gran mesa de madera y una zona de estar con chimenea. En la primera planta la Sala central y la luminosa Sala del pajar (donde se encontraba el antiguo pajar).

A pocos metros de la fachada principal hay una pérgola con mesas sobre la balsa ajardinada que antiguamente proveía la casa de agua de lluvia. La cas
neighborhood_overview:
Can Sici está a menos de 10 km de Girona. Pertenece a la barriada de Sant Medir, en el término municipal de Sant Gregori.
Se sitúa dentro del territorio de la Vall de Llèmena, uno de los lugares naturales mejor conservados de las comarcas gironines, por donde se extienden pequeños pueblos, antiguos vecindarios y singulares masías en un marco de gran valor paisajístico. La combinación entre los campos de cultivo, los diferentes tipos de bosque, los riscos y la presencia del agua, conforman un paisaje armónico modelado por la naturaleza y los usos tradicionales de sus recursos.

name: Fidara
description:
Una habitación muy especial, situada en la planta baja. Cubierta de bóveda catalana, con salida directa a uno de los rincones más bellos del exterior de la casa, junto al pozo.

The space
En el exterior puedes disfrutar del bar, la piscina, los rincones sorprendentes, y el paisaje excepcional que rodea la casa. Las fantásticas playas de Pals se encuentran a 20 minutos andando y el núcleo antiguo de Pals o el nucleo cercano de Begur a pocos minutos en bicicleta por caminos interiores de gran belleza.
La masía está situada en un entorno ideal para conocer la zona de Pals y el bajo empordán, donde se suceden los pequeños pueblos medievales y las playas de la Costa Brava. En el área más cercana es posible además participar en gran variedad de actividades deportivas y culturales muy variadas: museos, festivales, senderismo, golf, deportes de agua etc. A menos de una hora, se puede visitar Torroella de Montgrí, Figueres, Girona o Perpinyá con toda su oferta cultura

Located in Torre Vella, a very quiet urbanization with views. Next to the woods and olive fields, ideal for walking.
At the entrance of the urbanization is the GP supermarket, open all year round. It is located between Torroella de Montgrí and L'Estartit, 3.5 km from the beach.

neighborhood_overview:
Torre Vella is situated on a hill; it is very calm and has beautiful views. Located next to the woods and olive fields, lovely for walks. At the entrance is a large supermarket, open every day of the week. It is 3,5 km to Torroella de Montgrí, typical Catalan village. And 3,5 km to L´Estartit, beach and centre.
Lovely weekly markets, city’s to visit Barcelona, Girona and Figueres.
Plenty of nice old villages you can visit but also beautiful small bays.
Estartit has a large Sandy beach, which slowly goes into the deep, so ideal for children. There is also a large free parking place at the beach. Estartit is known for diving around the Medes Islands but you can practice all sorts of water sports.

In L´estartit on the Boulevard are different restaurants you can find that are realy good. There is N´gruna and Gelatone. The prices are really good and the food is excellent. A N´gruna they serve different plates and at Gelatone you can have a lovely pizza of pasta.

description:
Stay in a typically Empordanese house located in the heart of the Costa Brava. This beautiful 18th century rectory has been transformed into four cozy apartments that preserve the historical essence of the establishment.

Our apartments are 50 m2, have 1 large bedroom with a double bed, 1 full bathroom and a living area with a fully equipped kitchen.

The rectory of regencos, where our apartments are located, has a beautiful garden with a swimming pool.

The space
Spacious and fully equipped apartment of 50 m2, overlooking our garden with pool. Perfect capacity for 2 adults and 1 child.

Apartment decorated by interior designer Anna Puig. Her vision has managed to turn our rooms into cozy and bright spaces, taking care of every detail accompanied by the practicality and comfort necessary to satisfy the needs of our clients.


Each apartment has:

• 50 m2

neighborhood_overview:
Our customers can park their car esaily, few meters from the apartment.

Place that stands out for the tranquility of the town of Regencos at the same time that it is perfectly located, between the towns of Pals and Begur, just 10 minutes from the places of interest and the best beaches on the Costa Brava.

The Rectoria de Regencós, as its name suggests, is located in the medieval town of Regencós, characterized by its tranquility. It is the perfect enclave for those who want to enjoy the typical village life of its people, its narrow and cobbled streets and surrounded by fields with views of the Quarlemany mountain.

We are in the small and cozy medieval town of Regencós, between the well-known towns of Begur and Pals. The perfect enclave for those who want to enjoy nature and the sea, in a dream environment.

It is located just 5 minutes by car from the best beaches such as Sa tuna, Sa Riera, Calella de Palafrugell, LLafranc, Pals and Platja

Hace 29 años que me dedico al mundo de Real Estate y tambien desde entonces he pasado mis vacaciones en Tossa de Mar , a mis hijas le gustaba tanto que finalmente me compre una casa en Santa Maria de LLorell ( Tossa de mar) Me encanta, no se si me gusta más en verano para disfrutar de la playa y de la maravillosa agua transparente  o en invierno de esos paseos tranquilos tanto por las playas como por las montañas cercanas, tienes mil cosas por hacer.

neighborhood_overview:
What do we love about Roses. I suppose the beautiful sea, the fishing fleet, which leaves port everyday to return in the late afternoon, which is a lovely sight from our terrace. The sunsets. The restaurants and the nice boulevard of Roses.
The nice villages to visit near Roses, such as Cadaques, Figueres with its Dali museum, the National Parks of Cap de Creus and Aiguamolls.
host_about:
Twenty five years ago we wanted to buy a house in France for our holidays and we found Le Coustal. We restored first the old farmhouse dated 1870 and this is the place we used to live in ourselves. Now this beautiful  farmhouse is also for rent and we named it La Ferme.  We ourselves moved to Château Preyssac in Thenon,  which we are renovating right now.  We started to restore all the other buildings on the domaine. Many years later we could buy the land of our neighbors and we were able to completely renovate the Maison de Maitre and opening it for guests six years ago. 
We are originally from the Netherlands, however 16 years ago we moved from Holland to the United Arab Emirates with our daughter Sanne. 
Nowadays I spend my time between France and the Emirates and together with my daughter Sanne and a dedicated team we take care of our guests in France and Spain, where we also have a family property ( las Rocas) hosted by my cousin Gijb.
Apart from las Rocas we now manage 3 more properties in Rosas: 
Belleza del Mar, Casa Diaz, and Casa Flamenco. 
in the future we hope to add some more treehouses at the domaine Lalande-Laborie. At the moment there are two and maybe in the future in the forests of Preyssac !!

host_about:
Hola! Sóc Marc López, de Palafrugell, però actualment resident a Girona. 
Sóc compositor, i treballo de professor de música en un institut de secundària i de professor d'harmonia i guitarra a escoles de música. M'agrada molt practicar esport i tota mena d'activitats a l'aire lliure, cosa que vaig fent en funció del temps lliure del que disposo. 
Conec molt bé Palafrugell. És el poble on he crescut i on he viscut tota la meva infantesa i adolescència. Tinc meravellosos records dels estius d'aquella època: les anades i vingudes diàries a les platges de Calella, la sal i la flaire del mar sobre la pell bronzejada pel sol, els vespres de Festa Major a Plaça Nova... No hi ha res com passar l'estiu en un poble de la costa mediterrània com Palafrugell. De fet, malgrat tenir la residència habitual a Girona, cada any hi torno a l'estiu i intento passar-hi tant temps com sigui possible. Això em permet reviure totes aquelles meravelloses sensacions vitals!  
Més que no pas un allotjament en sí mateix, aquestes sensacions són l'essència del que Airbnb em permet compartir amb tots vosaltres. L'apartament, si bé és molt  important, només és el mitjà que ha de fer possible que els hostes vingueu fins aquí i conegueu el poble i els paratges únics que hi ha a les rodalies. Però la finalitat, allò que és realment important aconseguir, és gaudir de les vivències i sensacions úniques que, com jo, tindreu el plaer i el privilegi d'experimentar passant l'estiu en un poble de la costa catalana com aquest.
Per mi serà tot un plaer ser el vostre cicerone, compartir aquestes experiències i guiar-vos a través de tot aquest tresor de sensacions mediterrànies. Benvinguts a l'estiu! Benvinguts a Palafrugell!
