neighborhood_overview:
It is an area integrated into a natural environment near the beaches of Sa Boadella, Fenals and Santa Cristina de Lloret de Mar, one of the most beautiful on the Costa Brava.
Very quiet and exclusive neighborhood, away from the festive atmosphere of the center of Lloret de Mar.
200 m. There is a local bus stop and a tourist stop, with a circuit through the botanical gardens, and supermarkets 300 m away. At Fenals beach you can take boats with a tour of the beaches of the Costa Brava.
host_about:
Soy una mujer servicial y hospitalaria. Me gusta que la gente se sienta cómoda y feliz a mi alrededor. Intento tratar a mis huéspedes como me gustaría que me trataran a mi. 
Me congratula compartir experiencias y una de ellas es ceder mi propiedad de Lloret de Mar para disfrute vacacional y de ocio.
En mi apartamento doy prioridad al confort, la limpieza, una buena dotación de equipamiento doméstico, servicios y un entorno íntimo y agradable para que tanto famílias como parejas disfruten de un alojamiento y estancia immejorable, relajante y placentera... Además, yo estoy siempre disponible presencial y/o telefónicamente por si hay cualquier problema.
Parece que consigo mi objetivo puesto que frecuentemente alojo inquilinos repetidores. Mi premio es ver las caras de mis clientes cuando se marchan (y vuelven!).
Esta es mi mayor satisfacción!

name: Ca la Mula, Cap de Creus
description:
Pide tu oferta a partir de la tercera noche, Casa en entorno rural, con calefacción, 3 dormitorios, 2 baños (bañera para dos personas, no jacuzzi), jardín con barbacoa, vistas al monasterio de Sant Pere de Rodes.
Ideal para desconectar, pueblo tranquilo a 2 km de la playa. Perfecto para 1 o 2 parejas o familia con niños.

The space
La casa se reformo en 2013, con calefacción mediante bomba de calor, instalada en enero de 2016, dispone de un comedor-cocina con chimenea (35 m2), en la planta primera, con vista a la montaña y al monasterio de Sant Pere de Roda y de Sant Salvador, dispone de 3 dormitorios, 1 doble (15 m2) y 2 individuales (6 m2), con dos camas de matrimonio y una litera, 2 baños completos, uno de los baños dispone de bañera para 2 personas, no es un jacuzzi, los chorros de agua y las burbujas estan desconectados, con las paredes de piedra y iluminación led de colores, perfecto para descansar después de una ruta a pie por los caminos que recorren
neighborhood_overview:
El pueblo de La Vall de la Santa Creu, data del siglo XVI, ubicado a 17 km de Cadaqués, se trata de un entorno rural, protegido por el departamento de patrimonio de la Generalitat, dentro del parque natural del Cap de Creus, con vista al monasterio de Sant Pere de Rodes. Se ubica a unos 2,5 km de la playa.
El pueblo dispone de un restaurante, abierto en verano, especializado en arroz con bogavante y paellas.

LLevo dedicandome 25 años al alquiler turístico. Me importa la buena relación con propietarios y huéspedes. Mi experiencia y empatía hace que tanto unos cómo otros quedan contenos y vuelven cada año a alquilar conmigo por que hay buena relación!

Ac ceso a mi despacho El Tura: 

Llegando a Barcelona & Girona, si toman la NII, a la altura de Orriols, hay el cruce de l’Escala -  Empuries ( a la derecha) si toman la Autopista AP7/E15, por favor salen por la Salida 5 “L’Escala – Empuries”.  Llegando a la L’Escala por la Gi 623, encontrarán lo puntos giratorios de St. Martí d’Empuries  y del Camp dels Pilans, siempre tendrán que tomar la dirección Riells – Montgó. A la llegada de la población, como referencia encontrarán un puesta de la Cruz Roja, el supermercado Champion y una torreta de los bomberos. La dirección de la agencia el Tura es Avda. Montgó, nº 21ª.

Acces a mon agence el Tura

En arrivant de France, par l’Autoroute AP7/E15, vous prennez la sortie 5: L’Escala – Empúries. Si vous prennez la Route Nationale II (aprés Figueres) il ya la sortie ver l’Escala, pour la route C252. En arrivant a l’Escala, il y a les ronds  points de St. Martí d’Empuries et del Camp dels Pilans, il faut prendre toujours direction  Riells – Montgó. En arrivant, vous aurez comme points de reference la Croix Rouge, le supermarché Champion et une tour de sourveillance des Pompiers. L’adress de mon agence El Tura c’est Avda. Montgó, nº 21ª.

neighborhood_overview:
The best area of the Costa Brava. Tamariu is very relaxed, with only some excellent small restaurants animating the small bay.

People come from far away to taste the delicious paellas, fresh fish and seafood in front of the sea. A unique experience.

Tamariu has 2 small supermarkets, both selling fresh products: fruits, vegetables and meat, 2 bakeries, hairdressing, international press, shops and bars (some of them with free wifi).The region where Tamariu is situated is simply amazing. You have the best virgin beaches of the Costa Brava around, and if you go inland, most of the villages are medieval, declared historic-artistic monument. The walks around the coastal paths are also highly recommended, with secluded coves to be discovered.

Tossa is a beautiful and quiet town, with a lot of charm. Ideal to travel with your couple, family or with the kids.

Besides enjoying the beaches, there are a lot other things to do. For example: walk around the old and narrow streets from the walled town "Vila Vella", go the the lighthouse and relax at the "Bar del Far", while you enjoy the incredible views of the rugged coastline and the cliffs. Wal

We are Ana and Kristjàn and we’ve been offering accommodation in Tossa de Mar for over thirty years. Seven years ago, we were very happy to found Let’s Holidays.

The passion with which we’ve been working these past years has made us grow, and we now have a vast team of professionals working with us. 
With them, we will make sure to find the best option for you and to get you everything you will need during your stay :)

If there is something that we have learnt this past years is that we like to be treated the same way that we treat you. 
That’s where our philosophy comes from. We like to chat and we will try to get you anything that you need and find solutions to anything that you propose.

At the end, holidays should be exactly the way we want them, right?

We present some of our services :)

The Home Selector is the person who will help you choose the option most appropriate to your tastes. You will save time in searching and finding the best choice.

The Host is the person who will take care of you during the whole stay and try to find anything that you need with the help of the other hosts.

Let’s Holidays Home will be your second holiday home. A place where you will be able to meet with our Hosts, chat, have a glass of wine and listen to some live music.

We’ll love to meet you!

See you soon ;)

neighborhood_overview:
Sant Feliu is a lovely town, dating back hundreds of years, dedicated to fishing and farming, and nowadays, tourism of course. There is still a substantial fishing fleet based in it's harbour (which also has has a large number of recreational boats, fron basic inflatables to mega-yachts). The daily market is full of wonderful locally grown produce, and delicious fresh fish. The harbour is 3 minutes walk from the apartment, the market 10 mins (walking slowly!). The town has 20,000 regular inhabitants, holding lots of it's original charm. It is not overly touristy, like other places nearby (Playa de Aro being the worst example - best to go there just for the night-life and the shopping!).
There are many great places close-by to go to for beautiful beaches, excursions, cycling, scuba-diving, cliff-walking, etc. etc.

name: Pretty Villa in Spectacular Setting with pool
description:
A countryside haven with in easy reach of the shimmering Costa Brava. Situated within the national park of Les Gavarres, aside a picturesque, medieval village, the villa has breathtaking views and spectacular walks. Enjoy traditional features with modern comforts, pool, garden & donkey.

The space
The situation is idyllic and unique. I don't think there is any other property in the area that can boast such a tranquil setting and be in walking distance of 2 of the best and affordable countryside restaurants in the area. To be by such a pretty but quite medieval village while in a national park is pretty amazing. The house is not "Ikead" it has taste, character and charm. The garden in beautifully planted and the pool at 11m, a perfect size. It really is a fantastic base to explore the medieval villages of Emporda, the beaches of the Costa Brava and the whole of Catalonia in general with the mountains, Girona, France and Barcelona also just a day trip away.
neighborhood_overview:
This area is known for its beaches, its food, stunning countryside, medieval villages, cycling, mountains and art.

A Gastronomic Extravaganza
There are various Michelin starred restaurants and many wonderful off the beaten track, local, authentic, affordable eateries. We owned a restaurant ourselves and can advise you on the best places to eat. There are 2 wonderful local restaurants just within walking distance.

Surreal Art
The area has been known for its ceramics since roman times and one can visit the nearby town of La Bisbal for ceramic shopping and the Friday morning, outside food market is delightful.

We are in the centre of the Dali triangle, with his wife Gala's eccentric castle in neighbouring Le Pubol and Figueres and Cadaques an hour or so away by car.

Surrounded by beautiful medieval villages such as Pals and Peretallada, you can spend a lovely morning at markets and cafes or go back further in time and view the exce
host_about: We love travel, art, design and cooking. We love creating and hosting delicious feasts at home.

host_about:
LLevo dedicandome 25 años al alquiler turístico. Me importa la buena relación con propietarios y huéspedes. Mi experiencia y empatía hace que tanto unos cómo otros quedan contenos y vuelven cada año a alquilar conmigo por que hay buena relación! 

Ac ceso a mi despacho El Tura: 

Llegando a Barcelona & Girona, si toman la NII, a la altura de Orriols, hay el cruce de l’Escala -  Empuries ( a la derecha) si toman la Autopista AP7/E15, por favor salen por la Salida 5 “L’Escala – Empuries”.  Llegando a la L’Escala por la Gi 623, encontrarán lo puntos giratorios de St. Martí d’Empuries  y del Camp dels Pilans, siempre tendrán que tomar la dirección Riells – Montgó. A la llegada de la población, como referencia encontrarán un puesta de la Cruz Roja, el supermercado Champion y una torreta de los bomberos. La dirección de la agencia el Tura es Avda. Montgó, nº 21ª.

Acces a mon agence el Tura

En arrivant de France, par l’Autoroute AP7/E15, vous prennez la sortie 5: L’Escala – Empúries. Si vous prennez la Route Nationale II (aprés Figueres) il ya la sortie ver l’Escala, pour la route C252. En arrivant a l’Escala, il y a les ronds  points de St. Martí d’Empuries et del Camp dels Pilans, il faut prendre toujours direction  Riells – Montgó. En arrivant, vous aurez comme points de reference la Croix Rouge, le supermarché Champion et une tour de sourveillance des Pompiers. L’adress de mon agence El Tura c’est Avda. Montgó, nº 21ª.

Loue à la semaine du samedi 16 heures au samedi suivant 10 heures studio entièrement équipé pour 3 personnes avec magnifique terrasse de 3mx3m dominant toute la baie de Rosas. L'une des 30 plus belles baies du monde au classement de l'UNESCO.

The space
Studio très lumineux avec sa baie vitrée de 3 metres de large.
Carrelage gris clair au sol peinture blanche murs et plafond.

D'ou la vue exceptionnelle ( voir les commentaires)

D'ou le calme , loin du brouhaha de la ville de Rosas bien que distante de seulement 2 kms.

Quartier très résidenciel.

neighborhood_overview:
L'Escala has a strategic location - everything is close. Girona, Roses, Cadaques - only 40-45 min; Figueres and Empuriabrava - 20min; Begur and Palamos - 30 min; Pals and Playa de Aro - 40 -50 min; Banyoles, Olot - 40 min - 1 hour. Overall, L'Escala is perfect for exploring the Costa Brava.
L´Escala offers various activities and areas which can be enjoyed with children. The beaches of L´Escala are characterised by their fine sand and shallow waters, which means that they are ideal for children. Also is a paradise for children, with children´s parks, go-karts and horse trip, as well as bicycle hire. What´s more, L´Escala offers a wide range of sports and adventure-based activities - discover new sensations!! Bicing in l´Escala is more than a simply renting bikes service. L'Escala Cycling is a public transport service. It is practical, sustainable and easy to use. Tour and enjoy the l'Escala region free from air and noise pollution. A walk along El Camí Forestal between l´Escala

name: Sleep & Stay deluxe aptmt old town
description:
Make your visit to Girona memorable staying in this fantastic deluxe apartment that is overlooking the main square of the town hall, Placa del Vi and on walking distance of all shops, restaurants and Jewish quarter.

We are looking forward hosting you in our beautiful medieval city!

The space
The apartment is beautifully decorated, with a spacious open dining, kitchen and living room with a super relaxing modern seating area featuring windows and balconies that overlook one of the main squares of the old town, Barri Vell.
The kitchen is recently renovated with all appliances needed and has plenty of kitchen wear. There's a Dolce Gusto coffee machine, oven, microwave, dishwasher, air-con and washing machine. In the living room there is a sofa bed for an extra 3rd and 4th guest.
There is one spacious double bedroom with a kingsize bed (160x200m) and lots of wardrobe space. The mattress is off a high quality, purchased in 2021 We provide high
neighborhood_overview: Located in Plaza del Vi,  this is the center of all cultural activities in Girona.  You'll have all markets, shops and landmarks walking 2 min away from the building.
host_about:
Sleep and Stay is a professional holiday rental agency and licensed Real estate Agency.
All our properties are carefully selected and we prioritize customer service, a personal touch and impecable cleaning. We leave a welcome package with cleaning products (dishwasher tablets, laundry tablets, sponge, cloth and extra garbage bags) and first essentials like coffee, tea, sugar, salt, pepper, olive oil and vinegar. Those items you just need for a couple of days away, are just great to have at your disposal. 
Most people that visit Girona once, never want to leave again. They want to come back, because Girona has it all. We recently opened a branch in Besalu which is small medieval copy of Girona. We have beaches, culture of Dali, the great Spanish kitchen with lot’s of different tapas and wines, old medieval villages and mountains great for skiing, hiking and cycling! What else do you want?

That’s why we fell in love with Girona and made it our business of helping people to find their dream holiday home for a week’s stay or even to buy a property and have a second home in this amazing region! Sleep & Stay is owned by Jolien Huizing Gerrans, Dutch nationality, and she has surrounded herself by an amazing team. Sonia (Polish) and Luis (Honduras). We personally manage each holiday property that are featured on this website and are experts in the Girona property market for more than 4 years. We all speak next to our mother tongues Spanish, Catalan and English which makes all language barriers disappear!

As a young and dynamic holiday rental organisation, specialised in amazing holiday rentals, property management and property finder services. We can assist you in finding a special place to stay in Girona. We value quality, comfort and well maintained holiday rentals as our most important goals. We want to find that charming place for you that makes you fall in love with Girona too and makes you want to stay forever.

Once you arrive and you need anything, we are here to help you. Available on (Hidden by Airbnb) , email and we're just a phone call away. Welcome to come and stay with us!

neighborhood_overview: The Pedret area of Girona is just within the city walls and so the old part of the city. Just 2 minutes away there are numerous little cafés and shops but there is a supermarket 10 minutes walk away. To the front of the apartment is the River Ter which runs through the city and this means that no one overlooks the balcony and there are open views to the river. Tourists & cyclists love how quickly you can be on the road to the sea or to the mountains at this side of the city. There are walks along the river or up the St Daniel Valley for walkers tired of city life.
host_about: My family and I moved to Catalonia from the UK 20 years ago, finding Can Torras two years later. Since then it has been a labour of love to renovate two apartments and my old farmhouse. I knew from the start this was where I wanted to live - the food, the scenery, the wonderful weather. Now I'm pleased to share the farmhouse, my garden and its magnificent views with visitors and offer my apartments in Girona for self catering stays. I am happy to share my experiences so that visitors enjoy the best that Catalonia has to offer.

Completely equiped apartment of 80 m2 aprox. with lot of space, fresh and very luminouse. View to the beach of S'Agaro, elevator, pool and garden on the buiding, private parking and only 3 min. by car to the shops and the beach. Cradle and chair o.d.

The space
The apartment has about 80 square meters and is fully equipped for an unforgettable stay on the Costa Brava. The kitchen is fully equipped with washing machine, dryer, dishwasher, oven, gas hob, microwave and fridge-freezer.
There is a Flat TV and DVD, and a PlayStation upon request.
There are two separate bedrooms, a room with double bed and the other one with two single beds. One bathroom is inside of a bedroom and one bathroom in the hallway.
There is a large dining area by the living room and a bright terrace with overlooking to the sea and the beach of S'Agaro, Playa de Aro and Sant Feliu de Guixols.

Guest access
The apartment has a community pool and garden and a
neighborhood_overview:
S'Agaró is situated between Playa de Aro and Sant Feliu de Guixols, two very idyllic and typical towns on the Costa Brava in the province of Girona. Playa de Aro is ideal for shopping and has a lot of brand shops, spend a day at the beach or go for drinks and dancing at night.
The apartment is located just 30 min. from Girona and 40 min. from Figueras, two capitals with a special charm and great cultural value.

neighborhood_overview:
Pals playa es una zona tranquila ideal para hacer turismo en familia, para relajarse y desconectar.
Es una zona ideal si te gustan los deportes de playa: kitesurf, submarinismo, SUP, y tambien para practicar golf (el campo de golf esta a solo 50 m), ciclismo y ofrece tambien una zona de arena compacta para correr junto al mar
El pueblo de Pals es un pueblo medieval se encuentra situado en la cima del Puig Aspre, desde donde se contempla una vista magnífica del Ampurdán pequeño o “Empurdanet”

La playa esta formada por dunas y pinos tiene una longitud de más de 3,5km y unas magníficas vistas sobre las Islas Medes

neighborhood_overview:
El loft está emplazado en un camino a 2 kilómetros de Sant Jordi Desvalls. Es un lugar donde reina la tranquilidad y el silencio. Un precioso paisaje de interior, rodeado de campos, huertos y bosques donde disfrutar de agradables paseos.
A escasos kilómetros de la casa se encuentran las playas más bonitas de la Costa Brava. A tan sólo 20 minutos en coche de l'Estartit, i l'Escala, y a 25 minutos de Girona. También podrás visitar numerosos pueblos con encanto. En la casa encontraríes la Guia de l'Empordà y recomandaciones.
En el pueblo de Sant Jordi Desvalls hay un pequeño supermercado de pueblo abierto todos los días; incluso los domingos.
host_about:
Nuestra familia siempre trabajó en el campo y nuestra ilusión de dar nueva vida a antiguos espacios utilizados para el ganado y sus cultivos nos llevaron a construir estas magníficas casas, respetando siempre el entorno y los lugares, con materiales honestos y de calidad.. 
Estaremos encantados de daros la bienvenida y explicaros lo que creemos es lo mejor y más bonito de la zona del Empordà y el Gironès.

name: 13 Calle Santa Maria In the heart of old Cadaqués
description:
In the heart of old Cadaqués, between the sea, 100 meters away, and Santa Maria Church, with its baroque altarpiece 23 m high, this family house can accommodate up to 10 people. Built on two floors, it has a large patio where between sun and shade you can have lunch and take a nap. On the second floor, a bay window overlooking the Riba Pitxot with its famous arcade painted by Dali, Picasso and many other painters who made Cadaqués their place of inspiration.

The space
This is an old house bought by my family in the 1950s when fresh water arrived by tanker. The current kitchen is installed in the old cistern. We tried to maintain the house in its original appearance by equipping it with a kitchen and modern bathrooms.

Guest access
The house is entirely up to you.

Other things to note
It is not possible to reach the house directly by car.
We advise you to park at Port-Alguer while you carry your luggage inside.
neighborhood_overview: The house is located in the old Cadaqués next to the Santa Maria church to visit for its altarpiece, near the town hall where often floats the Catalan flag and offers a beautiful view of the whole bay. This area is full of craft shops and small restaurants. The beach of Port-Alguer is a hundred meters where Ribat Pixot is famous for its arch and its view of the church and its tapas bar.

neighborhood_overview:
The village of L’Armentera has approximately 800 inhabitants. It’s very quiet and just a small number of its homes are second/holiday residences. There are supermarkets with excellent fruit and vegetables, butcher’s with high quality products, a fish shop with very fresh fish, restaurants and bars, some of them with free wifi. Agriculture is predominant, especially fruit crops.

From l’Armentera you can walk along the river Fluvià which is 500 m away, with instructions about paths, to cycle or walk. All its routes are beautiful. Especially the one along the river Fluvià, with leafy trees on its banks, its meanders, the fluvial island of Caramany and the estuary, There ‘s a sailing school there and you can rent small sailboats and canoes. The beach of Sant Pere Pescador, with fine sand, is very extensive, there’s always room, and because of its gentle slope is very suitable for children. At the end, holidays should be exactly the way we want them, right?

The Home Selector is the person who will help you choose the option most appropriate to your tastes. You will save time in searching and finding the best choice.

The Host is the person who will take care of you during the whole stay and try to find anything that you need with the help of the other hosts.

Let’s Holidays Home will be your second holiday home. A place where you will be able to meet with our Hosts, chat, have a glass of wine and listen to some live music.

We’ll love to meet you!

See you soon ;)

name: Rustic "Mas" farmhouse Emporda/Costa Brava/Girona
description:
Our wonderful rustic "Mas" farmhouse full of character in the quiet and serene Gavarres Nature Park/Baix Emporda between Palamos and Mont Ras near Palafrugell and Calella... far from the maddening crowd but just a stone's throw away from the beaches of Castell, La Fosca, Cala Estreta, etc on the Costa Brava.
Fully furnished & equipped by default, for 13 GUESTS.
However there is room, if necessary, for 2 more guests for an extra guest fee.

License # HUTG-017243

The space
Mas Cabré is a typical Catalan "mas" (farmhouse) built in 1842, according to the date chiseled on the front stone archway. However, it's been documented that a building of some kind already stood there in the 15th century. That's not surprising, since human presence in the area dates from prehistoric times and several dolmens and other Megalithic carvings can be found on the property or close to it.

During our renovations of Mas Cabré, we've kept its rustic, simp
neighborhood_overview:
Mas Cabre is all about location, location, location! You feel like you are far away from everything, almost in the middle of nowhere.

It is situated in the Gavarres Nature Park which is included in the European Union's Natura 2000 Network of protected areas whose goal is to ensure the long term survival of Europe's species and habitats in a sustainable manner.
The nearest house is 1 km away.
However you can see the sea from the house and the town and beaches of the Costa Brava are only minutes away.

Located in the beautifully scenic Baix Empordà region, in Catalonia, Mas Cabré belongs to the municipalities of Vall-Llobrega and Forallac, an area rich with history, great food and sports activities.
From there, you can visit old medieval towns or go to the beach; you can indulge in lunch or dinner by the sea or surrounded by nature; or you can visit a local winery and experience a wine tour.
And let's not forget bicycle trips, sailing, fishing

neighborhood_overview:
Blanes is located in the region of Catalonia, on the Costa Brava , 60 kilometers north of Barcelona airport .

Once a small fishing village, Blanes still retains some of its original charm ; The complex has a four kilometer stretch of coastline with sandy beaches and small rocky coves , most of which are equipped with water sports and other tourist facilities.

Moving away from the seafront you will find evidence of a town steeped in history, with ancient monuments , churches and buildings still standing as reminders of past colorful Blanes. The medieval castle of Sant Joan offers spectacular views over the harbor , beach and town.
In late July it marks the international fireworks competition , an impressive sight that can be seen from the beach every year.

The apartment is located in the old part of town, just 2 minutes away from the beach and high quality restaurants.
One minute away you will find the church plaza, where you can enjoy nice meals with a quiet and relaxing atmosphere, at the same time your kids play at the plaza without danger.
Just 2 minutes away, you will find a little supermarket and the commercial zone, where is difficult not to stop and watch the beautiful shops.

Tossa is a beautiful and quiet town, with a lot of charm. Ideal to travel with your couple, family or with the kids.
It is one of the most beautiful town in all Costa Brava, where you can steel feel the little old town atmosphere and where is not allowed to build tall buildings.
Besides enjoying the beaches, there are a lot other things to do. For example: walk around the old and narrow streets from the walled town "Vila Vella", go to the lighthouse and relax at the "Bar del Far", while you enjoy the incredible views of the rug
host_about:
We are Ana and Kristjàn and we’ve been offering accommodation in Tossa de Mar for over thirty years. Seven years ago, we were very happy to found Let’s Holidays.

The passion with which we’ve been working these past years has made us grow, and we now have a vast team of professionals working with us. 
With them, we will make sure to find the best option for you and to get you everything you will need during your stay :)

If there is something that we have learnt this past years is that we like to be treated the same way that we treat you. 
That’s where our philosophy comes from. We like to chat and we will try to get you anything that you need and find solutions to anything that you propose.

At the end, holidays should be exactly the way we want them, right?

We present some of our services :)

The Home Selector is the person who will help you choose the option most appropriate to your tastes. You will save time in searching and finding the best choice.

The Host is the person who will take care of you during the whole stay and try to find anything that you need with the help of the other hosts.

Let’s Holidays Home will be your second holiday home. A place where you will be able to meet with our Hosts, chat, have a glass of wine and listen to some live music.

We’ll love to meet you!

See you soon ;) 

Here you have all our options

name: La Sirenita Apartment - HUTG-018865-86
description:
A fantastic location front line to the sea - superb location, free ADSL WiFi!
TV in Spanish, French, German and some English available.
Parking space in front of apt! Walking distance of 7 minutes to beach Palangres, walk to Canyelles Petites (10 mins) or town of Roses with large choice of restaurants, bars!
Hear the sea from the apartment and just walk down the steps onto the coastal path and direct access to the rocks to swim and sunbathe. The apartment is on the ground level so easy access!

The space
Front line to the sea with superb sea views and over the Bay of Roses to the Isle of Medes in the distance which can be enjoyed from the outside private terrace for dining or the open planned kitchen/dining room/ lounge. The bedroom is spacious with one double bed and fitted wardrobes and there is a sofa bed in the lounge. It is perfect for 2 adults. No car needed!
TV offers: Full Spanish, Full French, Full German and some English and other eu
neighborhood_overview:
This area of the coast of Costa Brava is just beautiful! I have traveled all over the world and this area is hard to beat!
There are many things to see and do in this area including most types of water sports, boat trips, water park, go karts, horse riding, cycling, sky diving (wind tunnel also available) in Empuriabrava plus much more.
Out of season it is very quiet and a superb location for walking.
If you like walking then it's perfect to enjoy the stunning scenery along the coastal path or up into the national park of Cap de Creus or take a boat trip along the coast round to Cadaques which is really worth while.

You can walk to the sandy cove of Palangrers (7 mins), Canyelles Petites (10-15 mins), Almadrava (20-30 mins) or Roses main beach and town in under 15 minutes. If you want to hike further you can walk to many other coves along the coastal path including Cala Montjoi, Cala Joncols, walk to Cadaques or even further afield time permitting!
It i
host_about:
Hi, I love to travel although do not do enough of it nowadays! I like to think that our guests have the best experience in our accommodations, that they have everything they need and a very comfortable stay.
This area is fantastic to explore and we do all we can to make sure you enjoy it as much as we do. We have lived her for 18 years+!
I hope we meet soon!

host_about:
Sleep and Stay is a professional holiday rental agency and licensed Real estate Agency.
All our properties are carefully selected and we prioritize customer service, a personal touch and impecable cleaning. We leave a welcome package with cleaning products (dishwasher tablets, laundry tablets, sponge, cloth and extra garbage bags) and first essentials like coffee, tea, sugar, salt, pepper, olive oil and vinegar. Those items you just need for a couple of days away, are just great to have at your disposal. 
Most people that visit Girona once, never want to leave again. They want to come back, because Girona has it all. We recently opened a branch in Besalu which is small medieval copy of Girona. We have beaches, culture of Dali, the great Spanish kitchen with lot’s of different tapas and wines, old medieval villages and mountains great for skiing, hiking and cycling! What else do you want?

That’s why we fell in love with Girona and made it our business of helping people to find their dream holiday home for a week’s stay or even to buy a property and have a second home in this amazing region! Sleep & Stay is owned by Jolien Huizing Gerrans, Dutch nationality, and she has surrounded herself by an amazing team. Sonia (Polish) and Luis (Honduras). We personally manage each holiday property that are featured on this website and are experts in the Girona property market for more than 4 years. We all speak next to our mother tongues Spanish, Catalan and English which makes all language barriers disappear!

As a young and dynamic holiday rental organisation, specialised in amazing holiday rentals, property management and property finder services. We can assist you in finding a special place to stay in Girona. We value quality, comfort and well maintained holiday rentals as our most important goals. We want to find that charming place for you that makes you fall in love with Girona too and makes you want to stay forever.

Once you arrive and you need anything, we are here to help you. Available on (Hidden by Airbnb) , email and we're just a phone call away. Welcome to come and stay with us!

name: H2 Habitación doble / Mas Ferran
description:
Masferran is a project of its owner, Ferran, who, once the house restoration was completed decided to open it to the public and share this privileged space in l'Empordà to enjoy an intimate and relaxed stay.
The style was respected adapting it to the current comforts.
We recommend gastronomic routes, outdoor activities and cultural visits.
There is a wide selection of restaurants in the area and a very complete supermarket 3 minutes walk away.

The space
H2
Romantic and quiet 40 m² room. Special design, has integrated bathroom with shower, desk, King size bed, sofa, TV, heating, fan. Access to private terrace and solarium with garden views.
Relaxing decoration in warm tones, with restored furniture combined with modern pieces and natural materials.
100% cotton bed and bath linen.
Quality amenities and hair dryer.
It can accommodate 3 people upon request.
The rest of the rooms, such as kitchen, living room, dining room,
neighborhood_overview: Pals is at the epicenter of the Golden Triangle of Baix Empordà. It's a beautiful area, with marvelous beaches and quite central; perfect for visiting medieval villages and enjoying outdoor, cultural or gastronomic routes.
host_about:
Masferran es un proyecto de su propietario, Ferran, que compró con mucha ilusión esta casa de pueblo. Una vez finalizada la restauración decidió abrirla al público y compartir este espacio privilegiado en l’Empordà.
La restauración se hizo respetando el estilo pero adaptado a las comodidades actuales creando un espacio único para disfrutar de una estancia íntima y relajada.
Trabajamos fuera de casa pero estamos siempre disponibles para asesorar, orientar y hacer recomendaciones sobre la zona a nuestros huéspedes, aunque dejándoles espacio y privacidad para que se sientan cómodos en casa.
Ofrecemos aconsejar rutas gastronómicas, actividades al aire libre y visitas culturales. El espacio está abierto a mostrar arte local y informar de marcados y anticuarios.
Nuestras habitaciones tienen baño privado con ducha, artículos de baño y secador; cama King size, TV, adaptadores usb, altavoces bluetooth, aire acondicionado, ventilador. 
El resto de estancias, como cocina, sala de estar, comedor, jardín, son compartidas con el resto de huéspedes.
Servicio diario de habitaciones.
Ofrecemos wifi gratuita en toda la casa.

description:
Well illuminated double bedroom overlooking the garden and fish pond.
Has windows on two sides therefore received the sun for most of the day.
This room is not "en suite". It has its own private bathroom adjacent to the bedroom.
Casa Dos Torres is on the road to the beach which is a 5 minute walk away.
A full description is available is available on the casadostorres website.

The space
Casa Dos Torres is a registered "pension" in Calella de Palafrugell.
We described ourselves as a Bed and Breakfast but this category does not exist here in Sapin therefore we have been given the registration "P" by the Generalitat de Catalunya.

Guest access
Guests are permitted to use our kitchen facilities. This year with the pandemia the kitchen facilities will not be available.
There is free WiFi.
We have a pretty garden with numerous seating areas plus a swimming pool (in season).

Other things to note
neighborhood_overview:
Calella de Palafrugell is an old fishing village. It's centre has retained the original "look" of the place but it has grown considerably over the years.
It still does retain a charm and beauty which attracts people from all over the world.
Calella de Palafrugell is a well known seaside "village in The Costa Brava much frequented by the local Catalans.
The first Saturday in July each year there is the Havanares Festival.
Throughout July and August the Cap Roig gardens hold regular concerts.
This year there may not be concerts!

The space
Salón/comedor, baño, cocina completa, 2 habitaciones dobles. y gran terraza.
Lo realmente espectacular de Tossa de Mar son sus Calas, playa y Gran Muralla medieval, que hoy sigue viva en su interior, ya que sigue estando habitada por casas, restaurantes, tiendas. Paseando podrán llegar a visitar el Faro, se encuentra en el punto mas alto, aquí cada tarde/noche se puede disfrutar de música en directo mientras tomas una copa.
La comunicación al resto de pueblos en la Costa Brava es fantástica para los mas viajeros. Barcelona y Gerona están a tan solo 1 hora de camino para poder visitarlas en coche o autobuses disponibles desde Tossa. También es esa distancia hasta sus aeropuertos.

description:
Masferran is a project of its owner, Ferran, who, once the haouse restoration was completed decided to open it to the public and share this privileged space in l'Empordà to enjoy an intimate and relaxed stay.
The style was respected adapting it to the current comforts.
We recommend gastronomic routes, outdoor activities and cultural visits.
There is a wide selection of restaurants in the area and a very complete supermarket 3 minutes walk away.

The space
H4
Intimate 30 m² room. Silent and relaxing, it is located in the garden. Singularly decorated, it has a King size bed, armchair, TV, air conditioning, heating, integrated bathroom with shower. Beautiful combination of natural materials and sense of spaciousness.
100% cotton bed and bath linen.
Quality amenities and hair dryer.
The rest of the rooms, such as kitchen, living room, dining room, garden, are shared with the rest of the guests.
Masferran has various silent space
neighborhood_overview: Pals is at the epicenter of the Golden Triangle of Baix Empordà. It's a beautiful area, with marvelous beaches and quite central; perfect for visiting medieval villages and enjoying outdoor, cultural or gastronomic routes.
host_about:
Masferran es un proyecto de su propietario, Ferran, que compró con mucha ilusión esta casa de pueblo. Una vez finalizada la restauración decidió abrirla al público y compartir este espacio privilegiado en l’Empordà.
La restauración se hizo respetando el estilo pero adaptado a las comodidades actuales creando un espacio único para disfrutar de una estancia íntima y relajada.
Trabajamos fuera de casa pero estamos siempre disponibles para asesorar, orientar y hacer recomendaciones sobre la zona a nuestros huéspedes, aunque dejándoles espacio y privacidad para que se sientan cómodos en casa.
Ofrecemos aconsejar rutas gastronómicas, actividades al aire libre y visitas culturales. El espacio está abierto a mostrar arte local y informar de marcados y anticuarios.
Nuestras habitaciones tienen baño privado con ducha, artículos de baño y secador; cama King size, TV, adaptadores usb, altavoces bluetooth, aire acondicionado, ventilador. 
El resto de estancias, como cocina, sala de estar, comedor, jardín, son compartidas con el resto de huéspedes.
Servicio diario de habitaciones.
Ofrecemos wifi gratuita en toda la casa.

description:

Ideal para parejas.Tienes barbacoa , aire acondicionado para el verano y piscina compartida. Hay wifi en toda la casa y podrás aparcar el coche delante de casa sin ningún problema.El apartamento se encuentra en la planta baja de mi casa en una zona residencial muy tranquila y bien comunicada, a 15" en coche de Girona a 10" de Besalú y 5" de Banyolas.
Nº Registro HUTG-020565

The space
Este acogedor apartamento te permitirá sentirte como en casa consta de una amplia cocina-comedor, salón con un sofa y dos butacas, chimenea de leña, aire acondicionado, calefacción cama doble de 1,80x2, dos armarios, lavabo y ducha.
Solo tendrás que llevar el equipaje.
Hay todo los utensilios necesarios de cocina: tostadora, exprimidor, batidora, picadora, cafetera, microondas... también encontraréis aliños, especies y café .
En el baño dispon
neighborhood_overview:
Lo que mas me gusta de donde vivo es que estoy lo bastante lejos del ajetreo y tráfico de la ciudad, pero muy cerca de todo. Todos los servicios (supermercados, farmacias, tiendas, restaurantes, bares,etc...) los tienes a 5 minutos en coche.
Es una zona residencial muy tranquila. Con una plaza delante de casa y sin problemas para aparcar.
Hay un Hostal que tiene servicio de bar y restaurante a 1 minuto a pie de casa.
Para hacer las compras puedes ir a Cornella del Terri que hay un pequeño supermercado, carnicería, verdulería, panadería, farmácia y dos bancos "La CAIXA" y Banco Popular se encuentra a unos 800m de casa (mejor en coche). La otra opción es ir a comprar en Banyoles, esta a 3km, 5minutos en coche. Donde encontraras todos los supermercados en el mismo lugar ( Mercadona, Aldi, Dia, Lidl, Bon Preu,etc ....)
En 10 minutos estas en el lago de Banyoles donde podrás relajarte, pasear y respirar tranquilamente.
A 15 minutos estas en el centro de Girona,
host_about:
Tengo 44 años, dos hijas estupendas y  dos gatos .
Soy positiva y alegre. Me gusta hacer deporte y todo lo relacionado con la salud.
Intercambiar experiencias con otras personas me encanta.
Cada día es una oportunidad y cada oportunidad una experiencia.

name: Relax and feel Girona
description:
Estudio totalmente reformado, en pleno casco antiguo de Girona, entre el rio y la catedral a 5 minutos de todos los puntos de interes de la ciudad. Un espacio donde relajarse, sentir y descansar.

The space
Distribuido en dos espacios, tu decides si abrirlos o cerrarlos. Divididos por dos puertas correderas, mi consejo... no las cierres! Salón y cocina totalmente equipados, habitación con cama doble y escritorio con material de papelería por si te inspiras., baño y dos balcones al casco antiguo. El apartmento es soleado, con mucha luz y porticones con vidrios dobles. Dispone de calefacción, wifi, sábanas y toallas, Cafetera Dolche Gusto, café, lavadora, secador de pelo, plancha y productos mínimos necesarios para que la estancia no sea interrumpida.

Other things to note

neighborhood_overview: Una vez llegues, Laura, la anfitriona, te aconsejará sobre los mejores lugares donde ir según tus intenciones. Locales de copas, restaurantes, heladerias, creperias, parques, rincones tranquilos, los mejores lugares para ver las puestas de sol, rutas de montaña o playa, y algunas excursiones cerca de la ciudad.
host_about:
Hola! soy Jorge, Diseñador y Acrobata aéreo de profesión, dedico mi tiempo al arte, dirijo Onair, la primera escuela de danza aerea de España afincada en Barcelona. Me apasionan los colores, este año sobretodo el amarillo, soy detallista, impulsivo, obserbador, gran anfitrion y amigo de mi gente. Vivo con Julieta mi querida perra en Barcelona y nuestro estudio en Girona en pleno casco antiguo es nuestro refugio para el descanso, el paseo y el lugar donde nos inspiran historias nuevas.
Hemos decidido compartir con todos vosotros nuestro espacio para que podais disfrutar y sentir lo magnifico que es pasar unos dias en esta ciudad, rodeada de historia, entre las grandes montañas y las mejores playas. Si algo tiene Girona, es que enamora. 

Si quieres conocer más sobre mi y mi trabajo puedes entrar en este enlace, (Website hidden by Airbnb) , no hay mayor reflejo sobre mi que mi propio trabajo.

name: Beautiful mediterranean villa
description:
Do you want to wake up with a breathtaking view of the sea, while enjoying a peaceful environment on the heights of Platja d'Aro?

This 4 bedroom villa is for you!

The house has a pool, a fully furnished kitchen, a large living room, and the possibility to park 2 cars.

The space
While being very close to various beaches, restaurants/bars or shops (10mins) this mediterranean villa still allows to enjoy tranquility with a large terrasse with a stunning sea view.

The house has 4 bedrooms, with the possibility to add an additional baby bed, 2 separate bathrooms and 1 additional toilet. The kitchen is fully furnished and has all the basics (oil, pepper,...). Furthermore, the terrasse has a barbecue next to the pool, ideal for summer evenings.

Moreover, the pool is located toward the sea, which is ideal for a morning swim before breakfast.

Guest access
The villa is easily accessible by car and is located
neighborhood_overview:
Platja d'Aro is an animated town in the heart of the Costa Brava, which is known for its beaches but also for its gastronomy and its wine. The city hosts many festivals during the summer such as the free "Nits the Jazz", which hosts jazz concerts once a week during the whole summer.

There is a lot of restaurants, bars, nightclubs as well as outdoors activities, such as minigolfs,acquatic activities, horse riding and many walking or cycling routes in the area.

Moreover, the well-know Golf d'Aro is minutes away from the house, on the same hill.

A small food store is a five-minute drive away, on the hill, in the Hapimag complex.

The house is approximately 1 hour away from Barcelona, 30min from Girona. There is also numerous traditional villages in the area.

disponen de toda la ropa de cama - Sábanas - Mantas - Edredones - Toallas.

A 6 km del pueblo Sant Joan les Fonts (Girona) encontramos Castellar de la Muntanya en un valle que forma parte del espacio protegido de la Alta Garrotxa. Castella
neighborhood_overview: A 6 km del pueblo Sant Joan les Fonts (Girona) encontramos Castellar de la Muntanya en un valle que forma parte del espacio protegido de la Alta Garrotxa. Castellar está situado a una altura de 650 metros sobre el nivel del mar, desde donde podemos disfrutar de vistas al Canigo, esta montaña es la mas alta de los pirineos orientales y durante gran parte del año su cima está cubierta de nieve. Mirando hacia el oeste tenemos una vista panorámica de las montañas de la Alta Garrotxa y a lo lejos, el mar. El paisaje es una policromía en la que predomina el verde, salpicando montañas, prados, bosques, barrancos y torrentes.

description:
Acogedora masía ampurdanesa, muy bien restaurada y equipada. Está situada a muy poca distancia de Banyoles, Girona y de las playas de la Costa Brava, por lo que permite hacer visitas culturales, rutas gastronómicas y numerosas actividades al aire libre.

Masía del siglo XVIII rodeada de jardín con piscina, bosques y campos de cultivo. La casa cuenta con cuatro habitaciones, todas con baño privado, y las estancias, que conservan los bonitos techos abovedados, están decoradas con un estilo rústico y elegante. La cocina abierta con el comedor y también la sala de estar cuentan con chimenea.

Cottage form the seventeenth century restored in 2015. The house is in a quiet area surrounded by nature.
It has 4 bedrooms with private bathrooms, kitchen, living room and large garden with pool.

Inside the house you will find: fully equipped kitchen, dining room, lounge (with TV, DVD and games) and common toilet on the ground floor.
In the first floor there a
neighborhood_overview: Can Font Olives está ubicada en el pequeño núcleo urbano de Olives, a ocho kilómetros de Vilademuls, en pleno Empordà. Su situación permite llegar rápidamente a Banyoles, en cuyo lago se puede hacer senderismo, ciclismo, remo y natación, y a Girona, donde se puede visitar su bonito centro histórico. description:
Beautiful and centric apartment, very close to the beach, at a very quiet zone.
Perfectly located, just 2 minutes walking to the beach and really close to shops, supermakets, restaurants and more.

The space
The apartment has wifi included in the price. It has 3 bedrooms, 2 bathrooms, dinning room, big kitchen and a terrace where you can see a little part of the sea.
Fully equipped with all the necessary amenities: dishwasher, terrace furniture, comfortable matresses and more. This will make your stay really comfortable.
Wonderful awning at the terrace, with microperforated material, will give you protection from the sun, but won’t bother the views.
AC in the entire apartment.

neighborhood_overview:
The apartment is very well located, in a very centric zone and at the same time very quiet.
Less than 2 minutes walking you have the beach, restaurants, supermarkets and much more.
Two minutes away you have the commercial area, where is really hard not to stop and check all the beautiful shops

Tossa is a beautiful and quiet town, with a lot of charm. Ideal to travel with your couple, family or with the kids.
It is one of the most beautiful town in all Costa Brava, where you can steel feel the little old town atmosphere and where is not allowed to build tall buildings.
Besides enjoying the beaches, there are a lot other things to do. For example: walk around the old and narrow streets from the walled town "Vila Vella", go the the lighthouse and relax at the "Bar del Far", while you enjoy the incredible views of the rugged coastline and the cliffs. Walk around the comercial area, full of little shops, incredible tours to the mountain, bike rides, ship tours
host_about:
We are Ana and Kristjàn and we’ve been offering accommodation in Tossa de Mar for over thirty years. Seven years ago, we were very happy to found Let’s Holidays.

The passion with which we’ve been working these past years has made us grow, and we now have a vast team of professionals working with us. 
With them, we will make sure to find the best option for you and to get you everything you will need during your stay :)

If there is something that we have learnt this past years is that we like to be treated the same way that we treat you. 
That’s where our philosophy comes from. We like to chat and we will try to get you anything that you need and find solutions to anything that you propose.

At the end, holidays should be exactly the way we want them, right?

We present some of our services :)

The Home Selector is the person who will help you choose the option most appropriate to your tastes. You will save time in searching and finding the best choice.

The Host is the person who will take care of you during the whole stay and try to find anything that you need with the help of the other hosts.

Let’s Holidays Home will be your second holiday home. A place where you will be able to meet with our Hosts, chat, have a glass of wine and listen to some live music.

We’ll love to meet you!

See you soon ;)

All amenities: Wi-Fi, washer, dish washer, micro wave, fridge, TV. Located on completely fenced large estate with private parking.

The space
This cute and cozy cottage is ideally located a few steps from the beach and has beautiful views of the Mediterranean sea. It can accommodate up to 5 persons and was recently totally renovated. It has all amenities: wi-fi, TV, NETFLIX, washing machine, dish washer, air conditioning, large terrace, barbecue. There is one bedroom on a mezzanine with a large bed. name: Chambre privée et petit déjeuner pour 2 personnes
description:
Réservez une chambre indépendante du reste de la maison avec sa propre sale de bain privée et sa propre entrée depuis le jardin.
Vous pourrez profiter du jardin, de la cuisine (jusqu'à 21:00). Aussi, des vélos sont mis gratuitement à votre disposition, et vous pouvez profiter de la piscine. Le petit déjeuner est également inclus dans le prix.

The space
Ce n'est pas un logement luxueux ... Il séduira les voyageurs ainsi que tout ceux qui aiment la quiétude et les rencontres. C'est une chambre simple, propre, commode. Parfaite pour dormir et se reposer.

Guest access
Les voyageurs pourront profiter de toute la maison, ainsi que de son jardin, de ses chaises longues, de sa piscine et des vélos qui sont fournis.

neighborhood_overview: C'est un quartier très calme ou s'y trouve le golf d'Empuriabrava. (Pitch and Put). Un supermarché s'y trouve également.
host_about: J'aime tout et tout le monde... Je suis français mais je vis en Espagne depuis 2012. J'adore ce pays et ses habitants. Je parle français et espagnol. J'essaie d'apprendre l'anglais... :-/ Je suis jovial, sportif et heureux. Je vis très simplement et j'adore ça.

name: Casa Playa a Santa Maria de Llorell
description:
La casa si trova sulla spiaggia del villaggio privato di Santa Maria de Llorell. Sono affittati il piano alto ed il piano medio, quello basso resta a disposizione dei proprietari. Appartamento elegante e confortevole, splendida vista sul mare.

The space
L'alloggio è reso unico dalla posizione. La casa è costruita a ridosso della spiaggia ed il mare dista pochi metri. Al piano superiore ci sono cucina, soggiorno/salotto e sala da pranzo, bagnetto. Al secondo piano le tre camere da letto e due bagni. Su ciascun piano una piccola terrazza con vista mare.

Guest access
Gli inquilini potranno alloggiare sui due piani superiori. Quello più basso non viene affittato e rimane ad uso dei proprietari che normalmente lo usano durante le vacanze estive.

Other things to note
A disposizione degli inquilini ci sono letti per sei persone. In più c'è un divano letto ad una piazza e mezzo. Adattandosi ci possono stare otto persone.
neighborhood_overview: Santa Maria de Llorell è una "urbanisaciòn", villaggio privato a cui possono accedere solo i veicoli autorizzati, che vengono controllati all'ingresso e all'uscita. La spiaggia è accessibile unicamente dal villaggio e dal limitrofo campeggio (Cala llevadò).

Ac ceso a mi despacho El Tura: 

Llegando a Barcelona & Girona, si toman la NII, a la altura de Orriols, hay el cruce de l’Escala -  Empuries ( a la derecha) si toman la Autopista AP7/E15, por favor salen por la Salida 5 “L’Escala – Empuries”.  Llegando a la L’Escala por la Gi 623, encontrarán lo puntos giratorios de St. Martí d’Empuries  y del Camp dels Pilans, siempre tendrán que tomar la dirección Riells – Montgó. A la llegada de la población, como referencia encontrarán un puesta de la Cruz Roja, el supermercado Champion y una torreta de los bomberos. La dirección de la agencia el Tura es Avda. Montgó, nº 21ª.

Acces a mon agence el Tura

En arrivant de France, par l’Autoroute AP7/E15, vous prennez la sortie 5: L’Escala – Empúries. Si vous prennez la Route Nationale II (aprés Figueres) il ya la sortie ver l’Escala, pour la route C252. En arrivant a l’Escala, il y a les ronds  points de St. Martí d’Empuries et del Camp dels Pilans, il faut prendre toujours direction  Riells – Montgó. En arrivant, vous aurez comme points de reference la Croix Rouge, le supermarché Champion et une tour de sourveillance des Pompiers. L’adress de mon agence El Tura c’est Avda. Montgó, nº 21ª.

neighborhood_overview:
The apartment is very well located, right next to the beach, supermarket, restaurants.
In less than 3 minutes walk find, most central area with all kinds of shops, banks.

Tossa is a beautiful and quiet town, with a lot of charm. Ideal to travel with your couple, family or with the kids.
It is one of the most beautiful town in all Costa Brava, where you can steel feel the little old town atmosphere and where is not allowed to build tall buildings.
Besides enjoying the beaches, there are a lot other things to do. For example: walk around the old and narrow streets from the walled town "Vila Vella", go to the lighthouse and relax at the "Bar del Far", while you enjoy the incredible views of the rugged coastline and the cliffs. Walk around the commercial area, full of little shops, incredible tours to the mountain, bike rides, ship tours, visit all the little and hidden beaches around, and so many other things we can recommend, according to your needs.
For yo
host_about:
We are Ana and Kristjàn and we’ve been offering accommodation in Tossa de Mar for over thirty years. Seven years ago, we were very happy to found Let’s Holidays.

The passion with which we’ve been working these past years has made us grow, and we now have a vast team of professionals working with us. 
With them, we will make sure to find the best option for you and to get you everything you will need during your stay :)

If there is something that we have learnt this past years is that we like to be treated the same way that we treat you. 
That’s where our philosophy comes from. We like to chat and we will try to get you anything that you need and find solutions to anything that you propose.

At the end, holidays should be exactly the way we want them, right?

We present some of our services :)

The Home Selector is the person who will help you choose the option most appropriate to your tastes. You will save time in searching and finding the best choice.

The Host is the person who will take care of you during the whole stay and try to find anything that you need with the help of the other hosts.

Let’s Holidays Home will be your second holiday home. A place where you will be able to meet with our Hosts, chat, have a glass of wine and listen to some live music.

We’ll love to meet you!

See you soon ;)

name: CAN DOU alojamiento rural nº PG-799
description:
CAN DOU Se encuentra en un privilegiado emplazamiento en la Garrotxa, Girona, junto al núcleo urbano de Les Planes d’Hostoles. Un espacio adecuado para disfrutar de los volcanes, la Via Verda del Carrilet y multitud de cascadas y pozas de cristalina agua.
Es un conjunto de dos casas rurales independientes: La Masía, que data del s. XVIII, y el Antiguo Establo.
Piscina para uso exclusivo de las personas alojadas en la Masia.

The space
La masía está dispuesta en dos plantas. En la planta baja se encuentra el comedor-cocina, la sala de estar con chimenea, un baño, un dormitorio de matrimonio y un segundo dormitorio.
En la planta piso se encuentra otro baño y una gran sala que da acceso a dos dormitorios de matrimonio y a un tercer dormitorio.
La cocina esta totalmente equipada con nevera, placa de inducción, microondas, lavavajillas, etc… la casa también dispone durante el verano de internet via wifi.

Guest access
Gran ja
neighborhood_overview:
CAN DOU está situado en la localidad de Les Planes d’Hostoles, en la provincia de Girona. Se encuentra entre el Parque Natural de la Zona Volcánica de la Garrotxa y el Espacio de Interés Natural de Collsacabra.
La comarca de La Garrotxa cuenta con multitud de núcleos urbanos interesantes para visitar: Sant Feliu de Pallarols, Olot, Santa Pau, Besalú,…
Además nos encontramos a 1,25 hrs. (115 km.) de Barcelona. 55 min (65 km.) de la Costa Brava, 1,11 hrs. (68 km) de Francia y a 34 km. del Aeropuerto de Girona|Costa Brava.
host_about:
Hola, mi nombre es Ramon. Quiero invitaros a que  disfrutéis de esta fantástica tierra que es la Garrotxa, seguro que os encantara. Por nuestra parte pondremos todo nuestro empeño en que así sea. 
Recibid un fuerte abrazo garrotxi... :-)

neighborhood_overview:
The Old Town of Girona is considered the historical center of the city, bounded by the medieval city wall, part of which was demolished in the nineteenth century, and is where we find the most important historic and cultural attractions of the city.
The houses on the river Onyar are a sight which must be enjoyed from one of the bridges crossing the river, and we approach the Jewish quarter from the Rambla. In the promenade bustle of visitors and locals, strolling, shopping, resting live.
Once entered in the Jewish Quarter, one of the best preserved in Spain, we can enjoy the historic legacy of the city, letting lose through the narrow streets and right steps, discovering corners, gardens, monuments and churches, between steps. The Cathedral, the church of Sant Feliu, the Arab Baths, Sant Pere de Galligants.
host_about:
Hola!!

Soy Anna, una gironina enamorada de su pequeña ciudad.

Vivo en Girona y trabajo en una tienda de antigüedades situada a los pies de nuestra magnifica catedral. Gracias a mi trabajo puedo pasear a diario por estas calles que esconden tantas historias apasionantes.

Soy una amante del arte y de la decoración.

Espero os guste el apartamento que ofrezco que he decorado con tanto cariño.

Os espero pronto!

Hello,

I am Anna and I am in love with my marvelous city.

I live in Girona and I work in an antic shop situated just in front of the Cathedral. 
Thanks to my job I can walk everyday through the streets that hide so many exciting stories.

I am an art lover and I love decorating.

I do hope you like the apartment which I have decorate with so much love

I see you soon!

name: CAN DOU el Antiguo Establo nº PG-000961
description:
CAN DOU Se encuentra en un privilegiado emplazamiento en la Garrotxa, Girona, junto al núcleo urbano de Les Planes d’Hostoles. Un espacio adecuado para disfrutar de los volcanes, la Via Verda del Carrilet y multitud de cascadas y pozas de cristalina agua.
Es un conjunto de dos casas rurales independientes: La Masía, que data del s. XVIII, y el Antiguo Establo. Cada alojamiento cuenta con su propia piscina.

The space
En Can Dou el edificio del antiguo establo, se ha reconvertido en un espacio singular. La vida se desarrolla alrededor de la pérgola situada bajo un nogal y un abeto, desde donde tenemos una fantástica vista de la Vall d’Hostoles.
El antiguo establo tiene capacidad para 2 personas, ideal para parejas o familias con niños pequeños, al tener en el espacio común una cama de matrimonio y un sofá cama, ademas de los espacios de la cocina y el baño.
Se encuentra totalmente equipado con placa de vitrocerámica, microondas, nevera con congela
neighborhood_overview:
CAN DOU está situado en la localidad de Les Planes d’Hostoles, en la provincia de Girona. Se encuentra entre el Parque Natural de la Zona Volcánica de la Garrotxa y el Espacio de Interés Natural de Collsacabra.
La comarca de La Garrotxa cuenta con multitud de núcleos urbanos interesantes para visitar: Sant Feliu de Pallarols, Olot, Santa Pau, Besalú,…
Además nos encontramos a 1,25 hrs. (115 km.) de Barcelona. 55 min (65 km.) de la Costa Brava, 1,11 hrs. (68 km) de Francia y a 34 km. del Aeropuerto de Girona|Costa Brava.
host_about:
Hola, mi nombre es Ramon. Quiero invitaros a que  disfrutéis de esta fantástica tierra que es la Garrotxa, seguro que os encantara. Por nuestra parte pondremos todo nuestro empeño en que así sea. 
Recibid un fuerte abrazo garrotxi... :-)

host_about:
LLevo dedicandome 25 años al alquiler turístico. Me importa la buena relación con propietarios y huéspedes. Mi experiencia y empatía hace que tanto unos cómo otros quedan contenos y vuelven cada año a alquilar conmigo por que hay buena relación! 

Ac ceso a mi despacho El Tura: 

Llegando a Barcelona & Girona, si toman la NII, a la altura de Orriols, hay el cruce de l’Escala -  Empuries ( a la derecha) si toman la Autopista AP7/E15, por favor salen por la Salida 5 “L’Escala – Empuries”.  Llegando a la L’Escala por la Gi 623, encontrarán lo puntos giratorios de St. Martí d’Empuries  y del Camp dels Pilans, siempre tendrán que tomar la dirección Riells – Montgó. A la llegada de la población, como referencia encontrarán un puesta de la Cruz Roja, el supermercado Champion y una torreta de los bomberos. La dirección de la agencia el Tura es Avda. Montgó, nº 21ª.

Acces a mon agence el Tura

En arrivant de France, par l’Autoroute AP7/E15, vous prennez la sortie 5: L’Escala – Empúries. Si vous prennez la Route Nationale II (aprés Figueres) il ya la sortie ver l’Escala, pour la route C252. En arrivant a l’Escala, il y a les ronds  points de St. Martí d’Empuries et del Camp dels Pilans, il faut prendre toujours direction  Riells – Montgó. En arrivant, vous aurez comme points de reference la Croix Rouge, le supermarché Champion et une tour de sourveillance des Pompiers. L’adress de mon agence El Tura c’est Avda. Montgó, nº 21ª.

host_about:
Hola! Som la família Xargay. 

En Pere, constructor d’ofici, és un apassionat amb la seva feina. Ha rehabilitat i restaurat la casa pairal incorporant la comoditat i confort dels habitatges actuals però cuidant tots els detalls. És el pare de la família.

La Dolors, treballadora de mena i incansable, prepara la casa per deixar-la a punt i per atendre la vostra arribada. És la mare de la família però també és el pilar de la casa.

La Raquel, química, li encanta estudiar idiomes però també li agrada donar-vos la benvinguda a la casa i explicar-vos totes les activitats que ofereix la zona.

La Sílvia, alegre, treballadora i biòloga de professió. És la germana mitjana de les tres.

name: Villa Sa Riera, beautiful 6 bedroom home, own pool
description:
This amazing villa was completely refurbished to a very high standard for the 2017 season. It has six air conditioned bedrooms, three doubles, two twins and a triple and 5 beautiful bathrooms. The villa has its own swimming pool which is adjacent to a large terrace with great views of the sea and the Islas Medes.

The space
Sleeps 13 (with a maximum of 10 adults) in 3 double (all en suite) 1 triple and 2 twin bed rooms. (one en suite)

All bedrooms air conditioned

Own Pool

All linen, bath and pool towels included

TV/ DVD player

Apple TV

Cots and high chairs for babies included free

Outside lunch table under Beautiful olive tree perfect for long lunches!

Outdoor teppanyaki wood fired hotplate and barbecue

Welcome pack included with essentials (including wine!) for your arrival

Mid week clean included in price

Amazing views

fast interne
neighborhood_overview:
The villa is situated in one of the most beautiful areas of Spain – the Costa Brava. The Costa Brava is a rocky coastline, plentiful in coves, secluded beaches and little fishing villages. The beautiful beach of Sa Riera, right in the heart of this coast and recognised as being one of the jewels of the Costa Brava, is about 15 minutes walk from the villa.

Begur, a well-known medieval town is about 10 minutes walk. from Villa Begur. Begur has cobbled streets, with a large central square surrounded by pavement cafes. There is a great mixture of fine restaurants, tapas bars, and even a fantastic open air pizza restaurant. There are also plenty of late night bars which cater mostly to the style conscious Barcelonians, no English pubs or rave clubs in this town. There are also many stylish independant boutiques which, in the Summer months, are open late into the cool evenings.

This part of the Costa Brava is much more a getaway for Spaniards than it is a mecca for fore
host_about: The Blandfords have owned Villa Begur since 2003 and Villa Sa Riera since 2016. We love the area and spend much of the Summer there if we can.

name: Villa in pine woods overlooking bay, walk to beach
description:
Cosy rustic villa in pine wood - large salt water pool close to the beach and the town. Spectacular views across Sant Pol bay and up the Mediterranean towards Palamos. Enjoy the peace and tranquility of this cozy villa that sits in a fantastic location within walking distance of one of the most beautiful bays on the Costa Brava, Spain.
Perfect for cycling groups, some of the best routes in Europe, many pro teams based here. Now with 1 GB fibre wifi! All InternationalTV and sport channels

The space
Villa L'Esplai can truly boast the title for best location, location, location. Perched overlooking the bay of Sant Pol it is possible to walk to the beach - which is probably the best for restaurants, beauty and activities in the Costa Brava - King Juan Carlos II and many celebrities choose to have a house here!

Guest access
Our guests rent the whole villa which has a stunning garden and a pool which is large, heated, salt water and ha
neighborhood_overview: L'Esplai is situated in an area where you can see snow on the mountain caps of the Pyrenees almost all the year round while standing on the terrace watching the sun glisten off the ripples of the azure blue Mediterranean while sipping a cool drink.  The coastline is generally regarded as one of the most beautiful in all of Europe and there are rocky coves with sea caves and steep cliffs for sea diving and snorkeling or long sandy beaches, ideal for toddlers to play all day in the safe Mediterranean sea.
host_about:
Hi - My partner, Janice, and I moved to this amazing part of the Mediterranean coast almost 14 years ago now, and we love it so much that we still feel that we have only just moved here.  We are lucky enough to have two villas here that we are able to rent out and over the years we feel we have become pretty good at providing a complete rounded holiday experience for our guests.

Before we moved to the Costa Brava we lived and worked in the hustle and bustle of London where I created my greatest legacy which was the funding and technical platform for JustGiving which is now the world's largest and most successful charitable donations website.  

Janice worked for a prestigious legal publishing house in the City and while we both thoroughly enjoyed our time in London it is nice to find ourselves truly in Paradise.

We both regularly enjoy many of the activities that are avalable in this amazing area including: kayaking, horse-riding, boating, tennis, skiing, hiking, bicycling - the list goes on - and we are happy to arrange activities for our guests where requested.

neighborhood_overview:
Sa Riera is one of the largest beaches in Begur, and the closest to the town.
It is excellently located, with the sheltered Port d’Es Pi cove to the right, and the Rei cove to the left . Sa Riera takes its name from a stream dividing the beach in half, it has kept its traditional character with low rise buildings and the pine covered surrounding hills. It offers a range of different sports activities and tourist services.
There are various bars and restaurants to enjoy the gastronomy of the region, and also a few shops, including a supermarket.
From Sa Riera one can walk the costal trail to the beaches of Platja del Racó and Pals.
host_about:
Originally from Barcelona, but I lived many years in the UK and for a few years now I’ve settled down with my husband Richard and our three grown up sons in Besalú, just north of Girona.
I love walking in the nature, practicing yoga and pilates, healthy food and crafts. I adore little villages with cobbled pavements and narrow streets, and balconies full of flowers.  But I also need regular doses of city life!  Shops, bars, cafes, busy streets, and lively markets.
My favourite season is spring, I like it hot and sunny! I love the smell of freshly cut grass and my favourite colour is the tourquoise green-blue of the Costa Brava waters!
I consider myself a social and friendly person, love meeting new people and discovering new places.
I will be delighted to welcome you!

neighborhood_overview:
The Old Town of Girona is considered the historical center of the city, bounded by the medieval city wall, part of which was demolished in the nineteenth century, and is where we find the most important historic and cultural attractions of the city.
The houses on the river Onyar are a sight which must be enjoyed from one of the bridges crossing the river, and we approach the Jewish quarter from the Rambla. In the promenade bustle of visitors and locals, strolling, shopping, resting live.
Once entered in the Jewish Quarter, one of the best preserved in Spain, we can enjoy the historic legacy of the city, letting lose through the narrow streets and right steps, discovering corners, gardens, monuments and churches, between steps. The Cathedral, the church of Sant Feliu, the Arab Baths, Sant Pere de Galligants.

Soy una amante del arte y de la decoración.

Espero os guste el apartamento que ofrezco que he decorado con tanto cariño.

Os espero pronto!

It is a 15 minute walk to the beautiful Sa Tuna cove with its crystal clear water, and cafes and restaurants. Surrounded by wooded hillsides, it is ideal for walks, especially along the Cami De Ronda on the famous "Rugged Coast".

The space
We have a large living room with a small kitchen, a newly refurbished shower room with toilet, one double bedroom and one twin bedded room.
An outside patio - ideal for dining - leads up a few steps to a private large sun terrace with some natural shade, and then onto the large shared pool. Opposite the house is a wooded area and views across the hills with glimpses of the Med.

Guest access

neighborhood_overview:
The "Unique Selling Points" of Tresviso are its quiet setting, its large shared pool, and its proximity to the glorious Costa Brava countryside and, of course, Sa Tuna cove with its quiet, sheltered beach and crystal clear waters. Added to that is the nearby hill top town of Begur - a very special little market town with plenty of excellent restaurants. This is on the Cap de Begur, a small promontory with the idyllic coves and beaches of Playa de Pals, Sa Riera, Aigua Freda, Sa Tuna, Fornells and Aigua Blava.
Further afield are the towns of Figueres and Girona - both about 3/4 hour away, Cadaques - the home of the artist Dali, and not forgetting that Barcelona is only a 90 minutes train ride away and the nearest station is at Flaca (with easy parking) on the Girona road.
host_about:
I'm Graham and Jan is my wife. We're retired and live in North Bedfordshire. Jan was a teacher and I was a school bursar.
Graham loves golf and walking, and Jan loves walking and her allotment. Other than that, our children and 4 grandchildren take a bit of time.
We would like our guests to make full use of our two bedroomed house and its large shared pool. It's set in a delightful part of the Costa Brava, with lots of little coves all offering crystal clear waters, and lots of beautiful walking country. And only about  1 1/2  hours by train to Barcelona!

neighborhood_overview:
Campelles is part of the Ripollès region, in the province of Girona.
It is a very well-preserved natural area with all kinds of fauna, ideal for short excursions along the river, with the option of bathing in its refreshing waters in summer. During the fall, it is a very good place to go looking for mushrooms, or in winter to ski on the nearby slopes of Vall de Núria, La Molina, Masella or Vallter 2000.The town also offers a great variety of local gastronomic products, they highlight its sausages and cheeses, honey or biscuits from Camprodon, near Campelles, are also highly appreciated.

The space
This charming 1200 square meters property, entirely built in traditional Begur stones, is located at the end of a cul-de-sac, and offers privacy and quietness, while being only 1,5km (10-15 minutes walk) from the lovely beach of Sa Riera. It has stunning views on the sea and Medes Islands. The property has been fully renovated in 2010/2011, and additional improvement are made by the owner every year. A main villa, on a level, features 4 bedrooms and 2 bathrooms (1 en-suite), a brand-new extra equipped kitchen, a large dining/living area with fireplace. On the opposite side of the large private swimming pool, another house offers 2 separate bedrooms with 2 en-suite bathrooms, fully renovated in 2017, with ni
neighborhood_overview:
The closest beach (Sa Riera) is formed by the small beach “Port des Pi”, the large beach “Sa Riera” and the small beach “Cala del Rey”. Only 10-15 min walk from the villa, it is one of the largest and most popular beaches of Begur, preserves its traditional character and offers a wide range of sports activities and tourist services.
The area is popular with golfers with a choice of 9 superb course within easy reach of the property. The Costa Brava has just won an award for the best emerging golf destination worldwide by IAGTO. Emporda is a championship course about 15 minutes away; in Pals which is about 10 minutes away there are two good courses both Playa de Pals and Sierres de Pals. Particularly a golfers dream in the autumn and spring months when it is not too hot!

neighborhood_overview:
Empuriabrava sur la Costa Brava, est une agréable zone résidentielle connue également sous le nom de "La Venise espagnole", en raison des quarante kilomètres de canaux qui la parcourent (dont 24 navigables).
C'est la plus grande MARINA d'Europe, avec plus de cinq mille points d'amarrages.
C'est un endroit où il fait bon vivre et qui dispose de plusieurs kilomètres de belles PLAGES.
Quelques activités/équipements/prestations à Empuriabrava (par ordre alphabétique, liste non exhaustive) :
Bowling, équitation, excursion en bateau, golf, gymnase, karting, kite-surf, location de motos, location de vélos, location d'embarcations, mini-golf, plongée sous-marine, randonnée pédestre, tennis, train touristique...

Pour les amoureux de la nature et des balades :
- Promenade sur les CANAUX
Pour admirer les canaux de la ville et ses berges, vous pouvez louer de petites embarcations. Aucun permis n'est nécessaire pour en devenir les capitaines !
- La
host_about:
Bonjour à tous !
Nous sommes Jana et Jean. Nous disposons de deux appartements à Empuriabrava. Nous souhaiterions vous faire profiter de cette belle région de la Costa Brava et de son agréable climat. 
Jana est une femme adorable, très féminine, avec une bonne éducation, sérieuse et consciencieuse dans sa profession mais, surtout, avec une belle joie de vivre ! 
Pour ma part, je crois pouvoir dire que suis quelqu'un de simple, ouvert, travailleur mais sachant également bien profiter des beaux moments de l'existence.

name: Catalan Villa on the Med: Pool, Jacuzzi, Views
description:
Stunning holiday home in Begur, a quaint village 100 miles north of Barcelona. Incredible sea views. Pool, jacuzzi, three sunny terraces, two balconies. Beaches five minutes away. Superbly equipped villa in the coolest village on the Spanish coast. Lots of lovely restaurants, boutiques and bars in the well-preserved village.

Book now for Summer 2023. We are usually fully booked for the high season by the end of January. For summer bookings, we require stays from Saturday to Saturday.

The space
We call it Casa Buenavista because the views are stunning.

We found this house on a whirlwind trip to the Costa Brava in March 2004. We were scheduled to see about ten places that day. This was the third one we visited. We quit looking when we walked onto the terrace and saw the view.

The outlook is not just majestic; it is also a tonic to the soul. Sit on the terrace, sip some Albariño and let the troubles of the world melt away.
neighborhood_overview: We think there’s no nicer place on the Spanish coast.  The Costa Brava (meaning rugged coast) is one of the most beautiful, pollution-free areas that still exist on the Mediterranean. The rocky coves like Aigua Xelida, Sa Tuna, Sa Riera, Platja Fonda and Aiguablava are breathtakingly beautiful.
host_about: I am a retired professor of history at the University of St Andrews and a freelance journalist.  I have rented my villa in Spain to hundreds of happy families over the last 15 years.  There's nothing I enjoy more than hearing how guests enjoy our little corner of paradise.

The space

The private pool (approx. 8m x 4m) with eight sun loungers is in the sun for all o
